user_reviews:
[{"Name":"SoulCurryArt","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWhdI4XBvTt_hb2FS8qvbTFp0uDaG2xUgX_dp11882wvcTrqrEh=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"When a local business not only makes the most amazing food but also goes above and beyond in customer service, you know you’ve hit the jackpot!
We stopped at Roy’s on our way from Victoria to Vancouver after a long day of sightseeing. We reached 10 minutes before closing time, they had already closed the kitchen and were winding up for the day. When I told them I had specially come to sample their Bengali cuisine with my family, all the way from the east coast, they opened their kitchen and hearts for us.
The food was cooked to perfection. We celebrated my husband’s 50th with his favourite; kosha mangsho ( slow cooked goat curry) which reminded me of home. The flaky laccha parantha was perfect with it. 10/10
We had the prawn curry with lime leaves and it was spicy and so so delicious. We washed it down with gur-er rosogolla (cottage cheese balls soaked in a sweet jaggery syrup)and my only regret was that I didn’t pack more to takeaway.
It was an outstanding meal, cooked to perfection, authentic Bengali food in every sense. The staff was extremely helpful and made our dining experience at Roy’s one that was really special.
Thank you Roy’s for bringing the Indian hospitality and food to Canada. You made a lasting impression on us and we can’t wait to come back when we are back on the West Coast.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMun4f_A6fXdDsFxDQUlfcNaEYNAC9ls_SVueYC&fid=0x0:0xb7f0a68c89ea8418"],"When":"2024-8-7"},{"Name":"Pooja Chaudhary","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVikZvhBSYSeJHyC2iVE3uoSeiUL7_8Q-E6SrAo6CM8YBBQWbE=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"TLDR; average food, got food poisoning after.

We came in with high expectations because of the rating, but were quite disappointed with the food - flavors et al. Between the two of us we ordered the Manchurian cauliflower, the paneer peas and a naan. The Manchurian was ok. The paneer was entirely flavorless - the gravy tasted like dal, which was so weird.

After all this, I chalked it up to just picking bad options on the menu. But 30 minutes after, I had an upset stomach and my partner had full blown food poisoning - that has definitely tipped my experience to a negative one.

Service is very nice though. The servers are super attentive and good come about super quickly.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNLHx2eLUo1ZPSAd1tNQ-qWLTwUTOqA815PPjZg&fid=0x0:0xb7f0a68c89ea8418"],"When":"2024-9-14"},{"Name":"Israt Jahan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIUGLh9yB2qVdZGIbYpQJ5Mon3-2NjEqAny7q46XimuvNTnMNA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Dhokar dalna and Prawn Malaikari made our weekend lunch special. Food was less oily,  that's  why we loved it more. Cherry on top was the happy hour deal. Surely coming back again to check on the rest items on the menu. FYI, From meat side, only lamb is served halal.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOaTA_dH6exm13wfzqcji-TrUHuVaWGvzm4SONy&fid=0x0:0xb7f0a68c89ea8418"],"When":"2023-9-30"},{"Name":"Lee Gildemeester","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUmwK5TPiyJO9K2BikS-yqaHifl8H0QHLdeDujEGzwKhWsKSXQ7=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Great food, tasty and consistent. Portions, including the Samosas, are smaller than I'd like. a bit overpriced considering the small portion sizes. 2 people can easily spend $80 with no leftovers. bill didn't reflect the 'buy one get one free' promo on my last visit. should probably be listed as a $$$ not a $$","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Manpreet Dhindsa","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXhVsf4hqwCPRKlTzCNXAyXqeKlgKKkWoEL8_wr-jkyvsKRNWYLGw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Simply fantastic food, menu options and service. So glad this is not just another Indian restaurant. Loved their menu, it's very well thought, curated and executed. Food was excellent, portions sumptuous and taste bang on! Their naans are a must try,  different and best recipe so far. Loved the potato pesto naan, different yet traditional!! Lamb was 👌 👏,  lentil cake curry delicious, lemon rice excellent , cauliflower Manchurian, a hit . Glad we stopped by tonight as we will be back for more moving forward.  What a wonderful team you all have, they were happy and working as a team, both front and back of the house . Keep up the good work guys. You are amazing!!! Thank you for great experience:)","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMEoViXLHjHpyP5gIg4Y1MtjAvzt-wiUG2fQo0G&fid=0x0:0xb7f0a68c89ea8418"],"When":"2021-10-30"},{"Name":"Arun John Varghese","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLVoZlTUN4otj58r2juzAQOie8Enk3IWZUtDNKbsBz_OdbDGA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"One of the best places to have authentic Indian cuisine in Tsawwassen. We were greeted & attended by Ms.Ujala. As her name suggests, Ujala’s enlightening hospitality was really worth mentioning along with the delicious food and quick service. Truly a very good place to spend an evening with good food and good people. Certainly recommend 👍🏽","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOs9GMTi-zI5TPw4Qyeh9TCu9HjaHe6iTCg-riW&fid=0x0:0xb7f0a68c89ea8418"],"When":"2023-7-18"},{"Name":"Rohan Mittra","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKTan-4gipBjSPNNLq7O6nnDAB6h3Ox83_ealwiawyIVYLWvek=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"After a really long trip of BC, I was really craving some good Bengali food. My oh my, did I hit the jackpot. Found Roy’s on Google and jumped at the opportunity. The mochar bora is what I started my Roy’s culinary experience with and it packed a punch right away. Then had the echor chingri which was delicious and finished the main course with some good old kosha mangsho which transported me back to my home in Kolkata. Now comes the best part, they had gur er Roshogolla 😍 I was in food heaven! Thank you so much folks for making my day! Will definitely come back the next time I’m in Vancouver.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO59cFWBcB4fvb3zzlfyy14GoYdf0H1XpHwFupG&fid=0x0:0xb7f0a68c89ea8418"],"When":"2024-4-1"},{"Name":"Ji Luo","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJJDDlwTdksi001rt6rIhoB59jo2HsOkhb0VH7JlXKVGsRC4Q=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Above average food quality and taste, decent service, but the portion is on the short side for each single dish. Nevertheless counting the buy one get one free (dine-in 2-5pm) deal it's really worth it and I recommend a try if you're an Indian cuisine lover.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOvdd3ItBFpEwiw16ge8wvUUTHNiRqTMnQErq6_&fid=0x0:0xb7f0a68c89ea8418"],"When":"2024-4-9"}]

user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Albert Luk","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVaD3o96lx5KFqGPVNTfbIw-nZHFFA950dd8GZz9qbGbOe0Sjog=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Don’t bring your date here: impossible to have a quiet conversation. Music is good though too loud. We made reservations but they placed us in the middle next to a boisterous table. Food: meh. Went with tapas and they were all bland. Server missed the wine order. Dismal experience.  Tacos: just ok, you’re better off going to some place else. Sliders: dry. Cauliflower: ok. Brussels sprouts: average.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM1r7Wwqiy86f9jgEI-tE16xg6t64ucQTH9-VyO&fid=0x0:0x70b2c89c4b724af6"],"When":"2024-8-17"},{"Name":"Tricia S.","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUBIPgdHNtXGMVDBPAiyBZPz5RlbPOO-0QbSlZMCorEUFy6yRE=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"As long-time residents of the South Delta community, my now-husband and I have always valued supporting our local businesses. When planning and hosting our wedding, we sought venues that would not only provide exceptional service but also reflect the warmth and spirit of our hometown. Mario's Kitchen and its neighboring restaurant, Gracie's Next Door, stood out as the perfect choices for our post-ceremony cocktail reception.

Mario's Kitchen has been a staple location for our family dinners and events over the years, and this time, we decided to host at Gracie's Next Door. The outcome was nothing short of spectacular. From the outset, the management and staff demonstrated remarkable dedication and professionalism.

The team at Gracie's Next Door delivered excellent service throughout our event. They were attentive, ensuring that tabs were accurately started for the correct guests and taking the time to remember each guest's name and preferences. The food was absolutely outstanding, with our guests continually commenting on how delicious and plentiful everything was. The impressive spread truly elevated the experience and left everyone delighted.

We were truly amazed by the turnout and the seamless execution of our reception. The hard work and commitment of the staff ensured that our day was flawless and unforgettable. A special thank you to Darren and the entire team at Mario's Kitchen and Gracie's Next Door for their exceptional service and support.

We wholeheartedly recommend Mario's Kitchen and Gracie's Next Door to both locals and visitors in South Delta. These establishments are key spots to wine and dine, offering not only delicious cuisine but also a welcoming and professional environment that makes every occasion special.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMZp_Ndokgi_04wHy3-0IyRHEL344DEmbdSzVAK&fid=0x0:0x70b2c89c4b724af6"],"When":"2024-8-23"},{"Name":"Keith Adler","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV-w0ymVj8anzOJoTo6l50yzn_DFPba_nWtAvCmch_RV1kWDnFy=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Best meal I had in Canada, from several trips. Lots of good options and clear allergen markings. Fantastic service","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPwCuN7xLwxfHJ3vDUHNwcvc1BcpeN1b_y0-9r7&fid=0x0:0x70b2c89c4b724af6"],"When":"2024-10-23"},{"Name":"Dana O'Higgins","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIdr3pjwz6o3aaIhH0k9AWopcCiN5GSus8Q2_EdBH5NrnP6zQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Great spot! The outdoor patios have numerous warming devices so you can sit out and have fresh air and dine even in the winter.

Excellent menu, so many gluten free options, and lots of authentic feeling Mexican items.

I had the roast lamb, it was quite good, topped with and interesting puree and served with nicely brazen potatoes and cauliflower.

Tortilla soup was really good, tostada's and coconut prawns were also really good!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Laline De Guia","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJ9wtiqDL7jFuGd32VGjqy4EYfl8BZ79PuR3ETkSSOu6bVNLw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Came in here last night and the place was packed but they were able to squeeze us in (a group of 7). My 7-year-old niece, who is usually the pickiest of picky eaters, ate like she'd just spent 39 days on Survivor and was rewarded with a feast — just a long way to say the food was fantastic! Our server, Shelby, was an absolute delight. Overall, it was a wonderful experience :)","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Melanie E","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUR0bJcxqNkJt-i1wxCH3EaQXevncA86panZszfT__NAs_0KWRp=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The rating is based on a dine-in dinner experience.

Ambience: 5/5 - A great place to dine with friends and family for special occasions or just because…
Service: 5/5 – our server, Bailey came to check on us often
Food: 5/5 – ordered the halibut burger wrapped in lettuce rather than a brioche bun. It came with potato wedges. The fish was cooked to perfection & didn’t taste dry. The other dish was the seafood linguine with plenty of prawns, scallops & mussels in tomato sauce. We finished the meal off with crème crème brulee. I recommend all 3 dishes. There’s an extensive taco menu. Great choices for vegans and vegetarians.
Value: 5/5 – reasonably priced compared to city prices
Parking: 5/5 – complimentary parking in front

If you’re ever in the neighbourhood in need of a good meal especially before or after a ferry ride, this is the place to go! Can’t wait to come back to try their tacos.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOdVwfN3Ye-oShaogEqjgWSQLCTrViu_VIJjwL-&fid=0x0:0x70b2c89c4b724af6"],"When":"2023-9-22"},{"Name":"Sukhraj Hothi","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWxQjM5nJbgElJc2hyhhoXQyiMBiFOcfOQTg0d9N8DVTMBMUnkcEA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Came here for a cozy brunch on a rainy Sunday; they got heaters and even blankets on the chairs!

The food was great, but I really couldn’t give it 5/5, service was just subpar. Maybe it was just a quiet morning for the place but overall, good food :)

Would come again,","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPeDXW4RyoiTdbRoI9lwaa4Hm7O8_VUEJ_oRoDa&fid=0x0:0x70b2c89c4b724af6"],"When":"2022-7-3"},{"Name":"Jack Canon","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVjiIxAtpA98tHCikn081BC4pndLFCoXumRILc8Dh6dhMHh3qy9=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"January 12th 2024 We had a wedding dinner planned for 20 with the wedding ceremony to take place on the beach in Tsawassen. Unfortunately it was -13°c and a wind of 60KM so at 9am I contacted Michaela and asked if there was any way we could do it at the restaurant. She said yes and Wow it worked out amazing everything was perfect right down to we moved inside they made it just so perfect. And our server Annabel I can't believe how amazing she was handling 20 guests everyone made great comments on the server and Great Food.
I truly cannot thank the whole team at Grace's for making our day perfect from just a simple I Do to a 1st Class wedding Thank You from the bottom of my Heart ❤️  Richard and Tina Glasner","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPF6u2phCG3uyp1FP8NG_R2B5DoyZ5lET_VW9xT&fid=0x0:0x70b2c89c4b724af6"],"When":"2024-1-14"}]

user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Hamed","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjViJ9EznENDd1HeEqpUkYuqmZFdKwptQI-w0AYNvWdb_l07iQpU7w=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The atmosphere was great. The management greeted us warmly. The waiters were very polite and friendly.

The pizza and pasta were both great. Pizza especially was full of toppings. Unlike the classic Italian style which is not as dense in toppings. We loved it though.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNzL21Em97yXFGck6U2k3_dGVBJQVpE1A6xaHfJ&fid=0x0:0x4a25ec699118faf3"],"When":"2024-9-16"},{"Name":"Leasa Ferneyhough","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVyIeO7VzLVo9O3Un3xr2ksgRw0ut6tXtLBY535nxO6cQHWOfU=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Our takeout meal of appetizers and entrees was so delicious. Perfectly cooked, fresh seafood. The bruschetta was to die for. It had a really lovely balsamic reduction on it that was flavourful, but still left room for the fresh tomato and feta to shine as well. Balanced flavours, seasoned perfectly. The team member who greeted us and brought us our order was friendly and quick. We received excellent service, even though it was Saturday night and the place was packed. I ate here 5 years ago on another trip to Delta and can honestly say the consistency of food quality and service was great both visits. A really great restaurant. Thank you!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMuif1-EHcFfV7oMquxibIylA8i46yjNmck7_Gt&fid=0x0:0x4a25ec699118faf3"],"When":"2024-10-1"},{"Name":"Emilia Muirragui","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWVbrBdWMJwAdDmTKF2rqn3OE2f7BKVf4ff7Eui90G41UPNKe7l=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I absolutely love this place! We came across it randomly, as a "near you" recommendation by Google Maps. And let me tell you that the food was SPECTACULAR! I had a special menu item: a Salmon Risotto and it was absolutely delicious. My husband ordered a quesadillas from the happy hour menu and they were really good and very abundant. I loved the atmosphere of this place, fancy but still not so fancy that you actually have to plan to dress up for it, very cozy, and they even have blankets if you decide to sit outside on their patio. I cannot recommend it enough and I cannot wait to go back for more.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOxjpG0lZT289xitiw9JXKe30lXckpwUutLhbPk&fid=0x0:0x4a25ec699118faf3"],"When":"2024-5-31"},{"Name":"prabhjot Sohi","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLNCwEpx0kUHz8GSEDHGZH3WZ7euyF1v5CYXR_LA2y5mgm9pg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I would highly recommend this place. The service and food both were great. Jackson was really helpful, polite and his services were amazing.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPHVObrledjY4PSr4f5orPixingObDYWX0xCmwc&fid=0x0:0x4a25ec699118faf3"],"When":"2024-11-16"},{"Name":"Charn Thandhi","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUAuCLfNf1I-ocypWvJIt2QP7eekFSmny-FkhPG2ukh8w4IUMbV=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"First time visiting this place with my wife and our good friends and I loved it. Never tried a Mediterranean pizza (not shown here) and I loved it as well as this Chicken Romano which I split with my wife. The food was delicious and I would absolutely recommend this place 👍👌","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipME9oPHhiivSjx3ceSanWL86eVgfBPboigrqx1R&fid=0x0:0x4a25ec699118faf3"],"When":"2024-8-6"},{"Name":"Mohammadreza Behnejad","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXbfFjgusvHBDGevsLnSFlRH6CqkrxaSYgN1dtBgif3eqTdhnw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Very good vibe in this place. Staff were professional and nice.

Food tastes delicious. They offer two size of portions. Larger size is $3-4 extra and can be shared for two.

A group of 10 people non of us could finish the full portion dish.

It took almost an hour to serve the food. To be fair maybe it was because of our larger table.

Cajun chicken Alfredo linguine and Lasagna was absolutely delicious.

Overall very satisfied with taste and quality.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO8nLXgqUlXLNwCwtiC-W9j_VPh_bNEUELF_Nw&fid=0x0:0x4a25ec699118faf3"],"When":"2023-5-17"},{"Name":"kayla Sabbe","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWpSiKbA3LurEcnUJo1uQLIuFZ7jgMo04Ijp9XqL_9LhSPx0Kg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"My husband and I dined here for the first time. We had lunch on the patio which was incredibly clean and comfortable. They offer blankets on the seats if it's cold out which was a very nice touch. It's hard to find a place to eat where the service is 10/10 all around nowadays but our server was so attentive, incredibly kind and just all around a pleasure. She was so good I called Mario's after we left just to let the manager know how she did. I wish I had her name but I hope she got kudos because a lot of younger servers nowadays just don't care much.

The food was also a 10/10.. as a vegetarian I got so many options to choose from as the server went out of her way to explain that I could get almost anything on the menu without meat. The goat cheese salad is a MUST try and the meat lasagna was so hearty, my husband loved it.

We thought this place was fancy so maybe the portions would be small and prices high for quality over quantity but no... you get quantity and quality for a good price. Everything about this place was so inviting, we will be back.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOAqVNqpPDLIkzghkw1-AudsPMk7H60y565KsPG&fid=0x0:0x4a25ec699118faf3"],"When":"2023-9-3"},{"Name":"Luan Reisdoerfer Cardoso","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXJy4d20z2cS8v7rChMGw3z6muiCCzuI588LnB8lkU6JnQBfH_g=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Amazing experience! We were looking for a new restaurant to try, and we couldn't have chosen a better one. Attentive service, comfortable patio, and mouth-watering food! I couldn't recommend it more. We are definitely going to return.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPbaFqcQr2taez51BVtJ5aSZBSMINB8VTL5eDWh&fid=0x0:0x4a25ec699118faf3"],"When":"2024-2-27"}]

[{"Name":"Nelli S","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUYqdeN-R5LF87KTDEqaw6sJisI0ncLfXvpqJx3EleF1LdBqzPr=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Great service, delicious food, very nice atmosphere. I recommend to come here on their Happy hours (2-6pm). Also we enjoyed Festival of Lights.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO4eeZkpUScusoGh05YtxXBhsxrART7364I5-BJ&fid=0x0:0xe3178a02fcde58a6"],"When":"2024-12-8"},{"Name":"Tuna Canoe","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIxuMgPtlPZ-uE8yNHSTq_Z5MJ1hEv_H44UTamA4NFV6LAU3JU=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"To avoid the impatient backlog of traffic coming off the busy Tsawwassen Ferry & Causeway, Take the 2nd exit ( turn right on 52nd street ) and take your very next right again . Here you will find a little gem called  ~ Pat Quinn’s Restaurant & Bar. ~ Just take an hour to relax and enjoy an amazing experience here while you let the traffic congestion subside .

I can write a whole bunch of amazing and good things, but this will be way too long !

The bottom line, amazing food , huge portions , great views, cool atmosphere. But honestly, the main reason we will return here again is because our service was an 11/10 ( our server Bryn ) You can have a meal pretty much anywhere , but we definitely will be back because of her amazing service today !

Thank you so much again Bryn !

Updated Oct.2nd lunch : with more pics : Salmon & Cod cakes , and Hawaiian pizza ( with Jalapeños) Outstanding service again !!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOfaecDlvFPPoRaFJDgZPHKOqJbBWt-bGwcXwVq&fid=0x0:0xe3178a02fcde58a6"],"When":"2024-8-16"},{"Name":"Shela Yuen","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLxRFX65srqH3-KccY4AUhBn3sK5L-aeATFZiVVf12Fx1nVd4g=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I am here for the third time! Rigatoni bolognese and fries are exceptional. Great atmosphere, nice view. With happy hour’s pricing, this place has become a must-go every time I come to Tsawwassen.

And today I found another reason that this placw is a must go — Mr. Tom Kwan’s services! He truly made us felt very warm and welcomed. Despite the restaurant’s so busy and probably under-staffed due to BC day, he still served us with unmatched hospitality. We are truly thankful for Tom’s services. Will definitely come again!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP-bcYoWbHS9EB_J9tZ205gW7KzP-UTkjxjMfsr&fid=0x0:0xe3178a02fcde58a6"],"When":"2024-8-5"},{"Name":"Dawn Mist","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVyR-na2sQcGqnSW-JxTn27RMX1oocQ3hojpV86Eb8qwbPHRL0=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"Been here several times and it is begrudgingly inconsistent. One time we ordered a couple of the beef dips and they forget the dip part. Sometimes the pizza tastes like pizza, other times there is no sauce on it. Very up and down, very inconsistent. We keep giving it a shot hoping that consistency might come back.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN2-WG9SE8XYfMbJBNz_nnPXMCCVdouQOCJp-H5&fid=0x0:0xe3178a02fcde58a6"],"When":"2024-11-15"},{"Name":"Jagdeep Chahal","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJaLw0I3vM9nfwmD3H8tXGPJeDG7bGdT8tRmfrHe4cLBPb2ag=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"One of my favourite restaurants. The food is always on point and the staff are always amazing. I was finally able to book reservations for Brunch with Santa and it did not disappoint. My nieces had the best time and created a wonderful memory for them. They’re already asking to come back next year and I think it might just become one of our Christmas traditions. There were no crazy wait times for the buffet and everything was always topped up.  Also, I loved how Santa and his elf came around to each table to chat with the families.  A great experience overall!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Thedishdetective Lala","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKD_tj6k6xpF8R8uVmPtHQuGBgjvefVOKaKmqeE1mkWnmvdyA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Pat Quinn’s Restaurant & Bar
Location: 5133 Spring Blvd #100, Tsawwassen, BC V4M 0A6

Clam Chowder
The clam chowder had a good portion size, though it was a bit runny for my taste. However, the seasoning was quite good. Overall, I’d give it a 7 out of 10.

Butternut Squash
The butternut squash was delicious, with excellent seasoning. I enjoyed it a lot and would rate it an 8 out of 10.

Crab Cake
The crab cake was well-seasoned, fried, and crispy. It was decent but didn’t stand out as much as other dishes. I’d give it a 6 out of 10.

Mussels
The mussels were a highlight of the meal. They were well-seasoned, had a good portion size, and tasted really good. I would rate them a 9 out of 10.

Steak
Unfortunately, the steak was disappointing. It was hard and chewy, despite ordering it rare. The only redeeming part of the dish was the gravy. I’d rate the steak a 3 out of 10.

Service
The service was good. The server was nice and attentive, earning a 7 out of 10.

Venue
The venue is really nice and cozy, providing a comfortable and pleasant dining atmosphere.

Price
The price was reasonable, earning a 3 out of 5.

Verdict
Overall, despite some hits and misses, I would come back for another visit.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMeCj6ISD-0mJyzQmc7SZNL2Tv9-9Pe9ea0Um9N&fid=0x0:0xe3178a02fcde58a6"],"When":"2024-6-5"},{"Name":"Susan Ninow - Realtor","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJLhR2xv519-zmTSY9obAY5M46DsiXjVum-r80rdag4lo3d0rCn=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Enjoyed an early evening with friends at Pat Quinn’s. The food and atmosphere is excellent. Loved the views of the golf course! Happy hour offers excellent value! The Happy Hour spring salad and burger is delicious!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMjRADCZiBMAlnAtraWZANwPbW7F1fGHHIla1Ke&fid=0x0:0xe3178a02fcde58a6"],"When":"2024-6-30"},{"Name":"Munro Stuff","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWj0Wcuk6ox5dfAeJ4fAaMbhX_F-nzzt3p5oc_f0hBd0NpbGSM=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Had a good brunch here. The non-alcoholic green tea lemonade with mango was really tasty without being sweet. Excellent yam fries, perfectly cooked. The Tuna Buddha Bowl had all the right ingredients but the tuna needed a marinade and the bowl needed a better/more dressing. Good service and lovely festive decor.","Images":null,"When":""}]

user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Bradley Jones","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWQSjOdt_NCThfrgQQSPCAI9c1m2q4Cia70lWTZMyAGLNwKu8R3=s120-c-rp-mo-ba7-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"We stopped by Browns Socialhouse on our way to the ferry terminal and were pleasantly surprised by how much we enjoyed the experience. The atmosphere was lively yet relaxed, making it the perfect place to unwind before continuing our journey. I opted for the Spicy Ginger Beef, and true to its name, it packed just the right amount of heat. The flavors were bold and balanced, with the perfect level of spice to keep things interesting. Pairing it with a crisp, chilled Pinot Grigio was an excellent choice, as the wine’s refreshing notes perfectly complemented the dish.

Our server was fantastic—attentive, polite, and genuinely made us feel welcome. It’s always nice to have staff that checks in without being overbearing, and she struck that perfect balance. Service like this really elevates the dining experience.

Whether you’re in a rush or looking for a place to linger, Browns Socialhouse is a great option. It was the perfect pit stop before catching our ferry, and I’m already looking forward to coming back!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO5mXhWow9kivaMbpj3Y17Q4QYlioKH-GjLJOIg&fid=0x0:0x7ceb3fe94e40acff"],"When":"2024-10-19"},{"Name":"Wayne Lav","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUk880jfctdjiDn4tRAvocN5rCVUdtgArCHWFDiv2yxg-QvIz4L=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Browns in Tsawwassen is one of the few spots open past 10 pm, making it a solid choice for late-night drinks and dining. The restaurant offers both indoor and covered outdoor seating, with a pleasant ambiance throughout. There's ample seating inside and plenty of parking available outside. The staff is attentive and friendly, adding to the positive experience. The menu is straightforward, and the food is flavorful. TVs above the bar provide a chance to catch some sports while you eat, but the atmosphere leans more towards a restaurant than a bar.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPUX1fIVQUgoi3RX8zjIwyqv0wmK6w7yDoyEikN&fid=0x0:0x7ceb3fe94e40acff"],"When":"2024-8-4"},{"Name":"Trevor Moore","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVUwW9-UDVr0ZHxqbBSs5pfX74SSAUW25zvwcLqgNHWCSwKlj4M=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We ended up going earlier on a sunday evening and there was lots of seating. We ordered the Blackened Chicken Cowboy salad and a burger with yam fries, both tasted good. There was an issue with our order, but it was taken care of quickly.
The location, while attached to the Coast Hotel, is not accessable through the hotel.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPK3oTxITnPt8PEbHL7gLlZtsygYZUT1Vh5sGK-&fid=0x0:0x7ceb3fe94e40acff"],"When":"2024-7-24"},{"Name":"Anthony Cooper","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXCp3vRQvxR895Kdykt6EtzWcDiPpiIUgZ_b2lDj2Bq3nOjUuFY=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Calamari, Dry Pork Ribs and Hot wings were amazing! Even had a personal touch with my name on the take out bag! Thank you chefs and hostesses! You guys are awesome!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Mark D","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocK42E2QGIhGIbhXbF-hih0k9Xo5rh8B_sd8T3bpl0r9T0JBvRg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Just got done with happy hour nachos and a single amber ale...

The happy hour nachos are very very small...i get it to some degree...happy hour is tidbits...but definitely expected more substantial than this

$23 total with 15% tip for a beer and very very small serving of nachos...

Would have been much happier in the $15 to $17 range.

I evaluate every place i go and ask myself if i would return...probably not, just a bit on expensive side for simple snack","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Laurie Rankin","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUY_vttpoD4NVvddZfoKf53X65GbQUu156AJtSk0jSr4E1qRntVnQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We had dinner at Brown's Social House which right beside the Coast Tsawwassen Inn.

We had never been there before and were a bit overwhelmed by the loud music and numerous TV screens.

However, we were very happy with the prompt attention from our server, Michael.

We started with yam fries, served with a delicious chipotle sauce. For dinner we chose Southwest Chicken Bowls.

The food was fresh, colourful and nicely plated.

After we relaxed, we did not notice the music so much.

Having a professional server like Michael enhanced our overall experience.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMr32qaZ6i25jBp4lVCZd6eBtrdV00EQwDT_CnZ&fid=0x0:0x7ceb3fe94e40acff"],"When":"2023-4-12"},{"Name":"Chris L","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIlo27yi0c3tMg1MEFW8gltVROJwlBrQGtk927fnMS7KkAAA0UJ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"I frequently stop here for lunch if Im working in the area.

The food is great. Although this time I tryed the dry ribs, my only complaint is there wasnt much rib lol.

The service is top notch, the ladys are always lovely and helpfull.

This is also one of my favourite patios to enjoy a cold one one.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPnFMKjTCUdUB-2jXjFbEsLaNss5S8AW0vmCx7Q&fid=0x0:0x7ceb3fe94e40acff"],"When":"2021-6-24"},{"Name":"Brian - TGR","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUzC6iHnlfyEU-aB2UYUDobSOZA5Wfs8E2KRx4-J5jcYpXSPaQ2Zw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba8-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Exceptionally friendly service, really good food and the indoor patio was very enjoyable.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN3OLZfPss1zuZHY6jPl0PjPSABnPN-A5UoySUw&fid=0x0:0x7ceb3fe94e40acff"],"When":"2024-2-15"}]

Smoothies were rich and delicious.  Breakfast wrap was very good.  Tons of knick knacks and trinkets so make sure you explore the boutique!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Dylan H","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXp8Q5G9Taq1gORBDAR-0-q3Mif_1ZcyMswj7JniTLVWiiAbmHA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Beach Grove Cafe is the cutest coffee shop ever! They have an adorable boutique inside, with really cool finds, consisting of clothing, jewellery, home decor, and more. They have a vast selection of drinks, pastries, food, and ice cream. Their caramel macchiato is legitimately the best I've ever had, and their breakfast sandwiches and paninis are so good. They are extremely pricey for a coffee shop, but honestly worth it!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOzYIvDlPJ7KKmM8Ptu1j-9juenZhNsyWwK15gx\u0026fid=0x0:0x99224c2ac42c4a58"],"When":"2023-7-3"},{"Name":"Richard J Bergeron","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXZExnbUKFKvplHQ_0M_2nTN2L_GFTHbWz1_5aOGcpxIqn_GckSKQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Fun little cafe with souvenirs,  knick knacks , light lunch assortments , coffee , teas, paninnis , ice cream , etc . 7 or 8 outside seating available.  Right on Beach Grove Road near dike parking at bottom of 12th Ave . Busy place with locals . Had an Italian  Panonni . Was real good . Here again for an iced mocha frap. You have to stop here if you're comming or leaving Centennial Beach.\nStopped in for vanilla bean frap after bike ride to boundary bay  , Centennial beach . Such a nice ride and neat place for a coffee . Gals are great . Patio area outside makes for pleasant stop . (June 8, 22)","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP1DI9qugGNJY_gehFN_RWh1HO8g51mUkBPGxM_\u0026fid=0x0:0x99224c2ac42c4a58"],"When":"2021-6-27"},{"Name":"Michael Elliott","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUFrS4btCgjcGvF721LjucQ4camtRW09Zhys3iGwho34GYEqJaG=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Beach grove cafe is one of my favourite spots in Delta. The staff there are always kind and the service is great. The coffee is solid which is a must as I’d say I’m quite picky about that. Not to mention the amount of goodies they have for sale. Lots of products that make for great gifts. Highly recommend!","Images":null,"When":""}]

user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Alex Thornton","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIqxhEuh7iMg1REQztI_a_NmEsojkE3hjn3QZVAdAdUeR_q5g=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Willing to remove the review if not the correct place. In memory, this has always been the Centennial Beach Cafe/"the only place to get food and ice cream". There are however multiple listings across different websites, which show the same photo and menu but have a different name and disconnected phones. This phone number exists, connection is very poor. Unable to report food poisoning, and inquire if cross contamination is contributing.

Food taste: decent. It was acceptable chicken strips and fries, difficult but possible to mess up. Decent price (~$10) and quick service (midday midweek).","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Martin Urban","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXml4QRvTUaJIyaJ-ZUsBBE6AKLU5lKvyna3vp5WxSaWzOYBzM=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Whoever is managing this establishment needs to have a serious look at their operation. Understaffed. Very long wait time. Food could barely be called food. Chicken nuggets overcooked on outside and mushy inside. Guessing oil was too hot? Burger meat was so cheap.. then poorly cooked.. grey, cold and mushy. Fries.. which I cannot believe could be messed up, were raw in some.. cold and soggy. You could hear the poor staff slamming the microwave over and over trying to get orders out and keep the mush warm. Waiting for order you could hear server constantly tell customers they were out of everything. Bought food for children but after trying my own then inspecting theirs I couldn't in any right mind let them eat it.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Lance Kersey","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWR3WRn7HK2MQheFyDOVZykp-TWmPuOU3RYPYGWUvPDx5hFgCiG=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"They had sandwiches on the menu with grill marks, I thought they were paninis. What I got was a sandwich grilled just long enough to leave marks, but the ingredients inside were cold and cheese unmelted. The ham was a single 1/4" thick slice instead of sliced thin like normal. Like how do you screw up a ham and cheese panini so badly?","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Sherryl Jane","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocITtNJZ4YTk6ZBZiEJOQnw31bf9k2QsOEpFwY_Oya8-rbrYWg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Was told the kitchen service was closed by management just as I got to the front of the line to order. Only drinks and ice cream available. Pretty frustrating since I heard the lady right before me give a full order complete with fish and chips, drinks and burgers.  This was on a sunny weekend in the summer at about 1pm - so lunch rush. Kitchen was to remain closed for up to an hour because they had "too many orders to go through".

I see another reviewer posted 5 hrs ago about being told wraps all of a sudden not being available (p.s. they were available until I got to the front of the line).

Little ones did not have their picnic and had to leave the beach to get food.  There was no way we were driving in and out for food to deal with finding parking and setting up on the beach again.

Ownership needs to address this as they lost quite a bit of business with such poor planning. Who closes their kitchen in the middle of a lunch rush?","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"H N","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUTZ8cYDAqXtEuYt1yP_KsOvkuqkfDpZ-PQ6vd6BeFrSLl_lJSAPQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Prices could be better, but because of its prime location, it's a popular spot for beachgoers to grab a quick bite or a cold drink. There's also an indoor seating area.

My iced coffee ($3.55 plus tax) was a little acidic but hit the spot on a hot day. Loved how it came with a paper straw :)","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Alina P.","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIlpcCKdtSIxZ4i-IvD0ozIIbEce-uA8ASaPlBoDa09u5pUD0w=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Terrible customer service and dishonest employees. I asked for chicken wrap, but girl replied that they don’t do wraps at all today. But that was untruth because my friend ordered the same wrap 10 mins ago. So I asked girls to be honest with their customers,so their next answer was that they stopped doing wraps right now as they don’t have tortillas. So moral of the story is that I have received awful service from the dishonest employees. My advise to the owner: please keep an eye on your employees and make sure that they don’t lie to the customers.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Lisa Larsen","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXnPzCzQMxVOxKQMAhw9NqJPG_K0ievwf8eyJ2KBHF-23iJcWld=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Very disappointed
Cheese burger - without cheese …..
5 very small pieces of lettuce and
the burgers was cold
Overpriced and very long waiting time","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"T Y","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWwgX8yJBJckAWHJheXZWbhS6lYPCLfaTez8ZmiU8lmWGnXTEOgEw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Honestly not too bad for park concession. Prices aren't cheap but quality is way better than what Vancouver Park Board concession offers.

Their poutine was quite big and actually enjoyable.","Images":null,"When":""}]

user_reviews:
[{"Name":"DLH","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKNxoVJChN19TlxEyh2PqXcySZWcsWGp-pw0aGewSStRgeU=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Edit Oct. 27/23:

Return trip on a sunny morning, saw 5-6 planes coming and going.
We ordered 2 items to share for “breakfast” …Denver Omelet $19.95 and The Flying Club $18.95. The club was so huge with generous fillings that we took 1/2 home. Comes with fries or salad.

Happy to see Tina and Chris again, she’s a riot!

Oct. 21/2023:
Have heard good things about this restaurant for quite awhile.

Stopped in for brunch on our way back from Ladner and so glad we did!

Service from Tina and Chris was excellent and quick on a busy Saturday.
We ordered Eggs Benedict ($17.95), Crispy Chicken Burger ($18.50). Corned Beef on Rye ($17.50) and a coffee ($4.50).

Prices are a little high but the value was in the meals, coffee is still free refills.

There is a patio area on the airport taxi side where you can watch small aircraft’s and sometimes helicopters taxi in so seat facing that area. Kids would love it especially on a sunny day!

The restaurant is located inside the airport, we asked someone in the free parking area as first-timers we were unfamiliar.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNdzcEcSAUfhZVMqbTYg7F26xlOxWI3hlCm6YE&fid=0x0:0xbe1267c3150ee48b"],"When":"2023-10-24"},{"Name":"Nikolas Patentalakis","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVkK6kpPZmsqugkZHHHUTudWmaHcTBZOTH5jIJfhMtjzp1O_Vk=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Nice and relaxed place for food and talk. The taste was great, the service was friendly, good selection if you're in the area.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMJP40qEUUsJs-DqxJejJLNzNrZX5czXYRW6QWr&fid=0x0:0xbe1267c3150ee48b"],"When":"2024-5-15"},{"Name":"Micaela Robinson","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV2QksgdiepfAQ10tl72lYcRqkt6l1FugMIhmMIfzOnP4rJ1IYySg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Nice average restaurant, food is ok, pub style.  Service was great 👍.
The best part about the restaurant was the patio where you can eat and watch the planes come and go, and it's quiet frequent !

Not the best bang for your buck when it comes to the food.  However....the fries are amazing !
(Beer seemed flat and my son's chicken strips were way over done)
We will go back again.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNYRyIUETYRss89MdHg001CXwD9ChidMTVBI0aP&fid=0x0:0xbe1267c3150ee48b"],"When":"2021-7-8"},{"Name":"Karen W","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIZZPfpr3QNA42Rvf5GRma8e9wVZe75RxS8Wiz-RehL8Z3PSw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Food was yummy.  Waitress was super nice.  Clean spacious and great view of the planes

Update:  went again for mother's Day. It was busy but the service was excellent.  Food is yummy and good portions","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNl3V8jEm1Cm3oGJ3AJ3X83MjQle3bV1dUbxZYs&fid=0x0:0xbe1267c3150ee48b"],"When":"2024-5-15"},{"Name":"J","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWDTN1lhnYS5iEP8rL2hX6NJWGP7creXX64ESId7jrGtvi6HN4=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Friendly service, delicious hot food, decent prices. I've been there multiple times and always enjoy the experience!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"P","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJUUm8E0pJaPEFyir8aWMwdTk0hmE9aJw9Stux9y1rNRtE68A=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"This place was really well staffed. Good food, not too pricy and it seems like a popular breakfast spot but I can't comment on the lunch or dinner fare.

Sounds like they have a decent wing Wednesday deal w pints at $5.

If you don't live in S.Delta however I'm not sure you'd find the destination to be worth the trip unless you come here for more than the food.

Its worth checking-out if you are in the area but very much feels like a restaurant tacked onto the end of a quiet terminal at an airport.

It should be noted that the service here was far friendly, fast and attentive compared to what I have received at restaurants in well located venues.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNOwshIYECAEATB6k8tB-4er1CKJu5z6I2RBmPO&fid=0x0:0xbe1267c3150ee48b"],"When":"2018-5-1"},{"Name":"Roberta Jansen","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXKH87Hd_iQysIPycT0E4kbf-VLo-hJsPyz-0iW67QQxFQNCRFq=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Always a good place to come to. Has a bit of a diner feel to it in terms of the food. It's good for the whole family. Reservations on the weekend are probably a good idea especially with current covid in-person dinning limitations.

It is located right inside Boundary Bay airport so you can sit inside or outside and watch planes and helicopters come and go.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNbhAw4o9HcG23xdgU-iToq7vrOlE8lBPD2XxH2&fid=0x0:0xbe1267c3150ee48b"],"When":"2021-6-20"},{"Name":"Westbank Harvest Pure Fruit Juice","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUW1ZWYhDij58pE8I9cJAuHO53WkHTFafQwt-rH-1xgkBgAHi8n=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"This is my second attempt at the Skyhawk. I am firmly of the opinion that for the great cost that it takes to travel out to venues for meals overall (time, travel, fuel, meal, taxes, etc.). So here’s my rating.

* Cost and Value
Cost seems slightly higher than necessary. When I was young it was a quarter for a coffee and that wasn’t that long ago! $4.25 plus tax for a single, no-refill coffee is outrageous. French toast (on this visit) was a decent size and tasty. But still feels about $3 overpriced.

* Customer Service
The service here knocks two stars off. Both of my visits the servers were snippy, abrupt and had so little patience that they wouldn’t stand for ten seconds to wait for change or an order to be made. Entirely uncooperative, very surface polite…but eye rolling etc = management needs to immediately give a customer service lesson to most of the staff. The server was totally unwilling to discuss dietary requirements, minor modifications or to check on food allergy concerns. If I was the manager of this place I would have fired the server on the spot. They were all old enough to know better and regardless of the difficulty of the customers they may deal with, in an almost empty place I expected MUCH better decorum.

* Enjoyment and Presentation
The food was good, and presented decently. I would say there is a strong disconnect on what Canadian culture currently is, as vegetarian options were few and both the “veggie” soups when I went had meat bases! How disconnected from the food industry trends is the cook? Other than the rude server and a lack of options or cooperation, this rating is below average. Still passable if you need to have a filling meal while nearby.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNglz6VQRc8uX1Ev_WYLtrshL2SZ-GXuvnIuydR&fid=0x0:0xbe1267c3150ee48b"],"When":"2022-6-16"}]

[{"Name":"Jerry Yao","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIkwf2E1WF8z--h8mFLrUAWr1RNYrZKAAKQBGFCgReDiNF86w=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Found fish bone in salmon dish. Plate is icy cold for main course. Spaghetti and rice becomes watery after touching the cold plate. Chef should be aware of this. Food portion is good, environment is fine, service is also good. But still lot of things to improve.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOsHPgsrCS8L-_GUdwwqmlGf3AzybnLpW34vUI3&fid=0x0:0xef2f97c42e16e3e5"],"When":"2024-9-2"},{"Name":"Thedishdetective Lala","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKD_tj6k6xpF8R8uVmPtHQuGBgjvefVOKaKmqeE1mkWnmvdyA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"**Location:** 1602 4949 Canoe Pass Way, Tsawwassen

**Clam Chowder**
- **Rating:** 8/10
The clam chowder was impressive, with a rich, creamy texture that wasn't watery at all. There was a generous amount of clam, which added to the overall flavor and satisfaction.

**Calamari**
- **Rating:** 5/10
The calamari was fairly standard and didn't stand out much. While the portion size was generous, it was a bit too salty for my taste. It was well-fried but lacked any unique flavors or seasonings.

**Steak**
- **Rating:** 6.5/10
The steak was reasonably good for the price, offering a decent cut of meat. However, it could have benefited from more seasoning to enhance the flavor. The accompanying vegetables were slightly undercooked, which detracted from the overall dish.

**Price**
- **Rating:** 2/5
- **Notes:** The pricing was quite cheap for the quality of food served. While some dishes were enjoyable, the low cost was a pleasant surprise compared to the overall dining experience.

**Ambience**
The ambience of the restaurant was nice and cozy, creating a welcoming atmosphere. The decor was pleasant and added to a comfortable dining experience.

**Service**
The service was good. The staff was attentive and courteous, ensuring that we had everything we needed throughout our meal.

**Verdict:** Will come back again.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPwnUhv8otttaLvfhmouNIkPuhjci9JvsRZyzmG&fid=0x0:0xef2f97c42e16e3e5"],"When":"2024-5-17"},{"Name":"Teresa Wright","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocL98sa5_1FmXtHLNNF3WDAOGgI03qDcyVGoMEnhGH4FWHfuSw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I came here after I got off the ferry on Wednesday, October 16th. I was greeted by a very nice young woman. She suggested a couple of things for me, and in the end, I went with the two stones burger. It was juicy and piping hot served with crispy fries and house salad. I would eat here again! The server was super friendly and outgoing!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN_zdFXA68q5boYFlJFuk_xJYZ1QV5b748rdXr5&fid=0x0:0xef2f97c42e16e3e5"],"When":"2024-10-17"},{"Name":"Greg Leo","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWm8ssH7mLognVswOCUTCA_m_WUoavv1VB46ZtNXUUngffyGHMZ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Always pleasant..
Always delicious..
The 2Stones burger is da bomb..
Would luv it if they got Beck's and Guinness non alcohol beers in..hint hint
One of the only restaurants I eat in South Delta ..
Thanks for being an awesome place !","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Rebecca Kyriakou","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXFRK8XemYLbguyv8cIkBYTm6iiXr_JMZgzXGoSkEs5YghyEVk=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Just finished lunch Two Stones Grill here in Tsawwassen and what a good choice it was. The food was fabulous! Starter Calamari and then the prawns in butter and lemon pepper was Devine. My husband chose the Two Stones Burger. It was a rustic, hand made patty that was just right (his words😂). I would HIGHLY recommend anyone stopping in here for lunch or dinner. They have some amazing daily specials!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP28m2IHTtF2uaOMJDFTnietx2R6vjWUgpKlQEE&fid=0x0:0xef2f97c42e16e3e5"],"When":"2024-4-29"},{"Name":"Michael Scarn","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLAUdj_jT_b5wqz1YfQq7yKNPPnDMs3mF_DB5Qfrce33dBwSQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"We ordered the chicken souvlaki meal which was a part of their 7 items for $11 promotion and were thoroughly disappointed. Just some white rice and a single chicken skewer. It’s not worth any additional words - just look at the picture and decide if it’s for you!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNo3WAjQ9KAuSEPuSSHHlFGTBmUxjEr-clvFYVW&fid=0x0:0xef2f97c42e16e3e5"],"When":"2024-11-25"},{"Name":"Bernie","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVPXTBFQGy4UZogf6r0hGxUGZ8fvtwePPN5iicbAtQksaWtpwOP=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"After shopping at the Tsawwassen Mall, we try to find a new place for dinner and found the ‘Two Stone Grill’.  We got the Crispy Calamari, Chicken Souvlaki meal (with Caesar salad & pita bread) and the New York Steak & Prawns (with Caesar Salad). They have really good food choices, super delicious and reasonably priced.

Daily lunch specials are truly inviting.  A week later, I tried their Lunch Specials. We tried the Fettucini Alfredo, Chicken Tenders and Broccoli Soup with Caesar Salad and drinks for $12.00 each. It's all deliciously yummy and in big shareable servings. Aside from the regular menu choices, they offer good deals for Dinner 2 Course meals inclusive of drinks and ‘to go’ meals.

The dining place is small and has a cozy ambiance. Great place for couples on dates. I suggest making reservations because this place is mostly full.

Jessie, the serving staff is very friendly and attentive. Service is amazing. Parking is not a problem. They’re closed on Sunday.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO_93_g0m9ZBTznOj0OyGEucmUMSgUP5_lKQoSy&fid=0x0:0xef2f97c42e16e3e5"],"When":"2023-5-16"},{"Name":"Jesse","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJSDyGy576NjOpFot9rCBdIpO7u4qZP6Qzr6EXuEXmqpkbcdQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I am blown away !!! I just ordered a few orders of the spaghetti special’s and a couple of burgers and they were SO GOOD !!! I can’t believe how good these burgers are !! Tastes like a homemade patty not a cheap frozen one like everywhere else.  The bun was fresh and delicious!!! And the spaghetti! It is also delicious again tastes like a homemade sauce not the usually generic tasting one that every restaurant seems to use including Boston pizza.   This place is really really good.  Great prices and great food.   I will be back all te time now cheers guys great work !!!  Sorry burger didn’t lAst long enough for the picture.  It was too good !!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO8eL8tDEHp5D4B7j-K8PMAOmEaaQgVt_leLh7v&fid=0x0:0xef2f97c42e16e3e5"],"When":"2024-2-14"}]

It’s full of flies and bugs when we opened the bin.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO0gRcdBIq39MbXjx7eUt7X-MUeQj4EIDOZ_OsO&fid=0x0:0x18736defa4210a3c"],"When":"2024-9-8"},{"Name":"sanjin ramovic","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWWao3NCDoBfu96Y6YVIck2LSuOpB-Wbt71v94bbUF_9zLIh6UJQA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"Overpriced and underwhelming food. Incredibly slow service - it took 25 minutes to make 1 order of fish and chips with onion rings.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMmztxvke202YApEdqKkBT6b2e0Jzznkz7HF-Sn&fid=0x0:0x18736defa4210a3c"],"When":"2024-8-5"},{"Name":"Ryan C","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIoB010mjExiMk0IEVaLXZGgdqqWzSof9Q9bpDYlfbovE1_fQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Would give negative stars if I could. Worst, most disrespectful customer service I have ever seen. Ordered a $25 two piece halibut and chips (same price as sit down fish and chips restaurant) and proceeded to gag and be sick on the beach as it tasted like I had swallowed old fish oil. When I brought this to their attention I was given attitude, openly mocked by their staff and patronized. No offer to make it right, credit the food (which was thrown out), or even an apology.

Even as I wrote this I can’t believe the horrid service there. AVOID this place at all costs, so many other local places that offer take out on the way to the beach, that don’t treat (over)paying customers like pieces of trash.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Daniel Nielsen","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocI6bdcMoGqlBHUE76VBmrvHXekqDHiacpzGOEzxRU93ZEnRrQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"I got a one piece halibut and chip for $20 , there was no fish just Fried battered","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPC6VU5ipsU4bTkVthNG7H9yjV30hEWLUXJBHQp&fid=0x0:0x18736defa4210a3c"],"When":"2023-6-24"},{"Name":"Richard J Bergeron","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXZExnbUKFKvplHQ_0M_2nTN2L_GFTHbWz1_5aOGcpxIqn_GckSKQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Little slow cause of one person cooking and one taking order . user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Chris Falskow","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWDHYLkOf5n-HER50vuP5HWZOsRYYB1jUj2MxNuUj4Os_snreqq=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This is a long overdue review. Back in the beginning of October, we wanted Italian food for dinner. We also wanted to go somewhere that we had never been to before. A search brought led me to Illuminaté Restorante. We are extremely glad it did! So, a reservation was made.

Upon entering, we immediately found Illuminaté Restorante to be a comfortable environment with a rustic Italian feel. Obviously, it is a popular place too. We can understand why.

Our meal started off with the Grilled Romaine and the Grilled Calamari to share. Both were outstanding! The Roasted Garlic dressing was wonderful on the perfectly grill romaine. The Calamari was a surprising delight. The hints of orange and pickled fennel took this squid to another level. In a world, awesome!

Our pasta mains were next level Italian cuisine. The Pappardelle al Ragu was by far on of the best pasta dishes I’ve ever had. The Braised Angus Short Ribs and Mushrooms were in a sauce that was out of this world. As for the Spaghetti and Meatballs, one would think “What a basic dish.” This was far beyond basic. Whatever is in their “Family Recipe” is extremely flavourful and delicious. Best meatballs ever.

Of course there was dessert. We shared the Citrus Crème Brule and the Mini Cannolis. The Lemongrass and Citrus was a great edition to this delicious custard. One cannot go to an Italian restaurant without having Cannolis. The Pistachio and Ricotta filling was superb. These mini cannolis rivals those of Mike’s Pastries of Boston.

And then there’s the service. Marie took extremely good care of us. She is very knowledgeable about the menu when we had questions. In chatting with Marie, she told us how much she loves her job and what she does. It shows. It’s always a pleasure to have service like Marie’s when dining out.

So, would I recommend Illuminaté Restorante? Absolute! This is a gem of a restaurant that you don’t have to travel downtown to. We can’t wait to dine there again.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOXDTu5sqwygeUAS-YGuWvWI20XRqTq1z238hnD&fid=0x0:0x15d7115c41800af7"],"When":"2024-11-22"},{"Name":"KAP Magnuson","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVuEWJRpclnUBzUp95TdnZT4hJ49cO3TDHBdnPq4gPy3qq4zyA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"It was our first time at this restaurant. When we noticed such a high Google score we decided to check it out and we were not disappointed.  The food was amazing - we had the onion soup to start, the spaghetti and meatballs and the halibut.  Best halibut I’ve probably ever eaten and the other dishes were amazing too.  We finished with the ganache and needed to be rolled out to the car.  Our server Rebecca was amazing (hi Rebecca!), super friendly and knowledgeable about the menu.  Thanks for a fabulous experience.  We will be back - highly recommended!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOaFafIa0C-nnTbbzsG3IIYHOIPTm8d7AMTJaZl&fid=0x0:0x15d7115c41800af7"],"When":"2024-9-23"},{"Name":"Donna Ye","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJV1vavqz3zyaXi6Dvbre135doVls1OY1S5ukulsw_Q4Xvwxg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Was going for some cannoli, but surprised by its appetizer and penne sausage! The marinara sauce is greatly balanced and tasty. The mini cannoli’s are absolutely amazing. Love the light creamy texture of its pistachio and ricotta filling! The atmosphere and decor was great too.We sat at the patio with cute turkey lamp.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOti4icsQsVH9RjOMhRLdPAhj9IZPYcrtbXIO4S&fid=0x0:0x15d7115c41800af7"],"When":"2024-9-9"},{"Name":"Gia Dhillon","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXt-wWmrFf5v4ElmZfQdGGB4prkhbT7axsOdXsHSggrDA2TsNU7YQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"A hidden gem! Wow we had the Gnocchi Gorgonzola and veal scaloppini. I have to say 10/10 it was delicious pure perfection. The feature dessert, chocolate espresso mousse with passion fruit glaze amazing! The service was great. The vibes of the restaurant are lovely. I’ll be back again.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMF4O0NMfWW4rdABxqEuYiYWesN88umxgWPHwkR&fid=0x0:0x15d7115c41800af7"],"When":"2024-9-21"},{"Name":"Greg Leo","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWm8ssH7mLognVswOCUTCA_m_WUoavv1VB46ZtNXUUngffyGHMZ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I stopped in to treat myself to a nice dinner after hitting Windskill.
Had a non alcohol Caesar which was outstanding.
Ended up having the Wagu Ribeye.. It was excellent !
Cooked perfect and so delicious. Accompaniments were tasty too..
For dessert I had the off menu Chocolate Creme Brule which was the perfect finish..
Have not been here for to long I guess but I don't eat out to much anymore as I also love to cook..
I've been disappointed in some of the other local restaurants over time but its refreshing to know I can count on this fine establishment when in need..
Its not cheap, but nothing good is, especially food wise.
I never mind paying for good food and service..
My server was Marie and she was absolutely delightful.. She has a smile that could light up any room..
My compliments to the chef/owner..you regained my faith in quality restaurant food again.
Thank you !
Greg Leo","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPTj-WmKSJzNDNALSoyDSd6C_mNM8Ie63Q2e6mP&fid=0x0:0x15d7115c41800af7"],"When":"2024-8-16"},{"Name":"John Su","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUc9FQ5QoVibyoNeurZTd7sS4c7gYNxIpenj-uGAqD2nzBUX8GW=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Old school traditional Italian.  Great quality that tasted like home cooking, so simple and  well done was the flavours.

This restaurant is better than most of the popular  Italian restaurants in Vancouver easily, Tswassen lucky to have such a local gem.

We had the lobster pasta special and baked Bocconcini wrapped in prosciutto.

Will definitely be back and tell ally Friends about you.

We had a bday there and the staff was attentive to those little things for service such as decorating the plates the birthday cale we brought to the restaurant and remembering the flowers. Felt like family, so nice touch on that.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN6mvfrEPvArZETUhl0WGFI7msHI-YC9BPN79Ew&fid=0x0:0x15d7115c41800af7"],"When":"2024-8-29"},{"Name":"Munro Stuff","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWj0Wcuk6ox5dfAeJ4fAaMbhX_F-nzzt3p5oc_f0hBd0NpbGSM=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Enjoyed our dinner here. Great service and daily specials. Meals were excellent.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOYoWUqi3fexYis0jeDoNjjoIaOwCcF3zx1lmGD&fid=0x0:0x15d7115c41800af7"],"When":"2024-11-17"},{"Name":"Renu Singh","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIZvuHBKRjp_jsMy08_ZVHVd4w9doVVOIC483AZihlQ8FS_-g=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We've heard good things about Illuminate and finally visited, and we weren't disappointed! Sarah was friendly, knowledgeable and attentive, she went above and beyond. We will be back.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMl-RRLHreWeGBN1XgFU8PkRwlWCW3caUDuDRE7&fid=0x0:0x15d7115c41800af7"],"When":"2024-2-1"}]

user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Lucy Yep.","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWyWEm1iVA5BhD52EO30x5805b5fs28qVCdlDvtJbrD1_d2ndv1=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Four Winds is a new dining spot in Tsawwassen that offers an a good selection of food and drinks. One of their standout options is the beer flight, which provides an opportunity to sample various unique flavors. While I found some of the dishes a bit on the oily side, the overall taste was good. The cod burger was difficult to eat as the fish was super soft.

If you’re looking to avoid long wait times, making a reservation is highly recommended. The booking process is straightforward, and it even allows for specific requests like special occasions. However, while they do ask if you're celebrating something special, the service doesn’t come with perks like complimentary desserts, which could feel like a missed opportunity for adding a more personalized touch.

The all humans bathroom is very uncomfortable experience.

The patio is a great dining option on sunny days, adding to the vibrant ambiance.

Inside the place is too loud and it is difficult to enjoy a conversation.

Additionally, the customer service is outstanding; the staff is attentive just no need to ask if everything was ok so many times. In general they are very friendly which enhances the dining experience and makes you feel welcome.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPpfUVGMRRIqTa7WNaHKRsavvADl_-5U78K69Ex&fid=0x0:0xafb9ff01afcb06e7"],"When":"2024-11-11"},{"Name":"Andrew Giassa","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKs2M8Lm_fO5YMx6QeBO4bPk3OR_tJ-4_oCO6-v2DtArGT_4g=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Went to Four Winds post Boundary Bay Marathon for some celebration drinks and food! I have been to the Annacis Island location in the past, which I really enjoyed, however first time at the Beach House! I love the open space, high ceilings, decor, and ambiance! Had a big selection of food at the table, which was shared! Everything was so delicious, my favourite being the chowder (special) and Brewmaster burger! The s'mores dessert was so tasty too! As always, excellent beer with my favourite being the dark lager! Our server Izzy was super friendly and efficient, and that goes for the other staff too! Very wonderful experience! I would recommend to friends/family and will be returning!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO8p0Zs4-6am4DCganVb2SW9dpfeso-G-Cmqmq5&fid=0x0:0xafb9ff01afcb06e7"],"When":"2024-11-4"},{"Name":"Erica Bearss","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUDaS88i8UI0EGR8dmybERXtdUX7zrkVtQV_GqB74oaYyXXVe_JrA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This was our first time at Four Winds Beach House and Brewery. The experience exceeded expectations. The atmosphere was perfect and the patio was an ideal complement to the gorgeous weather. Loved the open concept inside and out. Our server, Annalise, was phenomenal and made our experience one we will never forget. The butter on the pull apart bread set the stage for even better mains. Order the Smores Bar—it will blow your mind. We paired dessert with an espresso martini and a rum spiked root beer float for a flavour combination that was truly world class. We will be back as often as we can.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM7XFCpeGcMo0HrzdbLJLDO44OXSVCOF7Aifuw5&fid=0x0:0xafb9ff01afcb06e7"],"When":"2024-8-30"},{"Name":"Bobby Bedi","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVhxgbY0n0zWF3qsYcFT7w4K-aoSZ7dS8epGuHDyXmvvSfvyb9f5Q=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"⭐⭐⭐⭐⭐
Four Winds Beach House and Brewery is a gem in Tsawwassen! They offer some of the finest beers in Western Canada, and the food is equally impressive—truly top-notch quality. The ambiance is sophisticated yet welcoming, and the outdoor patio is perfect on sunny days, making it a fantastic spot to relax and enjoy. Prices are great for the high-end experience they provide. You really have to come and see it to believe it—hands down the best brewery in Western Canada!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMwUaRnKAGM9QK_5XLAJ-fGDM1NkgchA7pWW7p6&fid=0x0:0xafb9ff01afcb06e7"],"When":"2024-10-3"},{"Name":"Linda Hansbauer","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVbhYntSwrf3fPiWmrNihB_RxxZEX6epZ6NkhTpeBuOWgHv5aaF=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"I  am a visitor from Australia 🇦🇺 🪃  and we decided to check out the recently opened establishment. Ambience nice - decor very pleasing to the eye. We only had drinks, and the kids had some truffle chips.  Water or sparkling water was offered - nice touch.  The beer we decided to have very tasty -  the consistency of pouring a beer - was not 300 ml as stated on the menu - every glass was different levels - judge for yourself.
I am sure after a couple of weeks all the new  staff will have all the training necessary,  to work in such a
nice and new upcoming restaurant. After writing this - I checked other reviews - customers made the same comments about the beer pouring. Overall, the place looks inviting - it is going to be very cosy, with the beautiful  fireplace - when the weather gets cold - so all the best to the staff and management.
My family will be back - the kids loved the sheets of drawing options, and it kept them entertained. Thank you!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNksgD8VwxT63_D7k_XOsuyx1M3e0q1z7p8A9kf&fid=0x0:0xafb9ff01afcb06e7"],"When":"2024-8-23"},{"Name":"Em","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXwT6tEzL3WJcfKi-6wpRMOJI1G-6s5wZxB5kN0OUIQi9PuSdOk=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"First time being here and it was excellent. The vibe was great, the service was immaculate and the food was delicious. We got some drinks, sourdough bread and oysters to start. Had the beach house burger and the brewmaster for dinner and tried the lavender cheesecake for dessert. All of it was  10/10. Had the pleasure of interacting with a Robert, Jesse, Etem and Barry. Excellent customer service will be back for sure. Definitely check this place out!  No TV’s, perfect for date night or a night out with friends. Four winds gives you more of an intimate vibe. Loved it! Oh and try the lemon aioli with your fries.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPBudFkkb_9hwfkCOrxdzZ13m2_elE8gA8LmMkI&fid=0x0:0xafb9ff01afcb06e7"],"When":"2024-12-4"},{"Name":"Ofri Livneh","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX16STGcz1WkHjUy4qq_7S8xXO7R5LIxtHEuX0qTlmdW8ybL5ZH=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This place is outstanding! Food, atmosphere, service and everything in between.
What a great combination of flavours that explodes in the mouth.🎉
Service is fantastic and the chef should definitely be rewarded for his creativity and work of art!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipODEYHDHLukdB22ja-dOmF6mSvd2qNrK6JEyFDF&fid=0x0:0xafb9ff01afcb06e7"],"When":"2024-11-20"},{"Name":"Jeff and Cat Chang","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUuaO4qWxQoHYN_xctVA-vkdLQu4qoKrOrAaxWLOEhghP9fOzs=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Checked this place out all the way from Vancouver and it was defintiely worth the trip out! For a brewery, we were surprised by how good the cocktails were. We had their version of a Paper Plane and a Negroni, both with a fun beer element to them.

The food is the real standout though. I didn't get a chance to take a photo of the bread roll and fancy butter, but it was literally to die for. I would have ordered just the bread.

We had the chicken piccata which was like a schnitzel but chicken, it was flavourful and crispy. The sald of golden beets and stone fruit was really nice as well, peach with basil? What a combo. If it's cold outside we'd recommend asking for a spot in the main dining room area. It's so cool and has an amazing fireplace.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN8RbS-FPABUCkTrEne9_OeoVJD5V8oXHqjWjDv&fid=0x0:0xafb9ff01afcb06e7"],"When":"2024-9-17"}]
