[{"Name":"Max Voigt","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVJ7EG7NzgbGGtweKH_4cMuIzP7KBBqWZv2RDcRky6qogzA1mlT=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Friendly staff and prompt fast service. About 5mins after ordering food was at our table. Wonton soup, fried rice, chicken wings, fried noodle and green beans all dishes came out hot and tasty. Not Americanized Chinese food - which I would see as a good thing. Would come here again when our family does a trip to the area.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Ray","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXGVd5s-06Fr3JDo-bYWWNiziS7uiGN7g2hEorOk1Vp-qtDK_-cTg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I really love their almond chicken, BBQ pork fried rice, and sweet and sour chicken balls. The breading is crisp, crunchy, flavorful and the meat is very tender, almost creamy. Serving sizes will leave you satisfied and not too full. Prices reasonable. I recommend for an after work dine-in!!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPHL0WOLHPvm8RLyH7HWc_IXC_3QA5DsEWaYSpn&fid=0x0:0xf1c9434b79ebe56e"],"When":"2023-1-12"},{"Name":"Geoff","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIB7GO5SNpE1WIKMrtKsZatBr4-vjVP1je4zsiQTxeZeBqfyw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Ive lived all over the lower mainland for over 50 years… and have had Chinese food from countless different establishments, but this was some of the worst Chinese food I've ever eaten. Poor quality ingredients and poor quality of taste. I really cannot think of another place that is this terrible","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Trevor W","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXyJ9v0nAxuFJWevbjIWIjM7AxUnw8p2XTyXFzmeKsiKCAZF4Nf=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Their BBQ pork fried rice is pretty good.  Sweet and sour pork, ya I will order it again.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Jen Olson Kurcz","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUJS-DSvDCCvB6r4JUDjb-1adsIMbJM3WQfNMZO6jkXwHbXDk4G6g=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"When I ordered, I was told 25 minutes. I showed up 30 minutes later to get my food. An hour later, and I was still waiting there....bad service on a $100 order.

While I was waiting, a couple came in, ordered, had their soup, and were halfway through their entree. This was arpund 40-45 minutes after I placed my phone order.

After 70 minutes, I went up to the counter again (3rd time checking in with her), and she retrieved my food from the kitchen...and confirmed it had been there for a bit. A meek apology was offered, but that's all.

I brought my slightly cooled off food home. The fried rice, chicken chow mein, and green beans with beef were good. The szechuan beef and chicken snd broccoli were bland. They tasted like the already cooked veg and meat had been tossed with the sauce---not cooked with it. And our fortune cookies were stale. Bland as it was, we needed to eat.

It's not an experience we'd like to repeat.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPOs6IyUTfvHJeiY3XL9NZ-ZK-_IjGqPta4Qque&fid=0x0:0xf1c9434b79ebe56e"],"When":"2023-6-23"},{"Name":"Isela Galaviz","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWp18vcoTvzvwDZAKZBhhxTSioNcKGzYMPItoc1q0S0-JFK7BHzlw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I was so pleased to hear a lady coming into the place screaming “finally my favourite place!” And immediately having a good feeling about it that was successfully confirmed after trying one of their most popular dishes and the great refreshing ginger beer. If I would live there it will also be my favourite place!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMjNg4AIs9VnvNgs_LRQB2cdWR9bVihNumcIGeC&fid=0x0:0xf1c9434b79ebe56e"],"When":"2022-8-30"},{"Name":"Parker Walsh","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocL51PSJQ0Ml87PlG5wU8AIkpKT9SdtcC6a0MWDC06P-NTkzrw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Great classic Canadian Chinese food. Quick to answer the phone, upfront about time of delivery. Fair prices. Good portions. Tasty food.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"R B","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocL1uEfq0J-PcMkK-u2eTdRLVRlSVJ4sGA_fCeEivn83k6iKSQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"The chicken in the cashew gai ding was unpalatable and we could not eat it. It was some kind of unidentifiable white mushy protein. It does not resemble, taste or feel like chicken. Maybe some way to get around higher chicken prices but this stuff was Absolutely disgusting. The vegetable dishes were delicious and well cooked but I would stay away from any kind of so called “chicken” on their menu","Images":null,"When":""}]

[{"Name":"Anastasiia Dmytriieva","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIkL6ohvQWL55q6h1FcPWENyGIClfcqwW1NZNt7UXMKI3mbxt8=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"In my opinion the  A&W it is the greatest fast food in Tsawwassen to compare with others. The stuff on front desk so friendly and positioned every time smiling and double checking the order to be sure everything is correct. My order was processed and prepared fast enough. The newest sandwich in the menu still favorite for me.
Thank you for your job 👍","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"C E","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocL9Sw12YtCq4W1VpSxyr7zX2I2LRxLhd47w143d-5D5HQq8yg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"After biking with friends for about two hours and covering 40 kilometers, we decided it was time for breakfast. We were delighted to find that A&W was open bright and early, and their breakfast options were delicious. The fact that they offered refillable coffee was an added bonus, giving us the energy boost we needed for the next leg of our bike ride. What's more, there is even a secure spot to park our bikes.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPuQGrNZq_AhZKMvxa5KihIMdtmePTjsNEXbU-Z&fid=0x0:0xaa82dbb2780db514"],"When":"2023-9-16"},{"Name":"B S","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocInhm-tKxAFagciityZcf5N_sFnfpkrdExop1cjkXnoljnHVuI=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"It’s soooooo slow I wanna rip my eyes out this service is so slow. Get more staff they forgot half my order. I give up on life. I’m pulling my hair out trying not to scream . So rude no hello no sorry . Just waiting in line still writing this review 😤😤😤😤","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Katie Fraser","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVU6rpqC0ctOYr1zBxtqTS70MCuIGg8lzkGnuf0TAfH1AjJ6HuX=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"Food messy, burgers are made very messy, if you only like their root beer thats probably the best thing about the restaurant. Love them, but not later hours. So very displeased with the service. Look at our onion rings, will check before we get home.”","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO0LYl81qfBaek4vVNOabMRDUQbc0YQ3g9FsEH_&fid=0x0:0xaa82dbb2780db514"],"When":"2018-10-6"},{"Name":"Kevin Percival","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIEsNXB4qySf4jQw8b2tRTH-4Or_Dtf2kzbj5Ez5_i60Lf7=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The best 24-hour fast food in Tsawwassen. When I entered the store, the worker, Manpreet, was acting frazzled on the phone. When she finally looked up she asked how she can assist me, I shared I’m here to pick up an online order, Manpreet then said “okay, it’ll be a moment” and then she continued to loiter behind the counter and pacing back and forth on the phone. Then after she finally got off the phone she started to make, what I assumed, was my order which was 7 minutes after I Manpreet mentioned it would ‘just be a moment’. This was unacceptable as we had 2 young kids waiting in the car and hence why I believe placing an online order would have been a better idea. Manpreet also did not apologize for the late order or the inconvenience this has caused me. This was the first time I’d ever seen one individual working at subway, during dinner time, on a weekday night. This entire encounter was unprofessional by subway standards. user_reviews:
[{"Name":"larissa sandoval","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXHMsnNOyQ-dDeoTnqKIXCM1pOeSc3Hn8eBLvjCMupM9LsN7CuRvA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The customer service was exceptional from the moment I walked into the restaurant. The atmosphere was warm and inviting, and everything was spotless. My food arrived almost immediately and was bursting with flavor—one of the best pho soups I’ve ever had. Plus, it was very affordable. I highly recommend it! Don’t forget to take a Vietnamese coffee to go. You won’t regret it.!

I visited Canada from South Texas for work and discovered this restaurant on my first night. I loved it so much that I returned every day for the next six days, trying a different dish each time!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPyj7lFmxISltInSiPPdk6ulOcLIaa3OeJdTLIW&fid=0x0:0x6e9eb54daa4159d7"],"When":"2024-11-18"},{"Name":"sandra lee","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJKnH1o2AEeZGgKmELOGnQMyc7MzehItqcwPsLlvsBp4hAp1Q=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"A hidden gem. This is the BEST Vietnamese restaurant in town.  The food is authentic, delicious -  fresh ingredients 👌🏻 You can really tell the chefs and staff care a lot about the food. The team is also super friendly and attentive.

Highly recommend—10/10. Also got extra springs rolls and another BBH to take home 👸🏻","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOyohww9C_HzcvtrCJnq5cX-hTdcFvzskI7IQC0&fid=0x0:0x6e9eb54daa4159d7"],"When":"2024-11-11"},{"Name":"Kimiya Missaghi","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJb2lDM_w29lxt8nTu2BYewMDuVlnwacYth1DYiBlerwGgsuQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Our new favorite Vietnamese spot! Perfect for a meal before or after the ferry. Great ambiance and amazing food. The owner is super sweet and hospitable. The Vietnamese coffee with fresh coconut juice wow 🤩","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOSheKC1VLjZs1Qyv9rLJ2vyttGf_YBLIfeDJdq&fid=0x0:0x6e9eb54daa4159d7"],"When":"2024-12-24"},{"Name":"Steve Leong","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWzFeTX1xzGFbNlSVZoreAyWYbXUkrUozWhYo5D0t4fKe1zvzvnEA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Pho Fresh is an excellent Vietnamese restaurant in the neighborhood, offering a spacious and welcoming environment. The hospitality is top-notch, with friendly staff making the dining experience pleasant. The lemongrass grilled noodles combo and the special house combo are delicious and served in generous portions. The pricing is reasonable, making it a great value for the quality and quantity of food. The vibrant ambiance and comfortable seating add to the overall enjoyment, making Pho Fresh one of the best dining spots in the area. Highly recommended for anyone looking to enjoy authentic Vietnamese cuisine.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOtsySdIr0-Xq25O7mhRcvU_aYfpyy_gLuMYTW2&fid=0x0:0x6e9eb54daa4159d7"],"When":"2024-7-1"},{"Name":"y sa","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXFngQqa2F90OIpbxkUL3vQVcASx5xoE2gyFjE4kMR1ydjk_2M=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"You can enjoy some delicious pho there! The homemade broth was especially amazing! Steamed prawn salad rolls and the dipping sauce were also good, making for an enjoyable experience. The staff were incredibly thoughtful and kind. I definitely want to visit there again with my family. I highly recommend everyone to visit!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM0pwqrrOi8ANgHSc3w8bRlzXj4Xx6cX2HP47Au&fid=0x0:0x6e9eb54daa4159d7"],"When":"2024-9-26"},{"Name":"Robin Clements","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV9PmsLxITJmMMeaAz28FAyYktWqAc6468HB42trXKaraHdb6JS=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We came here on a whim as we were early for our ferry reservation, and it was the best choice we could’ve made. The restaurant has a warm atmosphere, and we were greeted as soon as we entered.

The food was fantastic, and satisfied our cravings for pho. All the ingredients were fresh and the depth of flavour was perfect, and every time I thought I was running out of meat in the bowl, there was even more than I originally expected!

The owner of the restaurant talked with my boyfriend and I while we waited for our food, and served us directly. Although we only interacted for the hour we were there, we saw how much of a kind and thoughtful person he was through his interactions with other customers and his regulars.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNTdvLq6VmgOJLqtEsJCSacgnYxO3oIDJR7-nCw&fid=0x0:0x6e9eb54daa4159d7"],"When":"2024-9-28"},{"Name":"Jungyun Lee","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXGp0on-U3-UWh9MA5CmYGPw4gLbO_Ew26nJYGOjF6hdC1QFQKG=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The broth was very rich and clean. The service was also amazing. Additionally, the interior was very cozy and welcoming. I would definitely come again!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOYsf6mb7S2SseGuN0lcFJCzdJbZgx4g-m56TuS&fid=0x0:0x6e9eb54daa4159d7"],"When":"2024-10-14"},{"Name":"Tickets Canada","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocL0SLPz52bqTWVqYYEKCPdR-8-5YcNqhnfjmebE3sqxMOr0bQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I’ve been here several times now so I can say that the level of service and food are always fantastic. From the moment you walk in the door, the owners greet you very warmly with a nice smile. They make you feel immediately welcome wanted and appreciated which is something most restaurants seem to fail to do. The food tastes so fresh, so healthy, so tasty. It’s also quite speedy as well! I make it a point to stop here every time I am in town. It’s just one of those feel good moments.","Images":null,"When":""}]

[{"Name":"Emilia Tam","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVgfp9u2yzyy8HUI4c13oDqO8lmhh6nx7dy4FtdX8yKSFhFbDi4rQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Food tasted great but small portion. My husband ordered the baked tortellini with Alfredo sauce. The tortellini and sauce tasted like store bought and it was very heavy on cheese. Server constantly seemed like she was on a rush. We came here last summer and my hubby ordered a pizza which he did not like and tryst me, my husband does not have great expectations when it come to food.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNCApugE64erVfcceRBb9o1_hlZgipdPr-i0nG3&fid=0x0:0x5eeafa1a7ed01608"],"When":"2024-1-2"},{"Name":"Little Journey","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUlNkzOJynLpgqJCrPnrmAAn5viwim-B3Uir-26DOWxIzwcnZ0=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"First time ever to try Greek cuisine in town. The salad was refreshing and the lamp chop was delicious. Personally, I prefer the crust of the pizza could be thinner and crispier. Still it's an enjoyable meal with a big group of friends.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO98ROqMviTMOb0gsovRNy0WGAGpwIZOGmkjZZN&fid=0x0:0x5eeafa1a7ed01608"],"When":"2023-12-17"},{"Name":"Leon Hui","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJc9IH1eTfQrZfSlHMwJl3JETAFfMkBbsqVQd9USsEfKwJ3Cw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Friendly waitress and always smiling. Big portion of food makes it worth your buck. Everyone there seems need to pack their food home. The serve is awesome! Our server observed and not interrupted the meal still having. Loved that! I felt relax and had a nice chat there with dim down atmosphere. Starred this location for my choice of Greek food. Even though it is distance away, it is definitely a place to go if you are around there.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNWGWDIVnLxf5j3r6e4GA-Fd9dSUkQHJwF_7Jql&fid=0x0:0x5eeafa1a7ed01608"],"When":"2023-9-5"},{"Name":"Indy Virk","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLoeoRUuBv6iGVh8ojWW2AawuN-5SRQ7HjGXshYVFDCEo8xWQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Absolutely delicious authentic Greek food! It was our first time there, the chicken souvlaki was a 10/10. I highly recommend going and I can't wait to go back to try the other dishes. Extra shout out to our server and cook! Overall we were very impressed.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Elmira Nazari","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUS8psOPde-fgvVYsglTVKj-j9hpNdB1347mGr_T9d11yAStREO4w=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Was craving greek and this place was close by. The service was great and the atmosphere was quiet and relaxing. We got a few things:
Calamari - super fresh with tzaziki dip.
Greek Salad - nice portions, and a generous amount of quality olives for the olive lovers out there.
Roast lamb - slow cooked, the meat deliciously fells apart. Comes with greek salad, potato and rice.
Chicken Souvlaki - Chicken was a little dry, the rest of the dish was good.
Share platter - had a good variety of everything and would feed 4-5 people.
Cesar drink - really well made compared to alot of other places.
Favourite dish - roast lamb","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO23Gpd72Qhc1xl9qobY3Iq2cKQnpaYE3bGVp-t&fid=0x0:0x5eeafa1a7ed01608"],"When":"2023-9-17"},{"Name":"Heike Reinhardt","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUQu13xA_sdCrrCEzybl4Mb_Gnyu8_KDY2hb0kmgRKtEpDaH70=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Super sweet service, calamari with greek withe wine is great.
I had so much leftovers, which I brought home for the next day for lunch ;) I will ge again ✨️💓","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNOSOFcS3oqj--oATIR1cqesDAt8DXwlKgLR9Ce&fid=0x0:0x5eeafa1a7ed01608"],"When":"2024-10-8"},{"Name":"Jeff Boulton","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWwWomyzjheqZXm1ssNiqtjC1h17ofWn10zQqMCbIBk5xqgw48e=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Had lunch outside on deck, great service and food.  The moussaka was fantastic!!  Lots of food and great flavour.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMpQsNzv6hZ2-3eM5BpM7ufTGqzTz73MJMJmbKx&fid=0x0:0x5eeafa1a7ed01608"],"When":"2024-7-16"},{"Name":"Ronald B","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX_Mt0SdyzppT58qLdbbzj1sY4Nva9W-LpB9qFPiHaoQT6MHG0H=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"This place transported us back to Greece! We only ordered the Chicken Souvlaki, but it was still really good! The skewer ends were a bit dry but the rest was juicy chicken! I ordered a 6 oz glass of Tsantali Retsina. I would only recommend this wine if you’re feeling adventurous and have a palate for a dry, fresh pine and a saline finish. If you can get past the piney notes you get on the nose citrus, pear and apple notes.

Definitely one of the best Greek restaurants in the lower mainland we’ve tried so far!

Price: It’s priced the same as most other restaurants of this caliber. But you get what you pay for! Great Food!

Portion/palate: Portion is decent for the price you pay and the taste is so good! Minus the dry ends on the skewers. The wine was a delight because it is nothing you have ever tried! (I bet)

Place: Location is nice because it is on main street and parking is decent if you come when they open. We dined on the patio so I didn’t see much of the inside. A bit of a drive to get to, but if you’re in the area for the beach or an event definitely come here!

People: People were great! Good service!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOuv1BkZAiE_m0srnHDc5TL6GX05c6M9Tmv7x_X&fid=0x0:0x5eeafa1a7ed01608"],"When":"2023-7-5"}]

[{"Name":"Amy Wu","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKvtm7hBqZHDYxXgP_oxkelx2FGhwfW-EuwTv9rdyjxo-_-_8Nq=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"I’m not that picky with poke but this one was not good. I got the Peruvian Spicy Citrus. The sauce was too salty, there was too much of it and very little fish. It was a lot spicier than expected. Portion was also quite small.

Overall, very disappointed and would not come again.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOanZBdpFdTtvdYhc3NVIt66FZwcLNJ_s4kpf2B&fid=0x0:0xb32e11462bfcdb7"],"When":"2024-7-31"},{"Name":"Rubel Ahmed","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWcFyV0UnGjUg5eJnWh4zaitP2fi78AYcoftqix22diqKzGMwE1qA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"Here’s a refined version of your message:

I'm a regular customer at Hula, both downtown and Tsawwassen locations, and I’ve noticed a big difference in portion sizes between the two—it’s like night and day. Today, I ordered the Tikki and paid for extra salmon, but I was stunned at how few pieces of salmon I received. It was very disappointing. Not worth of $21","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO2aMon0SzhLu9AVzjvyfk7yfhzQEkiVxcvWGqp&fid=0x0:0xb32e11462bfcdb7"],"When":"2024-9-14"},{"Name":"Jeroen Stout","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX6mbN0-4i-7Hiy53rXUS_QQOBj0N4Lv-VJYrc-yp2ho_33mNi5=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"First time ordering a bowl here. Very satisfied with my order: double salmon, coconut rice, ancho smoky/sweet. Service was decent and fast. Atmosphere of the food counter is good, sitting places in a mall not so nice, but these are not Hula’s.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMUoXFhWqYAOjzjqv5TrAsTvvAmMsuzVz_BL4Ab&fid=0x0:0xb32e11462bfcdb7"],"When":"2024-6-11"},{"Name":"Sandra Chan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUS3d7aZA4lMhkB4lrjOTrDjB_p6PvngmeWQeM0VFHPfzqli2Uc=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"We were surprised at how few pieces of protein (raw salmon for both orders) was in our bowls and how small the overall amount was. The taste was good, though.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMJZPzfWmb0ZbpsorQuswzwa7i1uf4wfFzK7Edk&fid=0x0:0xb32e11462bfcdb7"],"When":"2022-5-4"},{"Name":"Ray","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXGVd5s-06Fr3JDo-bYWWNiziS7uiGN7g2hEorOk1Vp-qtDK_-cTg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I highly recommend the Ancho bowl with ahi tuna and coconut rice. The savory sauce combined with the soft hot rice, veg and tuna is perfect to my tastes. I am not the biggest veggie meal lover but there was just the right amount of greens for extra flavor and texture.
Yuzu bowl is good too.
Expensive for the portion, but you get quality seafood, fresh veg and a uniquely delicious meal. Overall one of my fave things to eat, would eat more if I could afford it.
Service is polite and fast even in busy times.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPosMNrOc9UT0GjaiceHk7X5OJgcfQBMHvJcYYT&fid=0x0:0xb32e11462bfcdb7"],"When":"2023-7-20"},{"Name":"Shanice KO","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUbAiJ8WffchhFHCc7nWHUGhokAijkg1PLmCSqnL8cAc66U9E5F=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"My husband ran in to grab us two Yuzu poke bowls with tuna before we boarded the ferry. The bowls weren't even close to filled and there was the most pitiful amount of protein I've ever seen. I've been to hula a few times before at the Guildford mall location and never had this happen. I'm guessing it's a training issue or active shrink-flation. The only redeeming quality is that it tastes good but for $34 we won't be going back. Steve's Poke Bar is way better and they don't skimp on the amount of fish or toppings.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Jo Zamora","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVRiQ0k2aipqLBzmIfT4DfVFgMtoFZ8OzkduSv0IOT7ZMof6If0=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Stood here for 5 min no one seem to work here and when the person in charge came back she did not even recognize that there is a person waiting to order. user_reviews:
[{"Name":"raechelle bishop","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWp3lLax-Ic4Pxkoex821fO7o43NmBPDrnvvciGvnHqgK_ujxsD=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"My husband and I love this location. Their food is always amazing. They staff is polite and the service is quick. We always bring people out for dinner here when they visit. Most of the time we order takeout.

My only complaints are on the takeout.

The portions are a lot smaller than if you eat in, tho the cost is the same.

The lids for the dips always melt and shrivel up causing whatever is in the container to spill all over the food.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMsLZaKZhiacIRtWd1wYnhHFdI63AYUgqIv7VyN&fid=0x0:0x62dbece1fff9c912"],"When":"2024-12-15"},{"Name":"Tony Li","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWPKcy0N8L_e03kCanD-kbqBYJvghgec1_Wu16Qs-S8YjI-PLg2nw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"When you crave for chicken wings, Wings is the place to go. They have every flavor you want. My favorite is the dill pickle, but ask for more seasoning on the side if you want the saliva to flow. The classic Buffalo sauce is great too. And if you want sweetness, both the Fuji and Jakarta heat are delicious. After 3 years, I finally tried the Bobby Wing that practically burned a hole in my tongue. After getting over the heat, it was actually good. Complement it with calamari and have the dip nearby. You'll want to douse your tongue in the dip, and not the beer. By the way, the tacos are really good. Get a mixture of meat if you can.

Update: Been there for lunch several times and noticed how quiet the place was. Unfortunately the place smelled more like a pub than a wings restaurant. I also think more emphasis can be done on trying to promote wing nights rather than trivia, hockey meals, etc. - all things that remind me of pubs than restaurants. The updated lunch menu is great and happy hour bites - all tasty and good value. Only the decor and smell of the place can be adjusted.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOOYXHEtrPcSZdiN36U7wq2aqy5bqhQXZwvgIbH&fid=0x0:0x62dbece1fff9c912"],"When":"2023-8-1"},{"Name":"Daniel Li","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUAxFTfz_ZYgM60gsStYArKOb4YgmHuHArMEsVm-TJD2WcKuo33=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"The service at this is average, there isn't anything particularly noteworthy to mention. We placed an order consisting of 2 kids' meals, Chicken Alfredo, Meatballs Marinara, Wings, and soda.

We ordered chicken strips for the first kids’ meal and pasta for the second set, which were satisfactory. The chicken strips were tender, and the pasta was decently prepared.  (Kids’ meal come with drinks and dessert)

My wife had the Chicken Alfredo, and she mentioned that it was good. My daughter particularly enjoyed the garlic bread that accompanied the dish.

However, I was quite disappointed with the Meatballs Marinara. I'm a huge fan of meatballs and often order them when available on a menu. Unfortunately, the meatballs at this place were lacking of the smoky flavor I was expecting. They were among the worst meatballs I've had in years.

The wings also left us disappointed. We opted for a half-and-half combination of lemon pepper and honey garlic flavors. The lemon pepper wings turned out to be dry, and the taste of the honey garlic wings was unclear.

As for the soda, we ordered Coke and Sprite. My son mentioned that his Sprite tasted like water, l  believe that the soda lacked sufficient carbon dioxide.

Overall, the experience had its ups and downs, with some dishes meeting our expectations while others fell short.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOC4bKrUklfBCqJ9xhJf3bKbqquKqCLN-eaPQmg&fid=0x0:0x62dbece1fff9c912"],"When":"2023-7-1"},{"Name":"Shawn Corkum","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXxtAysqj7F2p6bXglsUmRm5orOep5UPFSzANo7LTK_LKMLPrMwoA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Stopped at Wings for lunch, it was my second time here.  I really enjoyed the Beef Dip I had last time around, so wanted to give the namesake dish a try.  The wings are very good, if a bit pricey.   I had the Peri Peri with the house ranch, and it was tasty, with just the right amount of heat.  The wings are coated nicely, and are meaty.   My wife had the quesadilla, which was pretty bland.  They need a better lunch menu, imo.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNP6D9hBO-t9lFU5Lcehthb09hOXtmD_CLjaHi9&fid=0x0:0x62dbece1fff9c912"],"When":"2024-3-17"},{"Name":"Krazy Mitch","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUI7e00_EMxMC5lRcA9LNPHxr6Mbxl-ctUbXYQxIXvNjX2guHtK=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Well that was a dismal experience.
Never been to wings before,  won't go back.  $50 for a starter salad, a 14oz beer, and wings and fries combo.  The cheese bread was missing flavor,  the sweet potato fries need longer in the deep fryer, the wings we meh. I asked the waitress for a "fruit" beer, she said "we don't have "fruit" beer, I asked what the stanley park rotating was a Peach Lager, last time I checked peach was still a fruit..

I won't be back.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Elmira Nazari","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUS8psOPde-fgvVYsglTVKj-j9hpNdB1347mGr_T9d11yAStREO4w=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Delicious food. The Southern bowl, spinach dip and wings were all delicious. Went for the UFC fights and our waitress was really awesome and made sure she checked on us often. Recommended for sports events and casual outings!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOyO7GQChxe8Q0fF0fqHcHx_Tu70fmNAAIMliAY&fid=0x0:0x62dbece1fff9c912"],"When":"2023-4-10"},{"Name":"jason wong","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLAr7OPM3u3i7bBkh0r7Q9kS7_8Gu_88Crv223BgydShD66TQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Service was excellent, Hamburger was dry and need more mayo.. Wings are better than most place in Vancouver..","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPLOwBvpfETiHPlsVYopSh1Zsyaf_2LNe48lRa6&fid=0x0:0x62dbece1fff9c912"],"When":"2024-6-10"},{"Name":"Janet","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUJLdrp4_-PzGWs8I7cbVIruptxWktGjE-_19gAKtYsnjV7T8DB=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Came at Happy hour so it was pretty loud and busy, but the staff saw and greeted us right away. Given the crowd at that time it was understandable there was some wait but our server made a point of checking in on us so we didn’t have to wave multiple times. Food was decent, wings were a bit small but tasty enough.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMmugq2dGK8I5BuROfk_kvAIBjAJ5TiwtvQgtTx&fid=0x0:0x62dbece1fff9c912"],"When":"2023-2-20"}]

It was such a wonderful experience!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Inderjit Kaur Johal","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJS3BRB_NIdOpD-bBNwkOmi3-ZXk2Dxc5dOozpsVaPrN6KJOQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"White Spot Tsawwassen is a must-visit restaurant if you're in the area. The atmosphere is vibrant and colourful, setting the perfect mood for any occasion. The menu offers a fantastic variety of food and drinks,
**Delicious Food and Exceptional Service, The food was great, with excellent vegetarian choices. Definitely will come back.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"chsnwun","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW4P9KCaYveOCkTXiolanHwrE7k7jyl5DMR1IQhcDM5jPKzpelh5Q=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"GREAT experience  met Jas and not only did she make my Dining experience awesome she  took my order and cooked it

I got the Bacon Cheddar Bigger Burger with fries while my wife got the Mediterranean Chicken Burger. The kids shared a Chicken Fingers Pirate Pak.

I loved my burger. It was tasty and delicious. My wife enjoyed her chicken, which was not dry. The fries are good as we come to expect from White Spot.

The kids love the Pirate Pak, but what kid wouldn't!

It was a good meal and we had a great time.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOJCDFGe0xlnwuW3PU_SSvmyog5uC_degFwgEMJ&fid=0x0:0x17943d6bd3047396"],"When":"2023-5-23"},{"Name":"Mathew Lao","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVtO7Xiefy5DCdGGQ4Bz-1QO-aissnnVRn_Ycl2AHI76SyQyWE=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Just as I remember it years ago.

Atmosphere: 3/5 - clean","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP-owsUSuhBLQL70y_NZLWvDhF0fMVg2GKtzPoZ&fid=0x0:0xc6c6e136ffbdb874"],"When":"2024-8-19"},{"Name":"Devon Phelan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXorWAedHbb59VsAXuR_js0R_xERF5lT44CmILYrHhE3b98PaXr=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Ocean Palace has been my go-to place to eat Chinese food for years. Having local business owners run the place has ensured that they maintained the trust they have with customers. If you are conscious about MSG, just know that you can ask for no MSG with your whole order!

Be sure to order when they open (~5pm) so that you don't have to worry about a potential 1-2hr wait time for take-out or delivery late at night! The long wait goes to show that the food here is made authentically and tastes great!

It's also great to know that they make their spring-rolls in house!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"steve “Steve here” garnier","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU8syJgHRb0oL04Zsxzk5A8o3zGjkPiKanrBaAkjiMlFwFoULbA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Missing items from my order and It took over an hour and a half for me to get my order. I did order through skip but the order was received by the restaurant in about 2 minutes and the driver was there before the food was done AND it only took him 6 minutes to get to my house.

All I ordered was 2 combo meals and 2 pops. They didn't give me any drinks or cutlery or napkins.
And when I called the guy had the nerve to ask me to drive there to pick up my drinks they forgot AND tried to blame the wait time on skip the dishes.
Wasn't until I told him I was going to leave a poor review that he offered to refund me for the 2 pops that I never even received........uhm yea I'm deffinately not paying for the items I never got buddy. Thanks alot. Meal should have been free.

I also thought the meat portions were quite small.

***I'm not sure how to respond to your response so I'm doing it here.

Again your trying to blame the skip driver. You only offered to have the drinks delivered after I said no to picking them up myself and only offered the refund on the drinks after I said I was going to leave a bad review.

My opinion on the matter remains the same that was poor customer service and not taking responsibility. If you apologized right away and offered the refund even for just the drinks I wouldn't have givin this review.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"mike hagan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKvUqJb3JaTqllEtEnlhNA7LGjD22b8O1McJFccS2HHP1Cc=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Went Aug 03/24 to dine in with another couple after it had only been open for take out for years due to Covid & staff shortages. It’s the perfect spot to grab a meal after visiting Tsawwassen Mills.
If you’re visiting Vancouver, Canada, this sushi place is a must-try.

My family and I are always welcome with a smile and greeting! :) 100% recommend trying if you’re in Tsawwassen!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOE2PEnVFlbxCWTevdsmhvvlR7l1WYxqjs7e7aX&fid=0x0:0xd68d74066199f0be"],"When":"2024-11-19"},{"Name":"Tony Li","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXf8VP49ZjSvgG0JnhT1tc6Tv6OzLL9YEi_yNvwH1rW_K8-7VE=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Looking for a Japanese restaurant with a Korean twist? Kamome is it. There is KFC, Korean Fried Chicken and Kim Chi fried rice on the menu. You'll also the the bibimap, rice bowl contents cooked in a clay pot. Recommend the lobster roll or the bento boxes for lunch. And give the dinner for 4 a try. Delicious food. Only thing they can improve on, is the substitutions. Need to be flexible and better priced. People have allergies and may want to swap ebi shrimp for salmon but not for $3 more on a nigiri.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP_xYNJHOh9w6gm5mymZDNUEFrvbq9KznjyP4ba&fid=0x0:0xd68d74066199f0be"],"When":"2024-8-20"},{"Name":"John Stick","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLwA-jpzGraYUo7jr1qY95bukP2m4mzjWDFk6-stxq5hpHJcA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"We went to Tswassen Mills to see Santa at Cabellas...which BTW, is a hidden secret, great set up and free photo....

Afterwards we went to Kamome which is about a 2 min drive in the next complex over.

Lots of parking and a big place. The three of us, 3 adults and our 6 yo easily got a table. Service was attentive and good. The server felt we ordered too much food, but he never met my 6 yo either.

The best dishes were the sushi tower and the yam tempura. All the other rolls and items were good, nothing I'm going to rave about, but filled us up.

The food came fast and was fresh.

If you are in Tswassen and craving Japanese food, this place will give you what you want and a decent price point.

$$","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPS42_c2cGl4al3EqHlN4ca6nqhNNC2ncj_sEs6&fid=0x0:0xd68d74066199f0be"],"When":"2023-12-12"},{"Name":"Paula Kor","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVCCckh4f87jBroNxUDIpqu4Q7EezAD-0DmaNXgqRVCjwxqjfsh=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Found this hidden gem by chance while driving around Tsawwassen Mills. user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Thedishdetective Lala","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKD_tj6k6xpF8R8uVmPtHQuGBgjvefVOKaKmqeE1mkWnmvdyA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Menbow Ramen Tsawwassen
5000 Canoe Pass Way, Delta, BC V4M 4G8

Nestled within the bustling Tsawwassen Mills Mall, Menbow Ramen offers a convenient spot for shoppers seeking a hearty meal. Located adjacent to the food court, this casual eatery presents a range of Japanese-inspired dishes with an emphasis on ramen.

Food

Takoyaki
Menbow’s takoyaki is a commendable starter. Served warm, the exterior is delicately crispy, while the inside retains a creamy, well-balanced texture. The flavor is satisfying, though not particularly distinctive. A reliable choice for takoyaki enthusiasts.
Rating: 7/10

Shoyu Ramen
The shoyu ramen delivers a robust, savory broth complemented by tender chashu slices. The portion size is generous, making it a comforting option. While it satisfies on all fronts, it doesn’t venture into memorable territory.
Rating: 7/10

Tantan Ramen
This tantan ramen impresses with its creamy broth and nutty undertones. The flavors are rich and balanced, though an extra touch of spice could have elevated the dish. It remains a solid pick for those seeking a slight kick.
Rating: 7/10

Mini Pork Rice Bowl
A standout on the menu, the mini pork rice bowl features succulent, well-seasoned pork paired with perfectly cooked rice. Its balance of textures and flavors makes it one of the more satisfying options.
Rating: 8/10

Deep-Fried Gyoza
Crisp and golden, the deep-fried gyoza is a dependable side dish. The filling is flavorful, though it doesn’t necessarily set itself apart from similar offerings elsewhere.
Rating: 7/10

Chicken Karaage
The chicken karaage, while adequately crispy, falls short of expectations. The seasoning lacks depth, leaving the dish somewhat underwhelming compared to other options on the menu.
Rating: 6/10

Ambiance

Menbow Ramen boasts a clean and modern interior that feels fresh and inviting. Despite being located in a busy mall, the restaurant offers a pleasant escape with its well-maintained space. The self-service kiosk system is intuitive and efficient, streamlining the ordering process.
Rating: 8/10

Service

Service is functional, with staff acknowledging customers without any particular warmth or attentiveness. While it meets basic expectations, the experience lacks the personalized touch that can elevate casual dining.
Rating: 7/10

Price

The pricing is fair and consistent with the portion sizes and quality of the food. Menbow Ramen offers good value for a quick and satisfying meal within a shopping mall setting.

Verdict

Menbow Ramen Tsawwassen offers a reliable dining experience for mall-goers seeking quality ramen and Japanese-inspired dishes. While it may not deliver standout culinary moments, it excels in convenience, cleanliness, and overall consistency. For shoppers in need of a quick, satisfying bite, Menbow Ramen is a commendable choice.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOdJppCTuFoOyKYEiGh_2mEUaLbU5wKqg1tPAIC&fid=0x0:0x5bc528369b8869b6"],"When":"2024-11-29"},{"Name":"Tony Li","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXf8VP49ZjSvgG0JnhT1tc6Tv6OzLL9YEi_yNvwH1rW_K8-7VE=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"After seeing a 2.8 rating, I wanted to go back to Menbow Ramen to see if it deserved that rating or not. If you've been to Japan, you would have experienced ordering your food from a kiosk before sitting down in the restaurant. Thumbs up on that, except when you select the daily special, don't assume I want to order a drink. It's almost as though it is included in the price but it is not. Just don't pick anything and add to cart. I selected take out so when the food came, it was nicely packaged in a covered bowl. Thumbs up on the package. No instructions but its easy to figure it out. Just in case youre not sure, ask before you leave the restaurant. Today it was an Asian guy who served me. He was polite. Other times I've come here, it's been a caucasian lady. She was also pleasant. On their soft opening, there were two chefs. Perhaps they were working out the kinks and they weren't the best public facing individuals minding the store. The broth is delicious. Unlike a lot of ramen joints in Tokyo, the broth is not oily. You can drink it without worrying about the fat. They deserve 4 stars for the ramen. Don't order the chicken karaage. I agree, the taste is off. Squeeze some lemon on it or skip it altogether. And come on Tuesdays when extra noodles are free. If you want chicken, order the Tuesday $3.99 box at KFC. Now that's a finger lickin' deal.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNQvTTC8SI-gJTFkY2PqkcxYweO0hmwn1D--qFS&fid=0x0:0x5bc528369b8869b6"],"When":"2024-12-11"},{"Name":"James Gonzales","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU0unpnU-8mggud0YcgWewTeEH_sT0-3Uzrhx_zm_qDfPS-Nug=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"No more need to go to Vancouver for good ramen places as this has great tasting ramen! Ordered the Tonkotsu and it didn’t disappoint. Flavorful broth and good noodles and toppings. Will come back for sure. (Apologies for the photo as I only remembered to take a shot after having one slurp already).","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPDe10mPlKUouFZs-aytUyvCI5DjUJXMMu_6iAL&fid=0x0:0x5bc528369b8869b6"],"When":"2024-11-18"},{"Name":"John Weng","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKs_ZMy-V1LCA-1Oio_wWVYCOTAIusDw5J00NkliThxbDjhRA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"This is a mixed review, let’s starts with the positive: flavor is acceptable (tonkotsu broth), the place is will lit and looked tidy. Kiosk staff is friendly, the blackshirt(manager?) not so much. The “daily special ramen” which I assumed was some sort of generic sauce to water mix, was extremely salty. Me and my friend both took two bites and agreed it wasn’t paranoia. When we placed the unfinished bowl to the return shelf the kiosk staff asked how was it, I replied a tad salty, very salty. Then the manager overheard that and told me it was impossible because they didnt add soy sauce, and asked whether WE were the ones that added it ourselves. I said no, we never add sauce prior to tasting it as is, and I never claimed they added specifically soy sauce. Whatever they had in the broth was extremely salty. Manager doesn’t even apologize, I shook my head and said it’s alright, never mind and left.

So Mr black shirt whoever you are, you’re giving the staff a bad reputation, because frankly the other staffs are sympathetic and nice.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP6M8dtndA01kooQurJPGx81psflGD5t_8lxU-C&fid=0x0:0x5bc528369b8869b6"],"When":"2024-8-11"},{"Name":"Dave","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocI_LjB1fIYfyDUjgL_-07doYO2DdqKnjIx6lTxP0wGruUckNw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"I just visited this place today Dec 22th which is full of Christmas shopper. To be fair the service isn't bad but the wait time for the food took us half an hour (Miso / Shio and Tan Tan Ramen).

Seeing the review which is 2.8 out of 5 I wasn't have any high hopes of the food, but to my surprise, the ramen isn't that bad at all (Even consider as restaurant quality). Perhaps staffing level would needs to readjust during the holiday rush?","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Ben Ho","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVHpMEx1fjmmf3AWQzf5DR-kr-pRDEx7TvKvnONf8OCMN1eqpeDFg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"The worst miso ramen I have ever eaten. Don't waste money.

The cook is definitely not expected.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPhABLVYP2IWOOTuSrHEeXd_jbKEzZxiME7wQo9&fid=0x0:0x5bc528369b8869b6"],"When":"2024-11-30"},{"Name":"Ray","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXGVd5s-06Fr3JDo-bYWWNiziS7uiGN7g2hEorOk1Vp-qtDK_-cTg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The ramen here is amazing in my opinion! It's on the richer side, very hearty and big fatty melty pieces of pork, which I personally love. They have self service kiosks which is to my liking. I came back multiple times because I loved the ramen, and there's a lot of different flavors.
I liked the black garlic ramen, the tantan ramen and the spicy ramen. All are great though. Love the egg too.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipORQey7vohNQFHHQLSqLm5JRVfdYgZ7nwoksz8s&fid=0x0:0x5bc528369b8869b6"],"When":"2024-1-11"},{"Name":"Mark Kim","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWCF24Za25W7mFVKPV1e78m89_C2VOF21rvAAzkauPiCAfdRgr9=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"I don’t understand the attitude of the manager here… If you dont like people, dont open a business... Taste? what did I expect.. Instant noodle taste better 😖","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMVd0uUOwK7TS47oog7t01BOP6oWLvbXudoJu1j&fid=0x0:0x5bc528369b8869b6"],"When":"2024-9-15"}]

user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Neil King","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX1Q0EM5pZx9WHzCr_pTn-6Omi-lDPJuUwZruVKPcLT89Ccy0-h=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Hands down the best Sushi in the PNW! Every dish is served fresh and made with such care and perfection from the owner/head sushi chef! I highly recommend asking for the Chef's Special whatever it is as it is always the best. And they have always taken such incredible care of my 3 year old daughter. This is her absolute favorite place to eat and has been since she could have solids. There is not a single bad dish on the menu, hot or cold. Definitely visit and enjoy your favorite Japanese cuisine.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNwoNBbh4BPJ8ksW_6VPrlJcshKLefj61I8y_P0&fid=0x0:0x2e5cef454a459987"],"When":"2024-12-20"},{"Name":"Dew Low","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIWRsVIHVBRgzu4BVKN_-yKVWvjyVlDF_H_GDiV_pudumLtpw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Had an amazing dinner here, ordered the dinner bento box and everything was delicious. Authentic Japanese food with fresh sashimi and perfectly fried tempura. Staff were friendly and vibes of the place was relaxing. Highly recommend!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMxQJlZ0fqh6jOP5Tk-ZJjnFGHjEI55tOHSO07N&fid=0x0:0x2e5cef454a459987"],"When":"2024-7-25"},{"Name":"Micaela Robinson","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV2QksgdiepfAQ10tl72lYcRqkt6l1FugMIhmMIfzOnP4rJ1IYySg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"My son and I enjoy coming to Bistro Peekaboo!  We try and make it a weekly thing since it is super yummy and conveniently located across from his Taekwondo classes.  Sometimes, we even able to get in 10 mins before they open when his class is over.

Their sashimi, sockeye salmon is Very fresh and delicious every time.

I've enjoyed a bunch of different rolls here, and they are all good.  A few of my favs are Mango cream cheese roll, crispy pineapple roll, spicy salmon roll, yam tempura roll, miso soup, salmon sashimi and of course saki and Asahi beer!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPRproP8xpnKhZKPN7PCNdG0F6LR2Iz54rgxh9X&fid=0x0:0x2e5cef454a459987"],"When":"2024-5-13"},{"Name":"Karen","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXl4Bs2i46X0UBgHBYM6tmfxeFCxnxMn0HyiqFjx8gCCPLCyH7FFw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The food was good, and the staff were very friendly. The Peekaboo roll was delicious, but the plate it was served on wasn’t ideal for eating. However, it did look great for presentation.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOMrsQaPMSo8NDqyBrpq2OceZdPC0h-Il4N5s6l&fid=0x0:0x2e5cef454a459987"],"When":"2024-9-17"},{"Name":"Ben Ho","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVHpMEx1fjmmf3AWQzf5DR-kr-pRDEx7TvKvnONf8OCMN1eqpeDFg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Just pass by this afternoon and have a wonderful lunch. It definitely the best sushi restaurant in Tsawwassen.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPfdGU2pQPf2tIbaX77W0MLEPs7wQfdz-TDTVdp&fid=0x0:0x2e5cef454a459987"],"When":"2024-9-19"},{"Name":"Anne D","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWcpvA-h-AyBmANCHdhhrDOmLepgyc7gk09U5rqfGXZ7NBfzhU=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Years ago, when people kept telling me about this place, I had trouble finding it. If you get lost, first locate the BC Liquor Store in Tsawwassen and then look across the courtyard. It is a cozy little place, decorated with beautiful architectural drawings and usually playing jazz. The meals are always presented artfully. Personally, I like the creative fusion dishes; just like in many restaurants in Japan. The service is consistently excellent, and I often notice the chefs behind the counter taking time to chat with the clients. My son especially appreciates the vegetarian rolls; very few places combine all his favourites of avocado, cucumber, AND sweet potato in one roll.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMLIEwz9kIk0N1M4VMQF_NwBTz07QlbUiuH9m8M&fid=0x0:0x2e5cef454a459987"],"When":"2023-9-2"},{"Name":"Ray","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXGVd5s-06Fr3JDo-bYWWNiziS7uiGN7g2hEorOk1Vp-qtDK_-cTg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I ordered takeout from here. This was my first time trying oyakodon, then I also ordered the chef special sushi, which was a surprise. The staff was welcoming and the order was very fast, 20 minutes. The employee was also mindful to ask if I would like chopsticks.
Every bite was a flavor sensation! The oyakodon chicken was so soft and there was a savory sauce with tasty onions and egg. The sushi was incredible! I was fully prepared to expect to maybe not like it. I wish I could know what it was exactly, because it was a great flavor I'll never forget.
Both dishes were very filling and satisfying.
Will definitely come back again and recommend to my friends.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMVjvnd4PKO-VTllNME5m55m_oPWSkmXhgaOG-3&fid=0x0:0x2e5cef454a459987"],"When":"2023-11-12"},{"Name":"My Dang","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWuX9KoQSNoXxWT2plnTBiOSoGxIN2IfRotXosxr5iuLPzIRMw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Small and cozy Japanese bistro restaurant with excellent food, wide range of menu and reasonable price. It is a hidden gem in Tsawwassen. It is a wonderful place for solo, or just small group of 4 or less as the space is small and can't fit for larger groups.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPrsGqksrhk03quMKnaaKgKkAOmqfhHWFqTo_iy&fid=0x0:0x2e5cef454a459987"],"When":"2024-1-7"}]

user_reviews: [{"Name":"Chris Lee","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXgN3Ssfvbb1EbijfsAqh9RD9v4HjU3iLte0juEBNWQn45kCyr6=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Needed food, so I picked up a donair and fries to eat in line at the ferries. I sure am pleased with my choice to do so. The donair was packed with lamb and the typical donair wrap ingredients; I enjoyed this. Oh, but the fries! The fries are just crispy and pairs extremely well with the garlic sauce dip.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMy5vRnpRS8EjD-RwQ9FX3xrKjvxBOpHW2EqsPL\u0026fid=0x0:0xf5ba066a46548f4e"],"When":"2024-10-21"},{"Name":"Mike M","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVjCgzb0OJlXCk-WAK9SsEnf3vMl57FpIAZS92vCp5R8BGKs9Q=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Small store but amazing donairs. Best on the West Coast. All the flavors enticing you to another bite. Very large portions if you get an extra meat option. This is the best donair west of Toronto. I am literally smiling from face to face. Don't wait to get to the ferries terminal  ,  stop two blocks away, and your taste buds will thank you forever. Authentic is a word I  don't use very often. This is the place for donair. Awesome food, friendly service, and your stomach and taste buds will love you longtime. The only affair I've ever had on my beautiful wife. I bite of yummynness. Love you and your company....God Bless","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOwO2mphCWc71j3Bhk9cN6QqIUsp8BKXKz7av4\u0026fid=0x0:0xf5ba066a46548f4e"],"When":"2024-3-27"},{"Name":"Hayley Kim","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUbRZ5Wdk8dqms4dVpG-KvC0dBCKi_SRF-K3IwyxC-laGKk9_e0=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"All the staff there are friendly.\nThey made the best kebabs for our family. The best wrap kebab I've ever had! I always miss that place, because I stopped there while I was traveling.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN8GoxyHx64EhXZ74voadITIdfG1ngiVxwLTINF\u0026fid=0x0:0xf5ba066a46548f4e"],"When":"2024-4-24"},{"Name":"Aaron MacEwen","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV3Ky6ximZkKg4l7lYD2oaitNzrrzF59AoquM1M8Z4is8xtKGnG=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"I mean I was working all day and starving.  So why not give a Donair some love.  Service was good your basic fast food.  Flavours were nice.  I’d go back for sure in a pinch.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"K M","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJKXwHJh7B8P0DZJcmF7dG-ROfM4k02K_Xc5rcOlL5lGq_4wdQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Huge portions for its amazing price. The food and sauces are very flavourful. The staff member helping us was friendly and tried to really engage with her customers to get to know them better and ask how their day was. Her cheerful personality and the amazing food deserves this 5 star rating!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOX1LTQ6F_DurKLX5SZSWFdKl3slxrtRWeoKj_f\u0026fid=0x0:0xf5ba066a46548f4e"],"When":"2020-12-23"},{"Name":"Chris Ericksen","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjViMdr5qANv3ULulQPLl_g1GGjwndbSbloLmalGzSvO7G73pBQY9w=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"May have an addiction to this place. The food is awesome. I have been ordering consistently now for about a year and a half. The staff are incredibly friendly and the management is also. I even used them for catering a large outdoor Dinner. I brought them my own catering dishes and other platters, and they were kind enough to put all of their food in them. Sauces and all other condiments were packed caringly in containers. Made the entire event a piece of cake. and most importantly, everybody loved the food.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"MiwitoLikes","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU9Cp-41jfC8lAGC19XcfHcrNAHhObunbBBMPLUw6S7yon19zyo=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Better than any of the drive thru options around - especially since they open late night after long shifts! Solid and consistent portions - service is fast and friendly! One of my favourites to visit in Tsawwassen if you looking for clean food! 😎 rice platter or bowl with extra meat, wraps are easier on the go! 👍🏼👍🏼👍🏼😉","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Nell Andrew","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU3E0E3F9Zbk8X_ZsoD5u-iFtBxecstcnw5dTMU9Ep6bRtahXMn=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"The food here is great, don't get me wrong, but the service is very poor. It's a loud environment, so the employee misheard my order; I ordered the Hawaiian wrap and got a Mayan wrap. When I returned to ask about it, the employee very clearly established that it was my fault and they would not do anything about it. Really sucks, because this used to be my favourite spot and I'm back in town for a visit to get my favourite meal and got shafted.","Images":null,"When":""}]

[{"Name":"C Pedrosa","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWcMDy4tMBdT1bu6DvBAjbPuH68jW3f1qeeNrDCc5DPFdSftMlu=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"I kept seeing ads for their steak and lobster , so we finally caved. We were the second couple to arrive a few minutes before 5 PM.
We got to order happy hour wings. I noted that our server was so personable.  The wings arrived really hot and they were really good.

Our main course was a bit disappointing though.
Spouse ordered the 10 oz steak cooked medium with fries and baked beans. The fries were hard and cold.

I ordered the steak cooked medium with lobster , coleslaw and baked potato. I opted for butter instead of sour cream. The baked potato was just that ! No bacon , no chives.

We did bring up the fact that the fries were cold and our server and the manager brought us a fresh batch of fries.

The dessert , Texas trash pie looked tempting so we ordered it as well. It’s too sweet and I wouldn’t order it again. The female server that brought our dessert to us didn’t even bother to ask or clear our plates. She just handed the plate to my spouse. Makes one wonder if she was ever trained to serve at a restaurant.

Her demeanor was such a contrast to our male server who was fantastic that I felt compelled to ask for his name. Matthais. He set the bar really high for the other servers in that restaurant.   They should all take pointers from him.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNQgS89goYBvIEA4erL8B64IwP41D2hYPg-KXX7&fid=0x0:0x57f9d87194f4dd7f"],"When":"2024-11-18"},{"Name":"Ching-Kai Chiu","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUGbYbS0ggvEFgjque4QRFtJ9y5gnvhUtfu0dvMbXF9kgoqrbF1=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"It is a good place to eat with kids. The kid meals there are valuable. My kid likes kid rib meal for 10CAD. It comes with a small drink, three pieces of ribs, apple slices, and a dessert. On Tuesday, I ordered tacos. With a drink order, each taco costs 5 CAD. It was a good deal.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMFJVdTdlsiZPIYWtPZS_KJ_Lrfe-oeu2o-8kyN&fid=0x0:0x57f9d87194f4dd7f"],"When":"2024-11-15"},{"Name":"leesa tran","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUWsWaHyhzcw7kKPh9V3HkvTK5TTa81TdmCDp9IylYllx4puXIy=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"Disappointed with the whole experience. Took over 30 minutes for each item to come after ordering. Server was a mess with forgetting our orders, than bringing us the wrong order e.g wrong sauce/flavour.

Our food must have sat at the counter for quite some time because our food was room temperature. I’ve never had a room temperature rib before, it was disappointing. Worse part was that the fries were so stale that we couldn’t even eat it.

Only thing that was good was the lobster spinach dip because it was fresh and hot.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOof9qDhGlWOeCXq80fSsim8qsf7Tn95eDzkI8K&fid=0x0:0x57f9d87194f4dd7f"],"When":"2024-12-17"},{"Name":"Cannon Rowe","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocI14kY3cTXxkzCIBbkX1kFfvrwmLcetgnKrtLpCxa4s_TEwXA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"I had high hopes, but it all changed after I ordered, the first thing was that there were clumps of dirt or sand in my water, so I decided to order a drink, my friend did the same. after we got the drinks we had to mix them together because we ordered the same thing, yet one had way to much flavour to the point where it was hard to drink it because it was so sweet, and the other one tasted like they mushed a strawberry and threw it in water. Then when we got our food both of us got a small portion (4 wings and such) when I ordered a larger portion (more food in general) I didn't mind it or want to make a fuss, so I just ate it without saying anything. I want to give this a higher review as the cooks did an amazing job, however I will probably not return to Montanas again, especially this one.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPknbAgwk9uD3azZyveHSvnIriNYbOz_1062dCD&fid=0x0:0x57f9d87194f4dd7f"],"When":"2024-10-19"},{"Name":"chaitanya gupta","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWP-Cx-tNwiu90cNABgEGrEB8sTBdVTRvK_y-kZN0OvutQ-s073wg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Montana’s is an absolute gem when it comes to delivering mouth-watering, finger-licking good food! From the moment you step in, the welcoming atmosphere and rustic decor set the stage for an unforgettable dining experience. The real stars of the show, though, are the dishes that come out of their kitchen.

The Antojitos are nothing short of spectacular. Each bite is a burst of flavor, with perfectly spiced fillings wrapped in warm tortillas that are crispy on the outside and soft on the inside. They're served with a creamy dipping sauce that complements the spices beautifully, making it impossible to have just one.

And let's talk about the Cheesy Bread – a true indulgence for any cheese lover. The bread is baked to perfection, with a golden, crispy crust and a soft, airy interior. Each piece is generously topped with melted, gooey cheese that stretches delightfully with every bite. It's the kind of comfort food that keeps you coming back for more.

Montana’s has truly mastered the art of creating delicious, hearty food that leaves you craving for your next visit. Whether you're there for a casual meal or a special occasion, the Antojitos and Cheesy Bread are absolute must-tries. If you’re looking for a place that serves incredible food in a cozy, welcoming environment, Montana’s is the place to be!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNX0pDkwTuuiS5cMOpHrFRC97aT--PpFwztXTzh&fid=0x0:0x57f9d87194f4dd7f"],"When":"2024-8-3"},{"Name":"Pame Muñoz","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWK-E6q_CKNcU5arueVpZB-EtqA-TtgCe6O8I-mSmV0JU1uRS3m=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The meal was fantastic - the nachos were absolutely delicious and definitely the best we've ever had. Additionally, the pork ribs were exceptionally good. The server attended to us with a pleasant and efficient manner.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOm0M0pEL5v6RoJeh0VoGeXcbtNiwptyW0xcxq-&fid=0x0:0x57f9d87194f4dd7f"],"When":"2024-7-7"},{"Name":"Sam","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUtX0MUDjCE0-vy-dhnXmKj8wSFb2TYmOdItbTBVjUWBQi-9BN1=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Went for all you can eat ribs! Our server Matthais was super nice, easy to talk to and attentive! Ribs were really good, I really liked the coleslaw. I wish I took pictures of the ribs but when I went it was close to last call so I had to eat my money worth!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Andrew Wong","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIGhMmyQR5fEQYPNmFQQ6jAf_8iCZTX8-Tw63p0QAlPVLS2Hw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Empty little joint. Went for lunch. Good value for kids. Burger was big for kids meal but dry, no sauce.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN8qt4IIQnEDEbh33MxcT2oL1T62Sxen_DpS5Tt&fid=0x0:0x57f9d87194f4dd7f"],"When":"2024-10-24"}]

We enjoyed it so much that we ordered from their catering package for a family gathering. The 20 person build your own taco bar had EVERYTHING we needed to have a great meal. [{"Name":"Kamal Sharma","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV7ugyEGknBNNlILf31u0JAbmLdIgL4MRgEDpq5W7GHR4dnFqyK=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Worst Indian food. Uncooked naan! And no matter what you order it’s the same thing just a tweak of different frozen sauce. I went there I was told it was Punjabi and I did confirm with the owner. I would say avoid this place or at least verify yr food. It was $60 waste and so the food ! Pleas don’t do this, the owner !","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOxP-hRUwMAXpkUxqovjd8Fe-2PIDtZvThPE88g&fid=0x0:0x68c8a7d638fd7531"],"When":"2023-5-21"},{"Name":"Lei Ann Shiramizu","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUYUzucb7SgV-kpKbnzOX0XifHnp5tm5dLeArb4HjzF0s91w6Q=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The mission of Connaught Place is simple: serve delicious, affordable food that guests will want to return to week after week. Mission accomplished.

I live in Seattle, so I'm a couple of hours away. But if I could, I would return week after week, and perhaps even day after day. Because coming to Connaught Place is like coming home, even if I'm not Indian.

After a long day of traveling from Salt Spring Island, we needed a quiet dinner to restore ourselves. I chose Connaught Place from the many positive reviews. We found the unassuming eatery tucked behind an office building and peered in the windows to see it empty. With trepidation, we approached the door just as a young woman was pulling up to pick up take out. I asked her how the food was and without hesitating, her face lit up and she said, "Oh my god, it's delicious! Plus, it's family owned and I love to support small business."

Enough said. We slid into a booth and was greeted by the lovely Satbir. She helped us (Indian-food novices), decide what to order based on our input: samosas, naan and lamb korma. She could tell we needed a little pick-me-up and kindly brought us papadum (a crispy wafer-like bread) with mango chutney.

The samosas were hot and tasty, however, the star of the table was the lamb korma. With generous chunks of tender lamb in a rich and creamy sauce, it was the stuff my dreams are made of. Accompanied by a hearty serving of rice, it was plenty for my husband and me. Even after we were satisfied, we kept on heaping food on our plate because we didn't want to miss out on one more bite.

While chatting with Satbir, we mentioned that it was our anniversary and she surprised us with scoops of mango ice cream! Just the thing to top off a memorable meal. We were definitely happy diners.

Throughout the evening, many people came and went from Connaught Place to pick up their to-go orders. But I suggest dining in the relaxing space because not only is the food superb, but Satbir is a delight, and an integral part of a wonderful experience. Oh, and you might want to order more than one main dish because you'll definitely want leftovers.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNwDP86BmOkutA77Dz0l0WGT6IKziVi7Vh0UKnH&fid=0x0:0x68c8a7d638fd7531"],"When":"2023-8-2"},{"Name":"Celestial Producer","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLcwqfWl1gr39vLtzTdQX1KjMjQn0etzAzDHo-cF4Ad1jRuxQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Best Fish Pakora ever and butter chicken ever...real spices...been coming here since they opened ...you can taste the love in their food...amazing family....who ever complains has no idea about food with amazing flavor or they get paid by the competition shame on you🤔 😋
Love you Connaught family xoxo 😘","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Abhinav Jindal","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJM4oZCfhRvIsNadmGhYgIAN02ymUQqZkd-HEyw_g2b22BpSw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We ordered Dal Maharani (Spice level hot) with Naans and Rotis, and it was really amazing. We got a really good portion of Dal (3 of us ate 2 rotis and 2 naans with it), which was surprising these days, but this is the first time I felt authenticity of Punjabi foods in BC. Also, the naans were so soft and not flaky like most of the restaurants these days. It definitely gave a vibe that they care about the food they serve, and I am definitely going to try out other items on their menu.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Katie B Kohn","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIblYPx-vTj1SiHiq7ul29XcTgXHp0t4YJvp8cUkuqUlix18g=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Oh I so wanted this to be good. But I got three dishes and somehow there is *negative* flavor??? I’ve never had curry like this. All grease, no flavor whatsoever. Like none. I also worry a bit about the freshness! Never wasted $80 like this before.

Update: I truly can’t get over how bad this is. Worst takeout ive ever had in my life. Like dirty dishwater. Wish I could get my money back as I’m trashing everything.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Patrick Burns","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXAssgLe-So5tFzU6uhQzJF29bn_SiEFDR-ANfbxHT4XQ2Re0Cp=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"It was very good. The Dal was perfect, exactly what I was craving and as good as anywhere. I also got Tandoori Chicken which was very good as well. The Naan was very good. Very flavorful and delicious. The rice was good too.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Alexander Voogd","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXaTUk3xqJzVvRr4_f1So4GR3nta8yXgA6objuo8ac7X7-7X3xvew=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Awesome food, we've been coming to Connaught for about 20 years now. Lovely husband and wife team running it. One of our friends we introduced to this restaurant,  an Indian food connoisseur, stated it to be the best she's ever had.
Please support our local people.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Paula Jean Lloyd","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLbZFu_mGLrykOVNo31ykayvJBF_JZRsYi8V16apprugDNNfg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"We ordered. The food came way too spicy. They replaced it with something less than cooked. The service was terrible. Big mistake . This is my first negative review ever.","Images":null,"When":""}]

[{"Name":"Michael Lacson Ello","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJus38Jm8x4a4FpscwrnNrQTjVBeHPRdqtc6sWQWa80xSZEdw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"The taste of the food was great , the portion of food per order is amazing, packaging was ok , price is reasonable and affordable, service is excellent the Filipina lady works so fast and very friendly but needed a little bit more smile and I know she’s already tired and it got busy when I place my order that’s why she can’t smile anymore and I can see that she’s working with the new staff I overheard that she’s doing training for the new staff because of that good job . I didn’t have 5 star for now because the consistency of the quality and texture of the food is failed for me because I got the newly cooked fried rice some of the rice was still hard and it needed little more time to cooked well before serving to all the guest second the spicy chicken that I got is hard to chew it’s little bit chewy and some hard as well then the rest everything was ok but

I still definitely recommended to everyone to visit this branch in Tsawwassen Mill to taste their lots of different varieties of food it’s affordable and delicious. 👍","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPWIrBC170gEsNzs_NQCvpebQNR22-pWbSeQuae&fid=0x0:0x2258541a2226475e"],"When":"2024-11-24"},{"Name":"No MSG No Garlic Foodie","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX-PVOn6GcWxsKb-qqVJDTqvJ5rfua5QVuFocwcMF-ZRwuEIPLm=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"We first encountered Bourbon Street Grill in Richmond Centre. I couldn't believe it when they told me that they don't use MSG in their food. And they have my favourite food – BBQ chicken, BBQ pork, fried noodles, and of course mixed vegetables. However, we discovered that there is a catch – chopped garlic is as common an ingredient as salt, and there's garlic in everything. But if we wanted to eat a balanced meal with a decent amount of cooked vegetables, that's what's available. We stopped by the mill before heading out to the ferry to grab a bite to eat. I was going to have a simple Chachi's sandwich but would prefer more vegetables, and Bourbon Street Grill is the next stall. But the food was almost not edible because of the amount of salt in the food. I ate less than half and left the rest. We've since gone back again in case there was a different cook. But same thing, the honey mustard chicken was over-spiced and everything was too salty. Even our friend who lives locally and is a fan of Bourbon Street Grill is not keen to visit this particular outlet. I do wonder if that's the reason they are not that busy!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMp2LX-PWUjs1v1GYVHpQW7qQHdPLFe25EuezSF&fid=0x0:0x2258541a2226475e"],"When":"2023-7-11"},{"Name":"Sukh jas","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKdZXO1s-FXEoal1FhYT-Pim0I2Ssia3Zer5WEGjGTRrnjXDQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"rice was mixed with day old rice. The chicken was Dried up. This place is not good. I informed the manager that the rice almost broke my tooth it was that hard. I suggested to her to through out the rice but she said it was fresh. I did not ask for money back but rather get rid of the bad food and she would not. I told her you can not feed this to the public. She kept on selling it. I will never go back.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"J Doyer","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXPPny9TtiK51znrVGw_mfnuA8ZqG4xTW9w4c-Vn42z-UkUntwsVg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We are from up north, decided to stop in quickly for a bite to eat.
