user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Bruno Rodrigues","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXhILuyIb0LIP6MudwbcSE2BAlE-f9U9SKRT2p9lsRwJ4hM0FgDLg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"One of the best places at UBC to hang out! Lovely staff and wonderful vibe. Tried the grilled chicken ramen and it was generously filled, almost couldn’t finish the whole meal. Other friends of mine ordered burgers and they said they were fantastic. Prices aren’t cheap, so it’s a place to go for a celebration once in a while.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPCAcUJj4YsDoBohcTlkfqkVoKoS5nD30m0xhBk&fid=0x0:0xefc97cb7df41fcd0"],"When":"2024-12-22"},{"Name":"M J","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKuOygw8Aep3D50DIY1TUyT5-BADbHqefvUMdU3qf0JomdEvw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Great selection of food and craft beer, good place to hang out for a few drinks. The small nachos was enough for us to share between 4-5 people, loved the roast beef sandwich too. Deep fried Mac and cheese was nicely cooked and the tomato sauce helps with the heaviness of the Mac and cheese. Ordered the IPA and loved it - crisp and had a nice aroma. The service was fast and attentive although it was busy at the time of visit.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMXcjzjGRoyy6vduMIRbCuk6WLqez6jCJo-pmrv&fid=0x0:0xefc97cb7df41fcd0"],"When":"2024-7-4"},{"Name":"Dylan Magierek","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV0kVFJpnKEbseG6UEIeqqL4lraFc9x941pplBP3I-C35nxYYtP=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"This was a nice sojourn from a long day of driving and walking around the UBC campus moving my son into the dorms.  The food was very good: especially the fries, chicken sandwich, side salad and burgers.  The French Dip was just pretty good.  I wouldn’t recommend it.  It didn’t have enough meat to balance out the kinda hard roll it came on.  Lots of beer choices and I enjoyed the Pilsner.  Expensive for a brewery/sorta pub!  But good service and atmosphere.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM9A45j3pzrU9X5vPV34VvyOZ59GJCSIADcF_aQ&fid=0x0:0xefc97cb7df41fcd0"],"When":"2024-8-30"},{"Name":"Anthony Le","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWIC22IEsZIbsu-lUm5EyMjgm7JYJbJkRjU13-W8XkZYXAuixkB6Q=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Nice place for a sit-down, fancy-ish meal. The drinks were pretty good, and the food is delicious; definitely a nice place for a formal meal.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOE7MmrhhKXG2H5sjxLe8eW9H0WqnR-Tuz2xtla&fid=0x0:0xefc97cb7df41fcd0"],"When":"2024-10-22"},{"Name":"Vanessa Becker","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVjP-M2atXZC7s46eJ4wd5XC-RHr2pn3fRoPwoLQqghdxSrQBA9=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Browns is a nice pub type spot. We got seated quickly for lunch and our server was friendly and attentive. Drinks and food came out at decent times.
My sister has celiacs disease and had heard Browns has gluten free options. They were able to make modifications on a meal and she enjoyed it, Blackened chicken Caesar with no croutons.
I got a cheeseburger with Caesar salad.
There’s a ramp and accessible entrance and chairs can be moved to fit wheelchairs.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNgyStbHqW6IqBgmoutJLEDmIuxPuu1FMQBsNe6&fid=0x0:0xefc97cb7df41fcd0"],"When":"2024-5-19"},{"Name":"Maria N","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVvvSp5rMnSOuZlWMjCChnc3kIAvhaXhf7fzSVxvOmtGCdirlnS=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Tasty food and quick service. There were barely any customers when we came in on Saturday afternoon.
We got a chicken burger with a side of fries and a salad with a chicken breast (came a bit late.) Both tasted good.
Very decent place to grab a bite around UBC.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMh6lhWfsmLChgTOHHA4RM65-xzqYFv7EYhpgf5&fid=0x0:0xefc97cb7df41fcd0"],"When":"2024-6-23"},{"Name":"Biggie Sandhu","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJJXTSWG9GRBzr7s-0VIl70S37U8PyPayiekKKBiKbK7ygPFA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Had our work Christmas Dinner here. Great workers great food.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNMIthBnLk1en1HwdUUDWZ3GIt9z3pNtalz6zAt&fid=0x0:0xefc97cb7df41fcd0"],"When":"2024-12-18"},{"Name":"Zibiah Sandhu","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIV7J0QaWpaOWLAzK9jqKBW9H-FOCY6ViMt-aqG3Okqi6IgVQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I am following up from my previous review that I had left a few weeks ago. Despite having a negative experience, the staff at Browns Crafthouse went above and beyond to make sure that my friends and I had a good experience to make up for what had initially happened. The manager Matt reached out and was very kind and generous, and offered to make the experience better for us. They accommodated drinks and many appetizers for our large group, and were super sweet the entire time. I cannot remember our servers name, but she was a tall caucasian woman. She provided excellent service and took my friend's gluten allergy very seriously. It was some of the best customer experiences I had. Matt himself had come out and greeted us, apologized for the previous experience, and made sure we had a great time. They went above and beyond to make sure that we had a good experience, and it was really appreciated!","Images":null,"When":""}]

[{"Name":"James","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXqV7s1ERcFGfwshWd43fVj2drCe4Q_9Q7yrW7t1yUcOV4l1RPe-Q=s120-c-rp-mo-ba7-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Classic American-style family-run diner serving hearty portions. I cannot stress how delicious their home-style potatoes are. They are thin slices similar to hash browns and cooked well.

While their menu doesn't have any food items that are exceptionally unique, you cannot go wrong with any of the choices.

The servers are nice and more than accommodating. Since there is no jam on the table for the toast, they'll happily provide that upon request.

On weekend brunch time, there is usually a wait, but they have plenty of indoor and outdoor dining seating in a rustic, open-air environment","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMyIqzVx3IpllwN0NYjD2vUnR7CIcaS_Rr9pzJQ&fid=0x0:0x4cb6776373016f4d"],"When":"2024-9-2"},{"Name":"Sunaina","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVhxDKiFQe8a5C5Tb2aKE23SI0Kdk4IWaJpX4r1npsWHQupcLu6Fw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Cute little brunch spot with both indoor and outdoor seating. Prompt service & friendly servers. We started with lattes, and got the smoked chicken chorizo scrambled eggs which came with potatoes and cornbread & the pancake combo with chicken apple sausage. My favorite was the pancake dish, I loved it! I’m a bit picky about how eggs are cooked in general so it’s hard for me to find the perfect egg dishes and they usually end up feeling mediocre. I’d love to try a different dish next time!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMoaz6Rnm3N-dY6FYKx-rnbHA_6iaS4gM8J5Dmp&fid=0x0:0x4cb6776373016f4d"],"When":"2024-3-22"},{"Name":"Cedrik Laplante","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX1fiDdQR57hkQayUOrLLKYe8hRwMHRj-f-yp8FEv14uvHM2DY_=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Food was divine especially the cinnamon butter for those fluffy pancakes! Eggs Benedict was good too. The stuffed French toast though! You really can’t go wrong but it is a little pricey","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPMff6FXvb3YAW-_H7khRSdB1hlvVuL9LSUYiLp&fid=0x0:0x4cb6776373016f4d"],"When":"2023-9-20"},{"Name":"Arthur Glauberman","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUF_clVoSZmScPHXT5Ms-BUb8Jmo72X-xWBoI2U0vBLB_o86Ax6=s120-c-rp-mo-ba8-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We just  discovered the Doyle Street Cafe which has a very exotic breakfast & lunch menu! While they are only open til 2pm, I’m told that on the weekends, there are lines outside, waiting for a table!  We had the most delicious breakfast., their DELMAR CREPE: crab cakes, caramelized onions, mushrooms, jack cheese inside a large crepe, served with best best home fries i’ve ever tasted!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNIuvHeXFBk2pELCG999j6ocLAx-qJgjFeUYGS9&fid=0x0:0x4cb6776373016f4d"],"When":"2024-2-20"},{"Name":"Elijah H.","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUhuMCL5qE_XwEF9xoarhFX8pVzbLM9hf5AbaEeTk94dnpjTm1bkA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I have been going here for years now, and it never gets old. This is one of those true 5/5 restaurants for me. The brunch here is PHENOMENAL, I've never had a complaint about the food here, and it always comes out quick, hot, and full of flavor. I highly recommend the Egg Benedicts (pulled pork and salmon), French Toast, and my recent favorite, the buttermilk pancakes (so fluffy and perfectly made). The potatos are always crispy and well seasoned, and my gf absolutely loves the bacon (with 0 regard to my bank account). The inside seating is nice but we usually sit outside when the sun is out. I love introducing people to this location it's one of my absolute favorites. Stop reading this review and just GO! (Food is a tinnyyy bit pricy but it's so worth it for the flavor/portion/service/ etc.)","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOolZVK2EJo6AXEdOQSEScqlyZr2ASboK6fy7mb&fid=0x0:0x4cb6776373016f4d"],"When":"2023-6-24"},{"Name":"BG M","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJ8ECc16Mqcli5HD65XbZIbBjpKfCFjUv72aQZNNL0AmxPyYw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Love this place. The food looked and tasted delicious. Server was friendly and the food came pretty quickly. Had the stuffed French toast, breakfast potatoes, scrambled eggs, bacon, but we got there too late and they were out of the cornbread. Must be delicious too. Relaxing ambiance, perfect brunch spot. Five stars.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOcxDrDM-lC8bRSqgiZLRlbCN0xr_l0sz5EnAPI&fid=0x0:0x4cb6776373016f4d"],"When":"2021-6-26"},{"Name":"Mal Pinlac","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocL4GxsuuBPotT1R6zutCydr7dJUoU9VskrlylQ9SY1q7Oc7QQe4=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This is my fave brunch place in Emeryville. The food always comes out  fresh and hot, coffee tastes great, the vibe is perfect and they have free parking. You'll want to get in before 11:30am otherwise the lunch crowd starts pouring in. Regardless of how busy the place gets, it seems they are able to keep up with the pace and get you seated, get your order and turn it around in under 10 minutes. There does not seem to be a bad choice on the menu and you usually have a choice between inside or patio seating 👍👍.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMct-elkow2r1AGaEdXHNJIOr9EQvlzaMIdz1GK&fid=0x0:0x4cb6776373016f4d"],"When":"2023-11-30"},{"Name":"Travis Hull","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUKxQxZ2Fw0iXg479yIzmfs1rvM-h6CiHCTG8-FuzNmS2uW6kb0NA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Wow, great American diner experience! Never ending cups of black coffee, giant portions, friendly service. The Homefries Heaven was more food than I could possibly eat, and of course I ate most of it. My girlfriend got the combo breakfast with French toast, bacon and eggs over easy. Super delicious as well, the cinnamon butter spread is really good. The atmosphere is busy but relaxed with the chatter of busy brunch goers in the background. 10/10 would recommend if you’re in the neighborhood. Thanks!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPgbDzpEacfxQrryeeFvQPKRZn95SEiDcJwj6Oz&fid=0x0:0x4cb6776373016f4d"],"When":"2023-10-14"}]

[{"Name":"Bruno Rodrigues","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXhILuyIb0LIP6MudwbcSE2BAlE-f9U9SKRT2p9lsRwJ4hM0FgDLg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Loved my experience at the Gallery. Ordered burgers with salads and my friends also ordered some chicken wraps and fries. Everything was pretty tasty and well seasoned. Beers were fantastic. Prices a little bit on the high side, especially for a restaurant inside campus, but it’s definitely worth trying.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOs1KGPNL5W9iWl4zIgcxQSrnJ2fRONlu24N4UE&fid=0x0:0x7b84d3debc8f1cec"],"When":"2024-12-20"},{"Name":"Anthony Le","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWIC22IEsZIbsu-lUm5EyMjgm7JYJbJkRjU13-W8XkZYXAuixkB6Q=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Pretty good place for a nice meal for ubc students. There wasn’t necessarily any service, but nonetheless the food was pretty good. Definitely would go here for a drink it I was a ubc student","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP9K99fN-Zftq2MUemombIFm2bz26P8kglKa8XA&fid=0x0:0x7b84d3debc8f1cec"],"When":"2024-10-22"},{"Name":"Randal Chin","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU-rLwNvZI_YNkKUeSaM-3PNFSDfyyf9aevvVnQDsEtEwj3jDdP=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"The dining room is spacious and has lots of natural light making it a good spot for lunch. During lunchtime there was no loud music playing so I could have a conversation with a friend. You order food and drinks at the bar, but I got both pretty quickly. I had a red sangria which seemed reasonably good. I had a citrus and beet salad which was also good but not very filling if you're expecting it to be a meal. The service from the staff serving the food and clearing the table seemed reasonably good.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Dana Sullivan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWQIw-0oOUNgoyniYugTscGkgpKJS8tpx4V0tAajn3ZGkNIfqEk=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"I like this place. I wouldn't go here as a night out, but at the right times, it's a chill hang. The atmosphere varies wildly depending on the day. On some nights it's louder and is in line with what you'd expect a university bar to be like, and sometimes it's very relaxed, and you can even find some people using it as a study spot (not something I would consider or really recommend, but you do you as long as it's not busy and no one needs the table). Sometimes it's somewhere in between or a weird mix of both. It's not always predictable, but I've found that to hit the quieter days that I prefer, early evening during exam season at school is best, and summer in general are chiller than the main academic year.
The food is good, often surprisingly good. The menu items are well thought-out and tasty, and nicely presented. It's not a veg-centric establishment but there's lots of choice for vegans! Off the current menu, I've had the Power Punch Salad, the Vegan Pulled Jackfruit, the Vegan Burger, Vegan Chick'n Caesar Wrap, and the Tempeh Teriyaki. I wasn't particularly impressed by the Caesar wrap - it wasn't awful, I just didn't feel like it was worth $19.5, but everything else was a delight. I'm glad their vegan burger is a (seemingly) housemade, minimally processed black bean patty instead of beyond meat or similar! I usually won't order a salad as my meal, but the Power Punch is substantial! The side salad that comes with the sandwich orders is actually pretty nice too.
They make good cocktails and have a long list of local draft beers on tap which I haven't really had a chance to dip into, but I got the "Green Bird" for fun on St. Patrick's Day, which is just a version of their house "T-Bird" lager that's been coloured green (maybe naturally, judging by the grassy notes I got from it, but I don't know for sure). It was actually a good lager though!
Sometimes the staff is nice enough, sometimes I get the vibe that they're too cool to be serving me or something, but because the only interactions you have with them are when you order and pay at the bar and when they bring your food out, an unenthusiastic bartender doesn't ruin the whole experience. Because of this service style, you can expect to be in and out of here faster than you would at a full table service restaurant, but it's not fast food, so dishes still take as much time to prep as they would at a "regular" sit-down place. It's also pricier than typical counter service food, but very reasonably priced compared to off-campus restaurants that serve food of this quality, and there's no obligation to tip 20%. To me, the service model, fair prices, and high quality are a combination of the best elements of counter service and full service.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOQwEdJ88aXsSlarpRs-9jcRwBTBo0B-hIa3KfE&fid=0x0:0x7b84d3debc8f1cec"],"When":"2021-4-19"},{"Name":"Steve Morgan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXmgrmzSyB3CC_qWamR3pXmaZna6-RxfqDluiFzTGNrypDReGc=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Very large service area. Games. Foosball table. Big patio. Not the least bit crowded for lunch in summertime. They have a limited menu but it has decent variety. Quality of the food is good for a university joint. Beer list contains a good number of local, craft beers. Kids can dine here but no kids menu.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPovaBoxIJBbbrqqo0D1-7ZOWCRu2vS1WYswiw&fid=0x0:0x7b84d3debc8f1cec"],"When":"2019-7-10"},{"Name":"N","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIY4v8Faubu_Z2iYv4KPw3dI0PsoX4C2vKMs2dyC6KeQw7f0Q=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Almost no service (walk up to bar to order) and any service you do get is most often unfriendly. Like the type of attitude you would think takes more effort than being nice. They are not making a case for autogratuities in general because I think this is one of the reasons this place gets away with such unpleasant staff. The other reasons include that there just isn't that much choice on campus and the food is basic but decent here. The view is nice if you're out on the patio. And there's a lot of space. It's very sad that the sit-down nice restaurant didn't make it because that's exactly what the area needs. They just didn't promote it and since this is the top floor, no one discovers this space by walking by. The service at the Gallery when it was in the old sub was never this sad. Have pride in whatever you do. Just making people happy and not disappointed is a reward in itself. Or fake it. Whatever. Just don't make people more down than when they came in.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Jade","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWyJzoLeWrDhvC2NhSPJXZCJklxu-S39z3hI0-Hrrv9m9AA5ZkKQQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"This is my first review below 5 stars.
They automatically charge a tip without telling their customers (I didn't notice any signage). This makes their prices misleading. Also, since I wasn't with a group and I ordered at the register auto-grat does not seem reasonable. I will happily change my review and return as a customer when they are more forthcoming about their prices.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Haleh Magnus","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUZGl2rvHWlqbzuuFKZ9pHQfQXwlTmRHH4ep4A1K4mjlsDM4dQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I went there for a light food, beer and to listen to good #jazzmusic from amazing musician of UBC Jazz Club. The space was bright , spacious. I found it busy and big line up. The Jazz performance are on Wednesday 6pm to 9pm by UBC Jazz Club.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPIUZZN56p20ZRBTeW6npihhigzi31LzbVDTis&fid=0x0:0x7b84d3debc8f1cec"],"When":"2022-9-22"}]

This has become my to go food place :)","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMJtnYd6yS-h-3XGUnWH15MFjWbtolyyiBi0gUG\u0026fid=0x0:0xe4456a08a1c33572"],"When":"2024-7-3"},{"Name":"Yesong Park","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUZ91KZByxRVp7hNBb-aKt5xKC5uCcHWJErPks1BHnBM5NsPqdN=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Easy to order, super quick pickup, and the Vegetarian Kimchi hotdog was good (I am from South Korea 🤣👍). The staff were kind💚 Looking forward to coming back. Thank you!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNRlR3UB5562u53xdhKrOsGJiz4rkZrE-p0ZaKU\u0026fid=0x0:0xe4456a08a1c33572"],"When":"2024-10-2"},{"Name":"Monique Williams","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV5hu9g1OY7Ix0dBixz7zsHrRgMIwTKO5A1wsJR8uSbYtgX4VMh=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"One of the best and unique hot dogs I’ve ever had! Got the vegetarian kimchi with marble cheese… and the Seoul chicken dog… SO DELICIOUS!! And the service was great, she was really nice and helped me choose the best options :)","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMxGps2TpWl4ZaIo9igfjKn_o84hHy6SiiGWHBt\u0026fid=0x0:0xe4456a08a1c33572"],"When":"2024-8-14"},{"Name":"Dana Sullivan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWQIw-0oOUNgoyniYugTscGkgpKJS8tpx4V0tAajn3ZGkNIfqEk=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Lots of cool choices for hotdogs and very vegetarian-friendly since you can get a veggie sausage with any of the dogs on the menu (not as vegan-friendly since most options include mayo and/or cheese). The guy who works there is super nice. There are also Korean subs and other snacks, and bingsu. They use a good veggie sausage and the toppings are always fresh. The hot dogs and snack foods are very reasonably priced, the bingsu are more splurge-y, but they are pretty big. The shop is very small, but the buzzer system they have works well, so you can wait for your order outside and get a buzz to pick it up.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOQM6Ga7Xs7_kR11FSzwpQzsjueEtvJo9hL6iqh\u0026fid=0x0:0xe4456a08a1c33572"],"When":"2023-8-12"},{"Name":"J Psk","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJysbWTRrHYTp8s-srkk4zt31Bl_q_WrtM2a-GsVp2w2ODMSw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Don't order the chi-bap (fried chicken rice) whatsoever. What I got was comletely different from the photo on the menu. The chicken is not fried chicken at all, they use oven baked chicken nuggets. The corn salad had like 3 grains of corn. NOT worth 15$ at all...","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO7aidT799VL6AA3Zdo-Tt2GjLqBpKF4IutJdaK\u0026fid=0x0:0xe4456a08a1c33572"],"When":"2024-9-10"},{"Name":"NixOil","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWa0-gf5561LR0YaDvsEO2rH9HzBIiXnz8EIWyrMmynW44HE3yV=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The best hotdog I have ever had in my entire life. This place was super fast and the hotdog was just amazing. I got the pizza dog which sounds weird but was so good that I had to review this place.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPV_LPo5uQklvQIOPMQmDjk9t5JYYTmqDNQoyQC\u0026fid=0x0:0xe4456a08a1c33572"],"When":"2023-12-30"},{"Name":"K","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocK8Kffru-eJ-MFdAxDjN_kWwnt7cEHBHmGbUwwPuMFBkRwEcGM5=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Best hot dog place we’ve ever been to! The hotdogs were juicy, tasted fresh, and all of the toppings went so well together. We ordered 2 kimchi hotdogs ($9 each) and 2 seoul hotdogs ($10 each). Not going into lie, we had some difficulty finding this place but we would definitely come here again.  there’s not really a place you can sit and eat because it’s just a bench right outside the place, and you’re likely going to be harassed by birds so be cautious when you’re eating lol. The food took a bit of time (15 to 20 minutes maybe?) to make but we weren’t in a rush and there was only 1 guy making all the hotdogs fresh in front of us. Highly recommend this place if you’re at UBC!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOyyvUswrdO-Ws48fgWp7Nkh-O9hEzBay1CETlT\u0026fid=0x0:0xe4456a08a1c33572"],"When":"2023-11-13"},{"Name":"Marvin","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIOUB9fqPRyAnJAGsLqhyOV_Bp81x_bJC8wIyyATYNP2vGJzmc=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Small little shop with amazing customer service. Guy at the front was very welcoming and nice. Hot dog was pretty good, a little expensive for what it was but still great. Definitely will be back to try some other stuff.","Images":null,"When":""}]

[{"Name":"Selina Zhou","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUdh_K07G_35WE1XQolPePKtbRPCS7etPd4GO37eQJrOR8PInDd=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Mercante is a great place to visit, and I urge you to, especially for their pizzas. However, as great as it tastes, it is clear that over the two years I have been going there, the amount of arugula they have been adding has decreased drastically.

Maybe it is just shrinkflation, or maybe nobody likes arugula, but regardless, that is disappointing nonetheless.

Stick to the pizzas with pesto or tomato sauce, they are absolutely amazing, the ones without are quite bland.

The crust is some of the best you’ll ever taste, or maybe all my years of never trying pizza this fresh ruined my tastebuds.

If I were to recommend a particular pizza, it’d definitely be the pesto pollo! It’s simple, pesto with chicken and mushrooms but it is a joy to eat.

The pizza is quite fast, cooked in around 10 minutes, and there are plenty of seating as well.

I tried the pasta once when it first came out… and it was basically just reheated in a shoddy take-out container. Incredibly disappointing compared to the pizzas.

The mini caprese salad has the best sauce I’ve ever eaten, so even if the price is a bit steep, worth it imo.

Anyways, please visit! And enjoy some of the pizza pictures I’ve taken over the years.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP8dRluJ1Y1QIiw864urKWtZC0j-aWF2bSdF9bd&fid=0x0:0x2199ac3872d942ea"],"When":"2024-10-20"},{"Name":"B W (Battery)","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV2VcTxYkMGGx4jwVvZYc_zLzH45KC5E2wcm69COre1h2Q43jQG=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"The pricing for the pizzas increase further and further BUT the quality and portion size of each pizza decreases. The flavour of the pizza is decent (not justifiable for the price). Compared to in 2021 the toppings added have been less and less (You can see in the photos below, One with less arugula is recently taken)","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOEaFBwrMdmz38q6u4vdNNgNito6eNO4ARACcrh&fid=0x0:0x2199ac3872d942ea"],"When":"2024-12-6"},{"Name":"charles bai","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVivIWOvTOamsgiucoqI5EKukhiOsZqTk7nog1iV-Y1Xav6PIczow=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Pizzas were ok. The dough is most as chewy as I’d like. The underside was a bit too charred for my liking. But other than that, it tastes like you would expect an Italian pizza to taste.

But what is that $7 for such a small slice of tiramisu…","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPyDKLlV2mlf_ToQxfsaQiVcIBUIa9jTyxTTki9&fid=0x0:0x2199ac3872d942ea"],"When":"2024-7-9"},{"Name":"JuChul Park","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJBl2ZXIT6h1ADZaXOEj0qdwPy-q7Gry2PxCal1RfLk4LIaRQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Wow, a hidden treasure inside UBC~
The coffee was a bit disappointing, but the pizza was the best. Since it's not a coffee shop, it would be perfect to just have it with coke^^","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNLPEGB-CaG0qEI3Tio6TacurZsxD_EtFBBO-5W&fid=0x0:0x2199ac3872d942ea"],"When":"2024-9-18"},{"Name":"Ryan Tsang","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVH174LmUPGzeC52GF3Com64V8GOYDH3Xrkt6Q91uXjQsUYZcmm4g=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"If you look at the menu someone else posted here, you can see that they have increased the price per pizza by $4 over 8 months. I paid $17 for this pizza bianca and I’m not even full. My friend did recommend the prosciutto tho. Just want to point out that you can get so much more pizza at fatih for the same price

Edit: went back to try the prosciutto, it’s a good, honest pizza on its own. It’s just that you can get more at other places for the same price","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPp8saw9uH9ksnbeKVj66TlamGY5BnRRiu2byMD&fid=0x0:0x2199ac3872d942ea"],"When":"2022-10-17"},{"Name":"Jane Shi","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWFWHgQId1z1gpOQAZDnSRuOfaVawcViBKqphYyzzEF887Ye7SC=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"I really like the pesto pollo pizza, however, it's price has gone from $13 4 years ago, to $19.45 now🥲 also it sometimes gets overcooked","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipODyyebpBbceGXMlNKDmaaFIc4DVQsrJKSrXt05&fid=0x0:0x2199ac3872d942ea"],"When":"2024-4-21"},{"Name":"Aihua Jiang","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXiIXew8o1uyfdMhPFiSNro9u7WkSI3CgBfNp4g3MiTBjo4SQPa=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Kids said that this was the best pizza they ever had! People here were super nice too!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOM3ppLtWgktr3TfhuELY8yq_Y6r7Nppem_rQVI&fid=0x0:0x2199ac3872d942ea"],"When":"2024-7-11"},{"Name":"Tanisha K Johnson","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLWKo2zP2bT5gefRcCNDXbo6jtsCNqEJZkafWXJiSZYIcvJbw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"The food itself is good, but the young Asian server at the front desk treats my friend madly. so rude! I felt disappointed since I am no stranger to the shop. Will reduce visits.","Images":null,"When":""}]

user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Dana Sullivan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWQIw-0oOUNgoyniYugTscGkgpKJS8tpx4V0tAajn3ZGkNIfqEk=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Reliable for simple and satisfying homestyle Korean food. Nothing blows me away but everything is good and flavourful. The meals all include lots of vegetables which I appreciate, and things aren't overly oily.
There's no atmosphere to speak of and I think they probably have more takeout than dine-in customers, but having done both, dine-in is the way to go, because the food comes out super fresh. The people who work there are nice and hardworking.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNXR2zL3EAW7SvQOTWGiznVuK83Eyw_nBeqY_6G&fid=0x0:0x4ab7ff7074636253"],"When":"2024-2-25"},{"Name":"Yuchang Zhan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJCu1wqeMUBpitsBVSAyQ29MPKUdyLQ__YQ2QBJ3AHY3DJY3g=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Went several times and recommended to all my friends. The owners are truly caring about the customers and always have THE BEST service ever. Once I mentioned I was cold, and later the owner offered me warm miso soup for free. This really made my entire evening.

Soups are always served warm with large portion. The pork bone is absolutely my to-go dish. So flavourful with so so much meat!

Never disappointed with their inari, I have tried beef, spicy salmon, shrimp, spam, tuna, kimchi, seaweed, some were even gifted by the owner. All the toppings are so delicious and flavourful, it’s hard for me to pick one favourite to be honest! The seasoning of rice makes everything even another level.

Foods are so authentic. My Korean friends said the dishes really brought them back to Korea. If you love Korean foods like me, you should definitely try it out!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNM3_rcDUbPQB4N10byn-i2gBKLWgdvTB41RrFy&fid=0x0:0x4ab7ff7074636253"],"When":"2022-3-10"},{"Name":"Sasha Sadiora","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXqMB9CioB05yUeMJrchJN57cOo1BuZF_w3T8u4DS8Px3X91XTp=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"The lady was very nice but the fact I paid a EXTRA $3.50 for cheese and got a KRAFT SINGLES slice is CRAZY","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMLwLofol73ghxQyaPInWLd2gYRGqz6pWOzjLKe&fid=0x0:0x4ab7ff7074636253"],"When":"2024-9-12"},{"Name":"Niloufar Sharif","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX3A88lqgzyr_DZVby4DylCumivfYhcpesHqnFk78Ei2iZVsggWWg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"As a student, this place is so comforting and the food tastes authentic and homemade. The owners here are AMAZING, so caring, and kindhearted! They gifted us three free inaris to try as well as miso soup! Now the food. The portions are so generous and they will not cheap out on quality or amount of protein despite the affordable prices.
We got the gamja-tang and galbitang. The galbitang has a very clean broth and you can taste the fresh ingredients. Gamja-tang was packed with flavors and spices and soooo much pork!

Cant wait to go back and try all of their other dishes 😋","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMNkVy2Nj_O8RT1_bytgunpwMTz22R8HjUrX_Hu&fid=0x0:0x4ab7ff7074636253"],"When":"2022-3-6"},{"Name":"Ahnaf Muqset Haque","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU9JdQZtXBMvD618JDWqRmaMkXk-I2NhqdPuW2NLQFP33Qn87KikQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"The only reason for my four star is their  customer service is heart warming. Really welcoming and good service. However, if you are actually looking for really really good Korean food then this probably isn't the place. It's okay as I would describe it but definitely not the best. Also, quantity is not adequate. However, trying to improve quantity first would be resonable step towards improvement!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPATOMJVNA_QXKyqiMpX11OXghmAXYiZDhRB6OR&fid=0x0:0x4ab7ff7074636253"],"When":"2019-4-19"},{"Name":"Anne W","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVq8l7IxqCBT6CUTt6a8ydNheNQQYDJZKBxOYNsNiNzdtSpTCtW=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The quality of the food here is excellent! I got the Jjajang Beef Udon today and it's now one of my favourite meals on campus. The sauce is delicious, as is the side of pickled daikon. The sauce is generous, so I might be able to get a side of rice and stretch it to two lunches (helpful with the high cost of living these days!).

Staff are lovely and helpful people. The outdoor seats on a good weather day are in the sun, so it's a great spot to enjoy your lunch. So glad this place is here!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP2GSZ-Y2SmizoNXA-E9OpCto2VOEvGfTSaozkJ&fid=0x0:0x4ab7ff7074636253"],"When":"2023-3-21"},{"Name":"Coline","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLbX_QKuaEf6ecbnocWzjer3WudYneLMe_JJVgbs8i0ijFAVg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"I ordered Inari, it’s ok. The meat or topping to rice proportion was a bit off. There’s more rice than topping. I ordered 3 but it’s not enough, and it came out to be around 14$ so I’ll say just order a regular meal instead of this as it’s not that filling. The service was pretty good tho and the atmosphere was nice and cozy.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOanBKptQ-R_H5eiyx4s67HHQU7ukggwSAkZ7tv&fid=0x0:0x4ab7ff7074636253"],"When":"2023-10-2"},{"Name":"cbl Google","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKseLK4QE-uFmbW8_hEmTOkS9RGzjwTJs3q9tyPwtQSc-dy=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Great Korean foods and such an awesome owner! Definitely a gem in the village area. Tried a few of their new inaris and was not disappointed. The spicy salmon and bulgigi are highly recommended!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMixXDyBd0gN0Cf58omWSw-4LIfMRQAXe33CFI&fid=0x0:0x4ab7ff7074636253"],"When":"2021-10-11"}]

user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Ben K","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIkChymkBEqoHC-DSLY-BlpEm3X8tgGaeAvEy7G17xjM-zfjw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Bottom line: it’s a great pizza for an affordable price (they often have promotions) on campus.

I got the “grab n go”: any small pizza and a pop for $10.99+tax. The Deluxe pizza was decent: crust was crispy, toppings filled the pizza, beautifully melted/charred in their XLT speed oven. And around the outer edge of the pizza is a heavy sprinkling of sesame seeds, which lends a texture like crunchy pizza dough. Kind of nice.

The online ordering platform tells you the order will take minimum 20 minutes, which was spot-on for my order. They also sell pizza by the slice for $2.38+tax in-store.

Best thing: they give you your takeout pizza in a cardboard box, so there’s no $0.25 bag fee!

The restaurant itself has probably 10 small tables—some inside, some outside—for eating there.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNDOuHiDIZTmdoXWax2rwLSqlNZvYhweoWLQ0nu&fid=0x0:0x860b3a2c6558c7be"],"When":"2024-8-2"},{"Name":"Iman Sh","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWY_It5dFbhJ3ahD3y8wnnvsyYECBdVwU0ipYiueTLf-0IgvGbE=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Uncle Fatih's Pizza is one of the best pizza experiences I've had in Vancouver. When comparing price and taste, it's honestly way better than other chain pizza places. We ordered a medium Meat Lovers and a medium Eggplant Artichoke, and enjoyed both of them. The chipotle dip was a nice addition, though it's not very spicy. The pizza itself is juicy and full of flavors.

If you were to compare it to an authentic Italian restaurant in Downtown, I can't say for sure how it would hold up—I haven't tried that yet. But this place serves great pizzas with good quality. As long as the quality stays consistent, it will always be one of my favorite pizza places.

[Update, July 1, 2024]
We ordered an extra-large half-and-half pizza. One half was Sweet & Spicy Lovers, and the other was Eggplant Artichoke. We enjoyed both. The Sweet & Spicy Lovers pizza has pineapple slices, so if you enjoy the sweetness of pineapple on your pizza, it could be really nice. The spiciness comes from banana peppers, which are quite intense—I’d rate the spicy level 9/10 and usually avoid the banana peppers with the last pieces. The meat on the pizza was very nice, though.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP3LNwcz4Mhb2_rAOeKq6HQ2yu9c_abTPsvF_gY&fid=0x0:0x860b3a2c6558c7be"],"When":"2024-6-27"},{"Name":"Bruno Rodrigues","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXhILuyIb0LIP6MudwbcSE2BAlE-f9U9SKRT2p9lsRwJ4hM0FgDLg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Awesome bang for the buck – 20th anniversary deal was any slice for $2.38 plus taxes. Slice was of a regular size and adequately filled. Ingredientes were good quality and the cheese was pretty tasty. Service was friendly, but I guess overwhelmed because there were only two people working at the whole restaurant. Maybe this setup will only last during the summer vacations, but there were some people waiting to make their order on the line even then.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNr_x3LSgypONBL59pcXxllJnkv_odePZ2Iyp46&fid=0x0:0x860b3a2c6558c7be"],"When":"2024-8-25"},{"Name":"Gurleen Mann","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLiPUG0uS2mNXBduiVsY6PVMjHnfxQ7NkDQyzxiXX7WnB_qcg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I’m really glad I stopped here with my family for lunch. The staff were helpful and answered all my questions. We ordered a small garlic chicken pizza, small spicy chicken pizza and veggie lovers (gluten free small pizza). The entire order was made quickly and tasted very good with fresh ingredients and a soft dough. They also had some dipping sauces on the side. Would have been awesome if they had small containers to place them in, but that wasn’t a deal breaker. All in all one of the best pizza places I’ve had in a very long time!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Jessy James","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUYtH31UTkbDUolpuvM8YhvZp6aRqCRrozjZhpKhJHwBksolrRrhQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Went in as they were closing (which nobody likes I know! 🙈) but we had no where else that was opened so we gave it a shot!

The last 8-10 slices all assorted and they charged full price for everything. Almost $36 after tip for end of the night pizza was a little crazy IMO. However they did their best to give us a deal anyways, so we left a tip as much as we could.

The pizza was tasty, I would personally recommend the ham and pineapple! The others were great too but not as traditional in taste as they were a little more complicated in ingredients. Not a bad thing, I just like my pizza simple 🥰

Otherwise felt the food was very tasty and would return if they had better prices, maybe some Italian style/thinner/cheaper made slices could help things as a recommendation? I love my Italian traditional pizza style myself, but I know this place is more westernized and that's also okay.

Otherwise a good experience, just think end of the night slices are typically sold at a reduced rate. They did give us 8 slices and the 9th free, but I feel it could have been half off. Maybe I'm picky, idk 😆.

Overall good stuff! 🍕 Thanks!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"YVR Duke","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVbrjJ5U6gKw7Gn1zE_GlxhUndims9WHlh7sVaHLXVrjOFlYd_B=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I missed the old Pi[e]r² Pizza.
This is the closest we can get on campus.  Freshslice is ok but it just lacks a character.

Recommended for pizza lovers.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOU3FmBdtQ7LMg_cBIVovU8hZILP6gYcvSoICF2&fid=0x0:0x860b3a2c6558c7be"],"When":"2024-7-3"},{"Name":"Zay R","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIrcv0nbceihjzzaPr2LIIin5v_Tj9YhzMv8cvDTNxNVU0GSA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"I always order from them via Ubereats. Sometimes they do have good offers ‘buy 1 get 1 free’ on selected pizzas which is definitely better and cheaper, their prices are a bit pricey without the offer.
As for their crusts, they were always well cooked, soft and very tasty. I like their thin crust more.
Their pizzas are freshly made. I tried couple of veggie pizzas, they were all delicious. However, their bbq sauce is not the best (barely taste it)
This time I got pesto chicken pizza and it was good.My favorite is Garlic Lover Pizza!
Also I appreciate the fact they offer Halal chicken :)
Overall very good Pizza place","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNR6RA-QEUZg9mR9rrhkIy-hHpvwt5R5I40hL40&fid=0x0:0x860b3a2c6558c7be"],"When":"2021-3-18"},{"Name":"Marcus Xiong","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWNKHkNu0r9L6u_s13vBOcHGIOl_tisn1xjH9tQbojiCd_NkDw-YQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"This is a quick place to grab a meal, and the food isn't low quality either. The pizza is freshly made and rebaked when someone orders them. The food is brought up quickly. I like the unique sesame seeds on the crust, and adds extra flavor to the pizza. Sauce is rich, and the cheese and toppings are a nice addition.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipONHV1r73zgfzQ_I6yWeRBU7_1WpRBMDqnxvZ2_&fid=0x0:0x860b3a2c6558c7be"],"When":"2023-11-13"}]

So many memories with my family! 🩷","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Steve Dahle","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJFPev8ihygs0WckPR92s1u0MzQFYPkaysEy8kNp2PbyRjPpA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We stayed at the Turner Cut RV Park in our Class A motorhome for 4 months. Dan, the owner, was always very accommodating and attentive to our needs. Samantha, his managing front  desk assistant, was always there for us and helping us in any way we needed with a very friendly attitude. All of the staff were attentive and helpful and kind and were constantly busy keeping up with the grounds and trying to update the facility. The location worked out well for us as a temporary home while we searched for our forever home. We are thankful that Dan made room for us.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"George Homan Jr.","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocK6kDcGsGqy_VIDn9SEGKaS-xFtfa9b0YmiPCmXM43sRU9Kpw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Dan, Sam, Al, Miguel, and the rest of the crew at Turner Cut were great. My wife and I spent 3 months there while on assignment for work. It had everything we needed, a place for our rig, extra parking for vehicles, and even places to play fetch with our dogs! The park is getting a face lift with privacy fences between sites as well as updated infrastructure (electric, water, and sewer). To my understanding, Dan took ownership fairly recently so I wouldn’t bother reading reviews from 3 years ago and beyond as they aren’t accurate. I would highly recommend this park to anyone in the area long term, short term, or extended stay.","Images":null,"When":""}]

user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Bruno Rodrigues","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXhILuyIb0LIP6MudwbcSE2BAlE-f9U9SKRT2p9lsRwJ4hM0FgDLg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Went there for the grad students meeting and absolutely loved it! The place was packed with vibrant people which gave such an energetic atmosphere. Staff was very friendly and contributed to the experience. The beers were great and the burger I had was good enough – not very large but also not expensive.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMDgBUdvc8jRuHppQfgKjuHI0zVR3S0Q2HrSskp&fid=0x0:0x7bf6312548e5f7ba"],"When":"2024-8-31"},{"Name":"Aileen Choi","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWtnbeuRSCrTtTivdNIO4OHLKHO_ilmZOOqqMZVCM5535PBeWYx=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We had our wedding at Koerner's Pub two weekends ago and we are beyond happy with the venue and how everything turned out! Caroline did such a great job with communication throughout the whole process and making whatever we wanted to do a reality. When we first booked, they said they're very flexible and can customize our wedding however we liked, and they really meant it! We added a signature cocktail a couple of months before the wedding and they made it happen with no hesitation. We are just blown away by how accommodating they are. We wanted a cozy, intimate, laid back wedding with the ceremony on the open patio and a cocktail style reception with canapes, platters and food stations and they more than delivered on that. The outdoor space is just beautiful surrounded by the tall trees, the atmosphere inside was absolutely perfect and the food was delicious! Our guests raved about everything! I could not recommend Koerner's Pub enough!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNSpoODXsooMuueBjFMVUbAncCRWmoP1B6ORPuo&fid=0x0:0x7bf6312548e5f7ba"],"When":"2023-11-7"},{"Name":"Jerry J","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX9DQ7B_TRq3u3bo5NkgYrIEp3oIpu1Uv2owPApsfpA107EzZBD=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"Don’t come here for the food. They “only do two things, tacos and burgers, but hey do those well” according to the staff on duty - LOL 🫠

The burger patty was as thin and crispy (smashed burger) as the one tiny stripe of bacon that you get for an additional $2.50 - for me, the smashed thing is mainly a cost saving measure. No lettuce or fresh tomato, just the mushy bun and greasy undercooked fries, all served on a plastic tray (no plate) to give it the perfect canteen finish.

The person at the counter did not want to be here (bad day for them it seems). Deco and atmosphere is ok, nice garden/patio. Beer and water good.

In summary, the place called Freshii at Wesbrook and this pub battle for the bottom of the list of eating out on campus.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMV5sDHilMGHK49b7Ep2ceOcuYUZ4P5cInKnkPf&fid=0x0:0x7bf6312548e5f7ba"],"When":"2024-6-13"},{"Name":"Nat D","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVq59Bz_Kc8jFzJNz9bEb180ByB9AU4nY2IRQXQnfI8npN0Tz_3=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Koerner’s pub is my go to for the BEST vegan tacos in the city! 🤤🌮 As a tasty side dish, be sure to order their yummy fries smothered in vegan mushroom gravy - truly heavenly! 😋 The prices and portions are very fair as well. The staff is always super warm and welcoming, and I greatly enjoy the pub ambience as well as the large patio surrounded by the lush greenery and mature trees. On a side note, be sure to check in advance to see if the pub is open as sometimes they host special events and will close for the day. This place is truly a hidden gem!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPV3UKCC0-8HY8nb3tMBs5r1g2Yp3mZ1z7ifA-D&fid=0x0:0x7bf6312548e5f7ba"],"When":"2022-8-2"},{"Name":"Jess A","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVQcaZCQGrB5OVS66pu43CkqxqUxwzuyGP2ki5075OI4cgNK_DdiA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We had our wedding ceremony and reception at Koerner's this past weekend. It was one of the best nights of our lives, in no small part to the staff at Keorner's. Ana, the venue coordinator, is on top of everything and was an invaluable resource. She responded quickly to all our communications, and went the extra mile to fulfill every request, including accomodating allergies and liasing with vendors to get the site setup just how we wanted.

The venue looked stunning - more beautiful that we could have imagined. It is an idyllic setting. It looking like our own little forest oasis! We had a night ceremony and it felt right out of a Midsummer Night's Dream.

The food was exceptional. I wish the chef had a restaurant we could eat at all the time! Our guests were comfortable and happy the whole night. The staff were attentive and fun. The beers they had on tap were awesome - even my favourite, Four Winds saison! We really can't say enough good things.

It was fun getting to know the venue - we visited a few times in the leadup, and hung out eating burgers and tacos. The vibe is great. We will be back as customers and look forward to attending one of their drag nights someday soon!

Big recommend and lots of love for this place!! <3","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMsoFuH2exuiAgDyAF2BAIjMYZg0qGUDYavAiXb&fid=0x0:0x7bf6312548e5f7ba"],"When":"2022-8-29"},{"Name":"Nanook Bearkiller","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJGd-lKZGiw3s1Cstm96X_oNJSIZl-bTkcRWm3S82g26MG6YQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Really poor service.
Went there at 12:30 pm. I had to wait for one full hour only to receive my burger. And then had to devour it without really tasting the damn food because my class was starting. This team is not good enough to be on campus. They're severely short staffed with inexperienced undergraduate students serving tables of 6 people. But with absolutely no competition around, they survive on monopoly.
I don't think I want to go there ever again. I try to change my friends' minds too if they suggest this place for any sort of gathering.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"jason wong","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLAr7OPM3u3i7bBkh0r7Q9kS7_8Gu_88Crv223BgydShD66TQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Very good taco’s but the the menu is very limited.. Very crowded on the weekends.. very hip hang out for the UBC students..","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMK9pm6ZuPgIIUqe-PBzrXbwWZ2KyumEdlGl06e&fid=0x0:0x7bf6312548e5f7ba"],"When":"2024-3-16"},{"Name":"Daniella Stewart","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJvrtZ9JggwDL2AwQ_WItI2VaTglWpBeElIlHroHM6ga-UoOQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"**Beautiful Wedding Venue***
We recently had our wedding at Koerner's Pub and we are so happy with that decision. The location is beautiful, Loafe catering was delicious, and Marcela and her team were great.
Having our wedding at Koerner's made for an easy day with no extra travel for ourselves or our guests between the ceremony and the reception. It felt intimate in the garden ceremony with a beautiful backdrop for photos. The tables already at Koerner's provided a simple and elegant feel that didn't require a ton of decorations which made for easy planning. Multiple guests came up to share how delicious the food was (we definitely recommend the flank steak with chimichurri).
Would highly recommend considering Koerner's for your wedding!","Images":null,"When":""}]

[{"Name":"Rowan Tetrault","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWfO97gMjqDhcxLto7LhpXIwpHTc_aV_Za2PD-ik6ShIa9lAwtk0A=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"This is one of the three conventional first year dining halls on UBC campus, and it is solidly alright.

They always offer a very wide selection of food at their various different stations including different types of pizza, burgers, pasta, and spins on traditional Mexican, homestyle, and Asian cuisine. They have all of this along with quite the yogurt/salad bar assortment + desserts and drinks.

Unlimited food with so many options is definitely a benefit, but some choices can be subpar at best and I noticed readily accessible protein options (primarily meat) are not always available.

My go to "clean" options (download nutrislice to be sure, but don't expect to see nutritional facts posted publicly ANYWHERE) that also taste pretty good include the sesame chicken salad with a hard boiled egg, any of their salmon meals, or a simple yogurt bowl.

It may be difficult to eat here everyday, but sometimes there are hidden gems and the staff never disappoint. This is why they deserve an absolute minimum of 4 stars :)","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOp1PYN4xQ9rgNxumgQsKC0nK56EXU44ehjOiVv&fid=0x0:0xec0f3de356e04cd1"],"When":"2024-9-28"},{"Name":"Robin Zhuo","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX4YJfTGesCXz1xbhn6UpYAqxjtSHa4hbLPPN34KDkRy9WuDw0=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Best 1st yr dorm dining hall for sure, but the quality are not stable :’( , staffs are absolutely helpful and amazing. If u r not in meal plan pay this dining hall for 12-20$ are insane.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOg61NRqlYqOY2-UH5B9vI8ZVC7VD4Ykn4YspXU&fid=0x0:0xec0f3de356e04cd1"],"When":"2024-11-12"},{"Name":"Alexander Hunt","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKntg94WsHup3cVgJBk3yO0jaRf4K-ndL2T0xGy94s_gBQtie8=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"The Feast is Totem Park Residence's dinning hall. With 4-5 separate kitchens serving unique styles of food, students and guests eating here will enjoy the food.

The atmosphere here is wonderful. There are celling-to-floor windows, allowing much natural sunlight into the dinning hall. The seating can sit 200-250 people. Sitting varies from cafe tables, to Howarts style long tables or high-chair tables found in coffee shops. The food-serving area of the dinning hall is immediately at the place where you pay so you can line up to get your food. To avoid the line at the main entrance of the dinning hall, you can go to the back to pay as well.

The food here is okay. This is not a high-end restaurant. The food may not be for everyone. Also, there's a self serve ice cream machine, yogurt and salad bar. There are coffee machines and juice dispensers. There are plently of fruits, snacks and bread. At night, the pizza kitchen opens. Food is served in small to medium portion which is perfect for those who do not eat as much or want to try multple things. Chefs are polite and kind and will be willing to give you a bit of extra food if you ask.

There is no washroom in the dinning hall. You will have to leave the dinning hall and lose your ability to come back to use the washroom.

If you come here during regular meal times, expect there to be lots of students. If you come during 8:30am, 9:30 am or any time when class is in session, there are not as many people. Menu of the dinning hall can be found at both front and rear entrance. Menu can be found online as well through Nutrislice app.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPWzm1_3n7h1l2H9rwoh2H89TZ0Fq1NXU3odOco&fid=0x0:0xec0f3de356e04cd1"],"When":"2023-9-15"},{"Name":"Jarod Walsh","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVvAxeA4y5ekP9kJ4EmyOw8TsE05_KmQ9ASGN1BZSNnDc39dHRw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"This buffet-style restaurant is amazing. You pay $16 and can enjoy unlimited servings of various foods, drinks, and desserts. While the food itself is just okay, it’s truly incredible considering the price.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM4uPJeAZ6lVIORSxF5yULsp8ZpenwbVQF3Fcqh&fid=0x0:0xec0f3de356e04cd1"],"When":"2023-12-7"},{"Name":"Brendan Mitchell","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV3Qlg33iKZu8wkzLBmt9R9RBp_9-J_M_xbmFoyCBbc0eyazMCC=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This place is awesome!  Very reasonable price and if you like to eat alot the variety is awesome.   I can't believe a place like this exists for the price.   It is not fine dining but it is deffinatly a few steps above what you would expect for eating lunch anywhere at a university campus.  Came here with my 9 year old daughter who is a healthy eater and we both had 3 breakfasts.  She loved being able to get up and go get whatever she wanted.   Good selection of different drinks avalible Aswell.   Highly recommend. For the price, nothing beats it!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMN7yTSIDM_65m4bBL6QwgHr2tRxv3ruxm0pDbJ&fid=0x0:0xec0f3de356e04cd1"],"When":"2024-2-3"},{"Name":"Munchica","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXbQ6ACs51IPQJlRLrmnunOErED8bimOf5-y1uov4EWpuZvjQQjrA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba8-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"This place is quite amazing and the food is very healthy, you can taste the health! For only a flat rate of $15.00 for lunch, it's an all you can eat buffet which includes roasted veggies, curry, rice, Bahn Mi, tacos, fries, burgers, smoothies, juices, milk, soft drinks, coffee, tea, salads, fruits, and desserts, including frozen yogurt! Where else are you gonna find a lunch buffet for $15.00 these days and such quality healthy ingredients!!! Highly recommend it! The only reason it lost a star is that the taste of the food is just average but for the price, it's awesome.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMefaQLhCYBXkPvbE6zYnfa2QtOKPoJTciFo0p1&fid=0x0:0xec0f3de356e04cd1"],"When":"2022-10-5"},{"Name":"Ahnaf Muqset Haque","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU9JdQZtXBMvD618JDWqRmaMkXk-I2NhqdPuW2NLQFP33Qn87KikQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Feast is one of the first year resident dining places at the University of British Columbia. They have a bunch of variety of cuisines and have all sorts of options(vegan, vegetarian, halal, etc.) to meet your needs. The food is not so great in terms of taste and is quite expensive. Ambience is great though!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNYAuVTb8ktuztAQgPbE2inlqJ4Yo-UDnubXkp8&fid=0x0:0xec0f3de356e04cd1"],"When":"2019-3-28"},{"Name":"Ethem Can","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXGyCt7ndLGEeKEaL2-gks_s7s8Q37Wov3ouVX3P4o--96Axg9t=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Foods are delicious and perfectly designed. Only downside is there is always crowded and you need to wait some time to get your food.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMYUnLzVImnmGR01tQ3elsZg4CjFNKf14pGd5Sm&fid=0x0:0xec0f3de356e04cd1"],"When":"2023-9-5"}]

[{"Name":"Parneet Kahlon","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXqz_l5BzN5_mBY3QC7SEZWEVervEPkE_VocF-ECzkBQsGcdPO6=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I was craving indo- Chinese food a lot and wanted to try a new restaurant. Came across this restaurant and it had good reviews, so decided to give it a try, must say they did not disappoint.

We ordered
1. lemon chicken- so far the best lemon chicken ever tasted, lemon sauce tasted fresh and flavourful, even chicken was crisp and juicy and no smell at all.
2. Chicken Hakka noodles- so good exactly what I was craving for. Lot of veggies and chicken and plus portion size is so good.
3. Paneer Manchurian- wasn’t expecting what we got, but it was much more.. paneer, veggies, sauce everything was amazing.

Definitely worth a try. Will be going back to try few more things.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNy-9bEGUIa9RuGiQfhCF1ksFMamO1YS5qoiEDc&fid=0x0:0xadd6447877bd9fc"],"When":"2024-5-5"},{"Name":"Asif Asad Jan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU-H8QYQjNPnQpvnOIo3aT330ZoDHwOQdzvDzJ5RZh4Z_6p8x_B=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"After hearing a lot of good reviews, we decided to visit the a/m restaurant last week.
It was a nice small restaurant with only take-out option. Few seats, where you can wait while restaurant prepares your order.
The owners are super nice people. Very friendly and helpful.

As for the food, portions were huge. We had them the same evening and also the next day, yet we still had some left-over.

Everything was tasty. Friend Shrimp Wontons were nice and crispy with good amount of filling. Tasted great with its sauce.
House Special Chicken was very good, had a lovely kick of spices. I totally enjoyed it.
Chicken Chow Mein was the best. Great flavour of chicken and veggies with yummy noodles.

Chicken Cream Corn Soup tasted really good. It had cubes of chicken which was kind of strange for me as I'm accustomed to shredded chicken. I would prefer shredded anyways (my preference).

Overall, we had great dinner for two days.
I highly recommend this restaurant 👌","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOkXRLwtAOvZ5Qs5oqrE8OjPG7LCulJVZuUebUL&fid=0x0:0xadd6447877bd9fc"],"When":"2023-11-2"},{"Name":"Zeeshan Sohail","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXQzSgXcEIo5d0fY039IL3LLi7k1i-9eyjB9u0xnur9BQekUdtD=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This place is only take-away but the taste is so on point it's a must have in the BC food scene. Crispy Chilli Beef, Chowmein, Egg Fried Rice, Sweet and Sour Chicken and Honey Garlic Wings are to die for.  Absolutely fantastic Chinese food every single time.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNNYyvpCBI8bUAXCvVXfONkjl8Qb7osluGxWhWP&fid=0x0:0xadd6447877bd9fc"],"When":"2023-12-30"},{"Name":"Jerry Z","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocK7RBlhmiqlmWEVXQb9JHQrpND43nYDVl3HJ7FJRNUCikja0DiP=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Pictures don’t do it justice!

Curry eggplants has a very unique taste and so perfectly executed. The fusion between Chinese and Indian is surprisingly delivered through the Chinese cooking style, with Indian flavour, and more nuances in between.

Tofu with vegetables and Crispy beef (sweet and sour) are both crunchy and saucy, great white rice pairing dishes.

All the dish you can customize the spicy level.

The owner is very friendly and attentive, shared some great stories about their unique journey from India to Vancouver to North Delta.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN_-_wWJJZ5b-uICWkUrJHRyCcWyBIuGZL9VIbm&fid=0x0:0xadd6447877bd9fc"],"When":"2023-1-30"},{"Name":"Amrita Nayak","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXJgJ3b8LMBlPc7G1Rv8sy6cyH33IeJwYGYkw6c-i8ocBKF5odAKg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We order regularly from this place and they never disappoint. Food is delicious, portions are huge, they do not skimp on the meat and the service is excellent. They go out of their way to make the items to your liking, exactly how you want it.
What makes the food even better is the people who run this. They are super nice and always greet you with a big warm smile.
Some of our favorites - Manchurian fried rice, ginger garlic chicken, masala (curry powder) fried rice, black bean chicken.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMTte94SYdZUDHEgZM2OsuRdRIA5Xqz4E8py662&fid=0x0:0xadd6447877bd9fc"],"When":"2022-11-2"},{"Name":"Syed M Kazmi","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWFPoFab8kRIuO97MoMRl6sTxjS02YjKCGuudVSUEA8Tr-nlg2z=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Ordered for take out from Manchu Masala. Their sweet and sour chicken is staple for us to order as it's balance of flavour and sweetness is just to my liking. I thoroughly approve their use of pineapples for this dish.

Their egg fried rice was good and the vegetables chow mein was excellent.

Tried their garlic chicken for the first time and that was a hit. It had the sweetness like their sweet and sour, but more of a garlic flavor twist. It was delicious and something we will order again.

Excellent portion sizes with reasonable prices and really good taste.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNWweI4UXOHcqAC8elcTRBs-P_UgrfCc0GJCQ4c&fid=0x0:0xadd6447877bd9fc"],"When":"2022-4-28"},{"Name":"Emily L","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVwMr5VlKt9ECBUDKUi62kHV2PESObS8EDu0Fr68tChck1Pc-Li=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Been here since they opened in 2020. It's always my go-to for affordable and yummy and quick food. Could not go wrong. Love the staff, mama and paps kind of atmosphere and they are so sweet and kind.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Jay Morgen","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU8eQhyjxINm15a8wZ5LZ0QB76sRSJyG8yl9te5yRgVrwsJj8MA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Amazing hakka food. My first time trying tonight and was very impressed
Wonderful flavour, great portions and quality. The meat was cooked to perfection and spices well balanced. Also really really nice people who run the place. They do deliver but are not on skip or ubereats and do the delivery themselves which I really respect. I will absolutely be going back next time I want chinese food and highly recommend","Images":null,"When":""}]

[{"Name":"DLH","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKNxoVJChN19TlxEyh2PqXcySZWcsWGp-pw0aGewSStRgeU=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Updated again May 2023:
Kids treated us to a Mother’s Day lunch and food, portions and service were very good. We ordered vegan as well as non-vegan entrees (see pics).
Only observation to note is that peanut sauce for the salad rolls wasn’t very peanuty flavoured.
Based on today’s meal, I am bumping my rating up to 4.5.

Update Jan 2023 **bumping rating from 1 star to 3.5: Gave this long time ND local Vietnamese Restaurant another go after an ownership change last year.

One of the owners was behind the counter tonight, very friendly and his partner Leslie, in the kitchen owns a Vanc. restaurant.

Our server was pleasant, albeit some confusion with our order, also due to our unfamiliarity with the menu.

We ordered the House Special Phò (L) $16.99, Deep fried Spring Rolls (2 to an order, $2.50 ea), Assorted Seafood Wonton and BBQ Pork with Noodles (S) $16.99, Deep Fried Rice Paper Spring Roll $4.50 and a Lemongrass Bahn Mi $8.75 to-go.

The soups were hot (as they should be), the DF Rice Paper Roll was greasy tasting and I didn’t care for it but everything else was good.

Make sure you ask for the chili oil, it’s bomb and a tasty condiment with soup and noodles.

My previous bad experiences were with dayshift employees so I hope the new management has corrected that.

Update Jan 2022: Went with friends for lunch to see if the poor service from hired staff had changed at all. Unfortunately it had not, food is plunked on the corner of the table without any acknowledgement. Nobody came back to check on tea/water refills. Requested the bill and same. Food was ok but the service leaves a bad taste in the mouth and doesn’t warrant a return IMO. Doesn’t seem to affect the local customer loyalty though as it’s been this way for years.
Demoting to 1 star.

Got take out beef noodle bowl (Phō)- large #6 well done brisket and skirt flank-$10.99. Soup was very hot but not as flavourful as Phō99 which is our go-to, but closed. Comes with generous portion of beef and the usual sprouts, cilanto, lime, basil, jalapeño and hoisin sauce.
Hadn’t been for couple years, while the owners are very nice, friendly people, the servers have not always been very attentive (to the point of being rude) in the past.
The food has always been quite good though.
Located in a strip mall with a variety of businesses and ample parking.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOnZ3Ufs7YsPQXmcMlvLnP0b-99yAaE24QWZ-s&fid=0x0:0x80f8ec4ed8554885"],"When":"2022-2-22"},{"Name":"Ronald Retandy","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKiVTWQFKjqXe4UnsBFRIZ7GxF9tGrva9JzQ7uYayyA9RXk6w=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Been going here for more than 20 years, I heard it was operating under a new owner last year. We've been going here a couple of times, food is still good. Deep fried wonton is still my favorite, pho is still decent.

Price has gone up by double though, and I'm not too sure how to feel about it.

Decent food and good service, might be the last time we come here.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNbTw75FjErm7R-a_7nB94qQmPqncf4mhCCSU68&fid=0x0:0x80f8ec4ed8554885"],"When":"2021-2-7"},{"Name":"Taz C","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJ235c-1POJF85QGI4N_CFSzUmrADwRBXdKObCvBIDceTrCYTc=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Awesome food, big portions. We frequent this place despite poor customer service because of the food.
Their pho is by far the best I've had in the lower mainland. Perfect balance ir flavours and aroma and generous portions. Customer service is pretty average, kinda makes you feel like you are in Asia.  The staff are neither polite nor friendly or will crack a smile but they are fast and efficient.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN1sKj7fxG0xMXQ80l3cn7x3skRhMX4Ay4ujxG3&fid=0x0:0x80f8ec4ed8554885"],"When":"2020-1-19"},{"Name":"Dallas Singh","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWMYF_2uOmj792l9EGoe7IgcbejSm4xJDnldT3f_eKAsHBaj3Y=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Best pho in North Delta! Tucked away in the corner of the shopping complex so it can be hard to miss. But once you have had one of these amazing dishes, trust me, you'll never go anywhere else! Food comes quickly and it never dissapoints! Good sized portions for your money too! Whether it's pho, chow mein, or a simple vermicelli bowl, it's all delicious!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMM6lbG1VWiUeM-AtejYlMcL1VV267CqEa6Qv8u&fid=0x0:0x80f8ec4ed8554885"],"When":"2021-6-20"},{"Name":"James H Terre","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXQe3cD2OAW2WicJ2iFvBRW7BSYgRuA0F0JJhj-r3nWIlovZFE=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"rare steak, beef brisket, tendon, tripe beef noodle soup (15.99) / rare steak, tripe, beef brisket, tendon satay noodle soup (16.99) / butter deep fried chicken wings (14.5)","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMPrgTxQwve5BJkGgsXYWShL48X-r9EyGaQnOBi&fid=0x0:0x80f8ec4ed8554885"],"When":"2023-8-10"},{"Name":"stephen wilde","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWrvNleje5tgYYW4_yJssFvWvErjTDdku1cFBuV2wYdlHLfuh1S=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"sadly we had to wait for a very looooong time for our food. there were only a few other diners in the restaurant and only one server who looked a bit frantic. when the meals did arrive - they were dropped at the end of the table for us to figure who’s was who’s. i did see a number of to-go orders leave and can only speculate they were filling delivery orders and not attending to their in real life customers!!!! i ordered the chicken sub. it was the last to come and not until we reminded the server we were missing 3 of our meals. i took mine to go. now i bite into an extremely disappointing cold cut sub with dry bread. sad.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMDBiV8IWiYrc1EjFrzMuzhl6wYKCpYphTl0Q76&fid=0x0:0x80f8ec4ed8554885"],"When":"2023-1-22"},{"Name":"T Radons","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLSlrOzuvgcVDj3aymAbLi78FkANCC9Xc5TtjYnP6GCW8zNqw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Front staff were absolutely awful to deal with, refused to provide any information on allergens in the dishes, infact at one point said they and the kitchen staff had no idea what ingredients were in the food. Asked for a manager or owner, she refused to provide a contact number and instead suggested I eat somewhere else and call back at a later time to see if the manager was in then.  Would NEVER trust this restaurant to eat at or spend a dollar of my money.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Brandy-Lynn Davidson","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVlrDRKj5gXrEMDMqfm1JmhzCsZkr9P0sp4JvsPu1nMwv-_YZUe=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I am very loyal to my usual spot but after seeing the reviews we decided to give it a try. I had the small #12 with the rare beef on the side. I am happy to announce that I was not disappointed!! Priced as usually for this type of dish. This is a great place and the lady who served us was quick but friendly. My only critique would be for them to offer water when you get there as we were only provided with the tea. Tea is nice but I enjoy ice water when I have spicy phò. We will definitely be back as it's so close to our home 😊🍲👌🏼
Cheers to a great phò!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNaPniHMd8GtuQXgcJ4YEPnGbg6_RAH5n_CVBfU&fid=0x0:0x80f8ec4ed8554885"],"When":"2018-11-14"}]
