user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Phoebe Nguyen","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVG0xd2xYnqZIp_umMyZOBb0ks9m0ApyoWjwxAds2lAqLSGAshC=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I visited this Indian buffet restaurant during the year-end holiday season, and it was a delightful experience. The festive Christmas decorations added a warm and cheerful atmosphere, making it perfect for holiday celebrations.

The food was excellent, with an impressive variety of curries—chicken, beef, lamb, and more—all bursting with authentic flavors. The dessert section featured many traditional Indian sweets, which were a bit too sweet for my taste, but I appreciated the option to enjoy ice cream and cake as well.

The ambiance makes it ideal for family gatherings or company parties. They even have private rooms that can accommodate groups of 20-30 people, providing a more intimate and enjoyable experience.

Overall, this restaurant is a fantastic choice for both food and atmosphere, especially during the holiday season. Highly recommended!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOPA66OJAdy5G8gMZbJlNfkaNA8QZzIgmLCkvE9&fid=0x0:0x591cca86b95caa3e"],"When":"2024-12-23"},{"Name":"Praneet Raj","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU-I5iB9QpG5eztISNYObvNJI9swIkyqnUB25NJVMbN3zDz8_-1=s120-c-rp-mo-ba7-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I absolutely loved this amazing Indian buffet restaurant. With over 150 items to choose from, the variety was incredible, and every dish I tried was of top-notch quality. The food was flavorful and authentic, offering a fantastic range of both vegetarian and non-vegetarian options. The cocktails were another highlight—unique and expertly crafted, adding an extra touch to the dining experience. The service was extraordinary, with attentive staff ensuring everything went smoothly. It was a delightful experience from start to finish. I highly recommend this place, and I will definitely be back for another round of great food and drinks.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMkq3HOa0ZwVl0aaeiobaXWtH0z_3agV9w4tZL0&fid=0x0:0x591cca86b95caa3e"],"When":"2024-10-10"},{"Name":"Emma Tolly","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUHRCBdZMx6SLHNyCO59Sh5fGUMwyy5tM8toUXrcDcdcp4sIyRj=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We came during December and they are also open during Christmas. The service was fantastic (better than most places), food tasted amazing (there were no bad dishes and a good variety to choose from), and the price is reasonable for buffet (approx 45 per person without drinks).

The interior design and atmosphere of the restaurant is lively and cozy. Would definitely come back again and recommend to friends and family.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP2jpFo-WHtW98eQZXCbiXTdyIzvcHDlsXdbeR1&fid=0x0:0x591cca86b95caa3e"],"When":"2024-12-23"},{"Name":"John Dreyer","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXJORpLiVTZLOTQ4ZSaEs8r3tBWR0ha3zIf2xPszyRTLu_SWs7Y2g=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This is my favourite Indian Buffet. High quality, good service and tremendous food. Everyone in our party could choose the food that suited them. Some liked vegetarian dishes, I am keen on tandoori meats, the kids chose a plateful of cakes to start with. Nice ( but expensive) cocktails. Plenty of free parking. Not too busy in the week, busy at weekends.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO2jl9tjwuH7m-OXrEmzpvAaIJGR6bBZu0TvEDE&fid=0x0:0x591cca86b95caa3e"],"When":"2024-11-24"},{"Name":"Ada","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocK_tT85lO7aZKFfq17wWpo8ldgI_n0GJFJfBhG1nWiEa2zXCQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"From my limited experience of the Indian cuisine, the taste seemed authentic. My favorite was the butter chicken, which got a little spicy near the end. The seating area was spacious. Lots of parking available outside in the plaza. The place was decorated nicely.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPNk8NSoaNv7MBZGAa4JRkh-cXmqdOTnmJhAn04&fid=0x0:0x591cca86b95caa3e"],"When":"2024-11-13"},{"Name":"Rajesh R","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUAtkYip3pIVP-ZJS7hPA_V6eSNoACvvmp34LIZmlC_HP9d_CM2=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Wow! What an amazing experience! Living in a remote area of Washington State, we were excited to visit Canada for the first time and dine at this restaurant. With modest expectations, despite hearing great reviews, we were blown away! The food, service, and atmosphere exceeded our expectations. We'll definitely return in a couple of days. Cheers!"","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNqBepo6FHti2n4_rVtKNu7g2LrWfbiNcGZL4ls&fid=0x0:0x591cca86b95caa3e"],"When":"2024-12-23"},{"Name":"David CM Chung","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUu9wKhvbfbXcUv3ddzu6Zbl9103spVjAaDikUakjLqFoCJejT0Fw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Not bad for a buffet place.  Price is alright.  Ample parking as it's at a Mall.  Not too busy.  But service was a bit slow....had to wait almost 30mins for simple Mojito drinks for my
table.  And also gave me the wrong bill for the drinks and i didn't even realized it till after we left the restaurant.  We were at company lunch function there whereby we pay for our own drinks.  Food is good though.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMlxoA71TKWOV2YuSu32by5V0MslYtBJUEsFJ2R&fid=0x0:0x591cca86b95caa3e"],"When":"2024-10-30"},{"Name":"Yix Huang","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX-J7BhURjrSxg0zehj9vV5_srUXqps-aWwLMecYw1PxcaNrD_qVw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Great value of a fantastic Indian buffet! So many curry options, with delicious chicken and fish choices. Vegetarian friendly.
Snacks are sweet and fresh, although it is way too sweet for me...
Drinks sold separately, but still with a a good price. A huge bottle of Evian is on the table, but keep in mind if you need normal ice water, it is available upon request.

Located in a mall, free parking available, both in front of the place, and the back.

Friendly feeling from the beginning of the dinner, treated well with the staff here.

Gonna come back soon!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM0X2XrqNDnkFOxVXiR7w5z3N1-2VTTY-KzRRx2&fid=0x0:0x591cca86b95caa3e"],"When":"2024-8-18"}]

[{"Name":"Traditionally Modern Food","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWMpQ_rffdB1oRpx4JBtbwY9ZnneLVTrtetaX6pnc7nm39hssP8=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This is one of the best South Indian restaurants in Delta, BC. I'm not sure why this place has so many negative reviews. We just had dinner there, and our server Shruti was extremely polite. The food came quickly, and everything tasted good. We are definitely coming back for this food","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM20zZFsAUvI1fOLiRl1xi1qFWk6sG-LhscqBPQ&fid=0x0:0xa4c824edd008d273"],"When":"2024-7-1"},{"Name":"Apurva Shelhalkar","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWhHoVKXEOi9H6a9TLWDbt3vYQbM1IQy-PEvGXNrQa1vEMaKeKZNw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I am maharashtrian but I like South Indian food hence my friends introduced this restaurant to me. Food is really yummmm authentic taste.... Payasam is my all time favorite South Indian desert it was perfect...all chutneys and sambhar authentic... And the bestest thing was the coffee and the service....thank you Salman and Navroop for friendly, kind service I really appreciate it","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPdB7ZBQRLofl3tZLMJoIQL3mmWsovMeueytNHR&fid=0x0:0xa4c824edd008d273"],"When":"2024-11-25"},{"Name":"Zollstock Mueller","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKBw0Z4GAdwRUgaxWB9Zu8Za1vWYf1-lUYtwt_2pYVjzMeraQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Dosas were super tasty! Salman was a super nice server as well :) will be back! They even had a buy one get one free dosa (Thursdays)","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMLF4dbQM3GGPvm63IvKTowA76E_spLOxEvKMVO&fid=0x0:0xa4c824edd008d273"],"When":"2024-12-20"},{"Name":"Ram Umasankaran","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKftpdQ02WG9ZhMAlO0WB7DyxRXKLOpEhwdKywabYT3UrIZ2w=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The buffet was outstanding. Especially the gulabjamun. Felt like my Patti's style. Perfect taste. The Broccoli Kuttu was outstanding. We loved the food and pass our regards to the chef.Thanks to support staff especially Ashwin and Neha.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP3Q7-8WA1MFnbF13qe9oJZsEOQN9tMxGDE9oKH&fid=0x0:0xa4c824edd008d273"],"When":"2024-10-6"},{"Name":"Ashley","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXVS35_N_eP6M2t_lCqCwBnzwAbbUNDMpkhHxKNDdR7yLzAbQpe=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"My family and I were craving dosas, and I've heard many good things about this place. So we made our way here, and we left satisfied.
I got the masala dosa, and it was delicious!! It was the first time I enjoyed having a dosa from a restaurant. All the chutney and sambar were great. I would definitely come back here again.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOBLsPRXFBV9VlJCJerSkRWYnGcSGAW3kjL6h3Z&fid=0x0:0xa4c824edd008d273"],"When":"2024-7-12"},{"Name":"Snigdha Sadanandan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIhvf4BlpGhcWOCjLLD3zSdAipdqUHf8J88XN4wyEb-g1lsKr3J=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We had a decent overall experience with ghee/paper masala, and kids' meals. The staff checked on us throughout the meal. The ambiance is quite good. There is quite a good choice of vegetarian items. They have tried to make it a South Indian-inspired dining experience, but the authenticity fell short. Prices seem reasonable and decent. Overall, the place is good to visit once in a while. I hope to visit again","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMzGthBCN9GQK46eyadg6IOO4K0nwFwKfSDIXgH&fid=0x0:0xa4c824edd008d273"],"When":"2024-3-1"},{"Name":"DEE","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUE68QQugYwIrGbHoSG7JAoZIp7yHKFKTnMFleiKIHnRsp_FxG0=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Exceptionally well service by the team.
Not taking names cuz everyone was great n did a fantastic job
(All the ladies and my dudes)

In fact, One of the best service I've experienced here in Canada so far.
Be proud of yourselves
💯🔥👍

The food and drinks were amazing too
I think I found a new favourite spot. 🙂✌️

BUT. what's with the MANDATORY  GRATUITY??
Common guys

Change your policy
Not cool
Gratuity (tip) should be a customer's choice

I personally would have tipped more than the 11$

Definitely coming back for more
💯👻

Mybad, didn't click pics of the food.
Will do it next time 😜🙃

P.S. the sambar was too good 👍","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPH9Nren6m3cSFTOw-8j774XfBjSUdUGCqkpIhY&fid=0x0:0xa4c824edd008d273"],"When":"2024-11-10"},{"Name":"Jayanand KV","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJ300Yeb4iZG-kKuVhK9gX6deBVBJYl5e792S9p7AKCEsTgpA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I have been to Saravana Bhavan at this location numerous times, however posting a review for the first time.  There were 5 of us, 3 adults and 2 kids. Went for dinner Saturday night at 8.30. Place was not too crowded; we were seated immediately. Medhu vada and podi idli were fresh and tasty appetizers as always. Mixed veg parotta, pav bhaji, and tomato onion chilli uthappam are reliable dishes for adults and have been consistently good. Kids got chocolate dosas, essentially ghee dosa with Nutella spread inside. This does not come with sambar and chutney on the side for some strange reason, previously it used to. Kids didn’t seem to be bothered.  Kids had Shirley temple, adults had mango lassi and filter coffee, both were good. Food is not very expensive in relative terms. $116 with taxes and gratuity, the latter is included in the bill. Shruti was warm, friendly and quick to serve.  Overall good experience. Certainly recommend if you like South Indian veg cuisine.  For those with big appetite I have heard their buffet is good, though we have not tried it much.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMHCx-pfZor4XPF7B6JEpC4wzRVOgFjP00BhNHM&fid=0x0:0xa4c824edd008d273"],"When":"2024-4-29"}]

[{"Name":"Shaifali Mittal","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUxOs2Oo1ooPVg1oGTC-uLTS9zXgxYb87JCjG1hUWsE9AQfGKcn6w=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Poor Packaging and Declining Quality at The Yellow Chilli

I recently ordered from Yellow Chilli, and unfortunately, my experience was far from satisfactory. The packaging was inadequate—there was minimal effort to secure the food, and it arrived in a messy state, with items spilled and containers damaged. For a restaurant of this caliber, I expected much better care in how the food is packaged and delivered.

To make matters worse, the quality of the food itself seems to have declined. The flavors weren't as vibrant or fresh as I remember, and the texture was off, indicating the ingredients weren’t as fresh as they should have been.

For a restaurant with a reputation for excellence, both the packaging and food quality were major letdowns. I hope The Yellow Chilli takes this feedback seriously and works to restore the standards they once set. Until then, I’ll be reconsidering future orders.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNgcWAhOSkBQZk1jNzSoTlAVc1IS0Mj81PMCogh&fid=0x0:0x59e2c461f803f0ec"],"When":"2024-11-14"},{"Name":"Aswathy Suresh","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVKR4DNly6qkrVukYEpwNeGLo6K3j-A3IXF_3S8Thv5C4UG9m5MDg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The best authentic Indian restaurant that captures the amazing flavours from across India. Regretting that we missed this restaurant before and that we never got to try Sanjeev Kapoor’s authentic recipe before. Every dish takes you back home and the flavours are so perfectly crafted. Would definitely want to go back and try every other dish.
The servers were very great and friendly as well 😊 perfect for a celebration as well.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipONTQSbFzB75IfC5rDFC5XbY13eHjc5Q1YD0Juz&fid=0x0:0x59e2c461f803f0ec"],"When":"2024-10-14"},{"Name":"discovery sonu ali","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU_b2reRKsjtiT_HffF8-yN5QM1sqqpXd5OaoIUa8-ff3hRWT7Gdw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The restaurant had an exceptional atmosphere, with a warm and inviting ambiance. The staff were incredibly polite, enhancing the overall dining experience. The food was truly remarkable, offering authentic Indian flavors that were both rich and satisfying. It's definitely a place worth visiting, and I highly recommend trying it at least once.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP2L9y5fGKX8ekh7Gjvk4NjDenh5dABvBe2tdJV&fid=0x0:0x59e2c461f803f0ec"],"When":"2024-8-15"},{"Name":"Kevin (KC)","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVrZpzDcm4xbgvb_oOynyP_bQvwIe7l-wMoPIs8L4UeVZ-waBkO=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"My first time eating at a slightly more upscale Indian restaurant...and it was amazing! 🔥

Came here for some late dinner with my Indian buddy and it wasn't too busy so we were seated right away. Originally we were seated at a table for two that was quite dark because of the lack of lighting in the area, so I had requested to our server if we could move to a brighter table behind us which she granted. The main reason for this is because I am not of a fan of eating in the dark, and as a food critic/reviewer, I like to see what I am eating clearly so I can provide better feedback.

We ordered the following for two people:
* Tikka 3 Ways
* Bhatti ki Macchi
* Garlic Naan
* Missi Rotti
* Puran Singh Da Tariwala Murgh
* Dum murgh biryani
* Falooda Kulfi

I ordered the tikka 3 ways for my appetizer and it was really good! I love that it was done 3 ways so I can taste which one I like the most...the spicy one was my favorite. The cook on the chicken was perfect and not dry.

For our mains we got the chef's special Puran Singh Da Tariwala Murgh and Chicken Biryani. For my bread I ordered the garlic naan and my Indian buddy ordered the missi rotti. Everything tasted delicious! The gravy was rich, savory, with a bit of spice and the chicken biryani was piping hot and cooked perfectly! 👌

The garlic naan was soft, flaky and fresh! The texture was really good and perfect for dipping into the curry. The only con my Indian buddy said was the missi rotti was slightly overcooked.

Overall though the appetizers and mains were delicious.

For dessert I ordered the Falooda Kulfi and all I have to say is...WOW! The ice cream dessert was bursting with Indian flavours...I felt like I teleported to India when I ate a spoon full of this delicious creamy dessert. This was definitely the star of the meal tonight! I am not a huge dessert guy - but this one I truly enjoyed...I also like that it wasn't overly sweet. 🍨🍧

The service here was excellent. Our server refilled our waters regularly and even educated me with some of the food I was ordering and eating. She also made sure we were getting new plates, silverware and napkins for each course. 👍

Interior and seating was also good. The table is a nice height and the chairs are padded. The only con is that some of the tables here are placed in darker areas of the restaurant...I guess it's fine if you prefer candle light dinners, but in my opinion there should be a bit more lighting that stretches across the wall where the tables are since they are further away from the glass windows and get blocked out by the higher booth seating which makes those areas feel less important.

Overall though, I enjoyed eating here and plan to eat here again to try their other menu items. I am a big fan of Indian food since I grew up in Surrey, so it's nice to be able to treat myself with some indian fine dining once in a while. 🙂","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMH7Apd1e8CNCeuPqPQ0X62CSoitNmB2nZ6-8Eu&fid=0x0:0x59e2c461f803f0ec"],"When":"2024-9-1"},{"Name":"Gunjan N","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKnGgkA1elJAwarcjcQNB0nZVdXLX3uwLu0NnIClSVktMj-5Q=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Being an avid follower of Chef Sanjeev Kapoor, this place did not live up to its chef's mark. Service was good, ambiance was good but there was no oomph to the food when it came to taste or presentation. Nothing was appealing enough to make me wanna go back. It may be because we had high expectations, and others may love it if they don't know the Chef.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPEbZDDye6aiT3Vkwc4P6gOmBc0nD3vaEXD4aNw&fid=0x0:0x59e2c461f803f0ec"],"When":"2024-6-23"},{"Name":"Nikki Paash","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUS1GPSPm9ymA5-pGC3kbNDX0EgXOG9Tr3DvBXx813m9sPBSfpY=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"I must say, it was a disappointment  at the start, found hair on the cultery and asked to change  that. The first dish  tandoori  lamb had hair in it ( look in picture  below).   The manager  Amrut, was  very apologetic  and saw personally  to all the main courses , making sure we do not find any more hair.  The dessert was on the house and repeat order of the tandoori lamb at no charge to take  home as a sorry.  Taste wise, the batter  used for prawns was too salty. Other dishes were very tasty. It was a let down  for me as I was expecting  better than what  I got at Sanjeev Kapoor  restaurant.   The ambiance  was dull, the place was empty, and the food presentation  was very mediocre. Not the Sanjeev Kapoor  flair that I expected. Check out  my review of Clove-the art of dining, look at their food presentation  to compare.Furthermore, it was a birthday  lunch which was spoilt by the unhygienic  situation as  well.However, the  manager  and the server both were  doing great jobs. The chef.. well... Let's just  say I won't be returning...","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOd5cPs-Xw9hQTyMz5fdM3DMrW4OvV3AQvYSN4M&fid=0x0:0x59e2c461f803f0ec"],"When":"2024-7-16"},{"Name":"Roy Pavithran","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUisVEx1KPdsNvsiDSaj5xrPz4-TDKiLVGBnR6psffAhZ3qSzUY=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Found it looking for a breakfast place. Happy with our experience. Good selections in  North Indian breakfast menu. Our host Harry was friendly, polite and professional. Would go back again. 👍🏻","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOKx4jvSh1Jps11JBtww0t5njJIENRFPgnUXLLr&fid=0x0:0x59e2c461f803f0ec"],"When":"2024-8-28"},{"Name":"Ankit Sharma","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLR44-v83LqqXxHNi33fNNryU9EnIj0iAXReeDkuR_D7-vScQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"One of the best Keema Pav & Amritsari kulcha I have eaten outside of India. This place is a gem in Surrey, the quality of food is always amazing. They don't hold back of spices and flavors, Kulcha is served is almost all punjabi places but the quality is unbeaten here, loved the harippa paneer tikka as well.

I regularly take advantage of their breakfast offer!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOpARqquBetHZ9ekud1O7aQmVMQi7fILZXUHllF&fid=0x0:0x59e2c461f803f0ec"],"When":"2024-7-29"}]

And then acted as if the food was ready for so long. Not professional at all. No sitting area. Prefer ordering never go and pick. [{"Name":"Shakhawat Hossain","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUj82Rw5TJH3Le4DVawG-AUG1veXD6bQXDq6jJZAyEkjbjh2JO9=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We tried the chicken biryani, which came with two pieces of chicken, shami kebab, and borhani for $14. The borhani had the authentic taste of Bangladeshi biye barir style, which was a lovely detail! We also ordered the half portion of tehari for $7, and it had a very generous serving. Both dishes were made with polaor Chal, which was well-cooked and full of flavor. Overall, we were very pleased with the quality and portion sizes. I really hope this Bangladeshi restaurant stays around!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPfNRDthM_46JLy-Iv77N7g9kVaGZRsdZZTwTJ3&fid=0x0:0x6b762b8fb576daa"],"When":"2024-10-25"},{"Name":"Md Khan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXC4M18l8R_PYe61dyUTvGkgpbVYIHk3kcsWiEyfOUQeATnQsh8=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We had great experience at Mia Mia this weekend as we went to taste Bengali food. We ordered beef tehari, chicken biriyani, kabab, burhani, and tea. It was not surprising that the food quality and taste was A class because one of the owners/partners of Mia Mia has international cuisine expertise with long experience in culinary art. Good portion of food, reasonable price and fast service. The server and other members were super friendly and very welcoming. Lots of free parking and very conveniently located at the heart of Surrey. A must try place. Highly recommended.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP99ye11j2nxRnKi9jXjac4f_8u9Pg1HW9dJMuS&fid=0x0:0x6b762b8fb576daa"],"When":"2024-10-14"},{"Name":"Tanzina Islam","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXHin0i0PTPm3-Og3CIoFbjHaIuxwcsLJfLsXm1yQ5BTP0mNLM7=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Amazing amazing Bengali food!!! The breakfast is the best I have to say. The chicken platter is a sweet creamy korma and the beef is fabulously hot and spicy! 🔥The vegetable took me back to authentic Bangali hotel breakfast back home.  Generous portion, AND COMES WITH COMPLEMENTARY TEA. ☕️❤️ Must must visit. Breakfast only on weekends! Stays super busy, so plan ahead to go earlier in the morning!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNT4IHLRgQqr6gJEhiR9QBweV_Box5aLjxvjPV2&fid=0x0:0x6b762b8fb576daa"],"When":"2024-12-8"},{"Name":"Md Fazley Rabby Khan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJZ2YY4au-50gbKmHlxD0UPJJkXj3tZNawIy0kFw1LA5i-6tQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Mia Mia Donair and Grill offers a cozy spot to enjoy authentic Bangladeshi flavors! The staff’s warm, friendly service makes you feel right at home. Each dish, from biryani to kebabs, is packed with traditional spices and freshness, showcasing true Bangladeshi culinary passion. With a comfortable seating setup perfect for small groups, it’s a go-to place for a delicious and welcoming dining experience. Highly recommend!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPjVlC6ufFJdLqQQywjoI9rS0g-N0kK5FIpbHv4&fid=0x0:0x6b762b8fb576daa"],"When":"2024-11-12"},{"Name":"fardin siddiky","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWyo_LdhLY6sNlHuJfc--o9yUN_PLiiTXo266yQGW1xSwxWvRuvxg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Mia & Mia Donair - A Taste of Bangladesh in Every Bite

If you’re craving an authentic taste of Bangladeshi cuisine, Mia & Mia Donair is a must-visit. Recently taken over by new Bengali owners, this spot has infused traditional Bangladeshi flavors into every dish, bringing a refreshing and delectable twist to their menu.

The star of the show is undoubtedly their biryani, which is rich, fragrant, and deeply flavorful—each bite transports you straight to Dhaka. The chicken polaw is another standout, perfectly cooked with tender, juicy pieces of chicken amidst aromatic chinigura rice. And then there’s the borhani—a refreshing, tangy, and mildly spiced yogurt drink that’s simply the best accompaniment to the meal. It balances out the spices and adds a unique touch to the experience.

With warm hospitality and truly authentic flavors, Mia & Mia Donair is an excellent spot for anyone looking to indulge in Bangladeshi cuisine. Highly recommended!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO3ep9_3L3NlehQGn1y27pHa31XAM6HN1i-qR4F&fid=0x0:0x6b762b8fb576daa"],"When":"2024-10-27"},{"Name":"Arman fayez","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUiwEjBAM6WpabiC7--N7OzvDeuHSyddolaob94DM7qlsyyft0=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Amazing food! Great place to eat!

Loved the chicken roast combined with pulao! The borhani hits the perfect spot! Its great to see how they represent authentic Bangladeshi cuisine ❤️ It’s a bit on the corner, would appreciate if they had more locations within the mainland.

Much love and support for the place!!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN3-KTrJCy1etLCYTXGI5KoPQV9XhJSO7IXF6dF&fid=0x0:0x6b762b8fb576daa"],"When":"2024-10-31"},{"Name":"Farhana Naznin","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLAnswi7rg7Kb6mxYG8xN1mxlcc2dAyL_EUItgQTqH6ko4OsY04=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Amazing Bangladeshi food… went for breakfast… it was awesome and reasonable price. Also took the parcel for polao-roast combo, authentic Bangladeshi taste","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM--w1VcHStuiTgTNsMLd106TFa-f-onU3l7AX6&fid=0x0:0x6b762b8fb576daa"],"When":"2024-12-13"},{"Name":"IR","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJ50LUWBgvjOkvHbu9_O-JapNBna7XhNHrv3aAnx1BeQzysxfE=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Happy to have an authentic deshi restaurant. We ordered the Tehari meal combo and chicken biryani combo. The basmati rice in the tehari was slightly overcooked but the flavour of both dishes was good overall and the borhani was great. Service needs to be improved, we had to ask for everything cutlery, water, refills, napkins and extra plates.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN861xk2I5U7bppfwE0XRns35hlHKIeFrSxA5oD&fid=0x0:0x6b762b8fb576daa"],"When":"2024-11-5"}]

It is definitely a decent try out people","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOOV6qGn63mh8sviYdeYJx6NPkijiNLdLIjF3j1&fid=0x0:0xc34a4aa203c9f83d"],"When":"2024-7-25"},{"Name":"Dhruv Sanghara","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLVbEuA51Ubo9i57M6YSwmMwM_H2cs7WuES2KJ8TN4wFVcPbQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Their food quality had been degraded quite a lot. When I reached back to them they said they have a machine system on how sauces are added but next time we will take care. Next time you order write same note and they will give same excuse. They used to be good but not anymore, there are way better places who will listen to customer.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPcA1127hFqBgJ-ArQoqbpqkEtMstz2NLaw9a1a&fid=0x0:0xc34a4aa203c9f83d"],"When":"2024-12-7"},{"Name":"Sandra Tran Do","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV9l6s1YZWB64Ki1thgUudvXKddmLpHe47fEzkyE5Wrayj1VfeG=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"I'm a Vietnamese foodie, when I heard about this place I just had to go try it

Ambiance was lovely, not your typical Viet restaurant. Service was fast attentive and very nice
I had a crispy rice and dip dish that tasted similar to home, it was a bit sweet for my taste but definitely didn't think that dish would be made into an upscale dish. The Viet ice coffee is sooo good, I really enjoyed the pho. I had the com Don lunch set for $22 added $4 for the sable fish. This set was okay it wasn't amazing to me. The salad roll and dip is not bad they kept it authentic. Would come back to try more food :)","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP5O7eS0rSJ79idbDOoAiU1X15etmdm787GN3HV&fid=0x0:0xc34a4aa203c9f83d"],"When":"2024-12-5"},{"Name":"Pooja Jain","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLoijTO-Lk55aRsErHcFNOKDM9e7vTR9eBb10OkJGOedR5BcA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We ordered the chaat platter which had dahi puri, aloo tikki, papri chaat and bhel puri. Tandoori chaap with medium spice also tasted good. The pink lemonade was the exact match of shikanji.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOy0xpd4CVFvNfOqPv9zhD4UXoRqRLF8oDi5ZjJ&fid=0x0:0xc34a4aa203c9f83d"],"When":"2024-8-23"},{"Name":"Mohit Wadhwa","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocK41YHBtlLIg8Jymb3a5faEQS6gB5IazboLFiRV54ebSuZq1g=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Whenever I visit Desi Rasoi, I always feel positive vibes. The tables are very clean, and the staff is friendly and knowledgeable. I went there today, and a female staff member, whose name I believe is Hema, provided excellent service. She always has a cheerful smile and offers great service. I’d love to try coffee with her someday. I highly recommend everyone visit Desi Rasoi!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Akshay","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXGdG4K1g--zDRRQKvTXxJZtBDkS7hJ7B1hRUaBBg_pquB_7pU=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Amazing place to eat the Indian street food. Their chaat items are second to none. We tried the pani puri and it’s a must try. One more thing which is totally worth it is the Paneer Noodle Burger. A perfect blend of north Indian and indo-chinese flavours. Do try their Shikanji as well. I would definitely recommend this place over some other popular places in the vicinity. We are for sure coming back here from the US again!!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPvUI-g2NgUuUspJaWlQcsXdTLgQd-NiyS7S_3k&fid=0x0:0xc34a4aa203c9f83d"],"When":"2024-6-3"}]

Our servers were so nice at the kiosk. Checking on us multiple times if we needed any suggestions. The food was great, explosions of flavour. And their milkshakes are incredible. Will be back for more Indian street food!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOTf2-tWb_gdGlGk4i5udr1P8OaLq37wTVkZput&fid=0x0:0xb32e17c9b67b82e6"],"When":"2024-10-27"},{"Name":"Scott Lee","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXHpW7vGME__Zs4wKjXR04Upnw88bkVVyz-H2288JsHocq9vI3r=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"It's a bit different from a typical Indian food that I'm used to. It feels very modern and bright with digital kiosks to take your order. While the service and the food was good, I wish they had more information on the food and the ingredients for none Indian diners because I was a bit lost on all the different types of street food.

I would love to come back with more research and order different kinds of food to try. The shakes also seem very popular so I will try them next time I visit!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPxWv96xZA74zOSzjfcCH4d6cOUwcibppuaJcIp&fid=0x0:0xb32e17c9b67b82e6"],"When":"2024-9-15"},{"Name":"Manali Chanchlani","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWezs3pEhIAEx2SzOjW7JtoyqG_GiVGiuXJWHoJHqiGIJBm6o-T=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Delicious food, friendly staff and very spacious place with lots of seating! Manreet recommended us to order their popular dishes and we loved them all!
Their tokri chaat is loaded with flavors and was our favorite. We also ordered the chole bhature, soya chaap and kulcha. Everything tasted fresh and authentic. Would highly recommend this place if you are in the area!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMs-166698wxCYL0eaOvNRub8UgIoul_SYttQU&fid=0x0:0xb32e17c9b67b82e6"],"When":"2024-10-19"},{"Name":"love kaur","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLj5pRuFSsZMFTmQoHH3vxJtAgbM9b9DTq4749Q7YEevQzGeA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Dining at this establishment has been quite disappointing. While we genuinely enjoy the food, the service—especially from the manager—leaves much to be desired. We ordered the veggie chow mein and waited nearly thirty minutes for our meal. To our dismay, we noticed the staff microwaving the noodles, which raised concerns about their freshness. Instead of addressing the situation directly, the manager sent three different staff members to pacify us, but he never made an appearance to clarify or apologize for the mishap. This lack of accountability and honesty only added to our frustration. They did not offer any solutions. The first staff member tried to offer us another dish, but that person didn't return. After five minutes, another staff member came to check on us, and finally, a third person appeared. But they want to cover-up their mistake.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNyTc__ihH7RD1MYVJlYHY9Cgsk-KadKkKqrMqh&fid=0x0:0xb32e17c9b67b82e6"],"When":"2024-12-22"},{"Name":"Shashank Ahuja","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX-fvMxEb4QFhR0YvgVAfCORCcbVvasQUqOuBvJPYqjKVFBfYAe=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"We recently visited this Indian restaurant and overall, the food was quite good. However, there is a concerning issue with their billing practices.

When paying by card, they round off the total to the nearest dollar, which resulted in us being charged 2 cents extra. While this might seem negligible, it adds up significantly across all their transactions. There’s absolutely no reason to round off if the payment is not in cash. If they want to simplify pricing, they could increase menu prices by a cent or charge the exact amount for card payments.

This practice feels unfair and unnecessary, especially when it’s repeated for every customer and transaction. While we enjoyed the food, this approach leaves a negative impression. We hope the management revisits their billing policy to ensure fair charges for everyone.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMoIYgqybT71ZDFaFdQmtWz4_rw5ruRaz8KY3FY&fid=0x0:0xb32e17c9b67b82e6"],"When":"2024-12-22"},{"Name":"Vijay Purty","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUchl-cnLhiNVGqTw5fSimADiSPSqpKzBXu64ANZGyiGYYuKpBokA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Amazing experience......... excellent food
After long time you can find all the Indian street food experience from every corner of the country, at one place with world class hygiene. Add--on what a great selection of shakes they have amazing flavours ..👌👌👌👌👌👌👌👌👌👌👌
Special thanks to Gursheen, Damneet & Taiyab.....","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOW9gR6EldCaIqexOfVff8dqfAO46lfVObTC7oy&fid=0x0:0xb32e17c9b67b82e6"],"When":"2024-11-29"},{"Name":"swap2188","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXwtZRmQRtq48ykmrP2qz6nPKUoV0_lPN_u0lBaDs7e-oz4rcw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Food is just yum 😋 if you crave for Punjabi street food this is the place to go. Everything is delicious and the flavors are just perfect.
We ordered Bheega Kulcha(must try), Punjabi Non-veg thali, Chicken tandoori, basket chaat (must try), Falooda & Rabri. If you planning to visit from US and takeout they actually do a good job of packing food. Overall one of the best food finds I have had so far in Vancouver.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMAzS0sgAykR1N2zDSN0pJQCuIR4V3_2g5p-NnA&fid=0x0:0xb32e17c9b67b82e6"],"When":"2024-8-6"},{"Name":"Sidharth Jhawar","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWqfvFdclSSlE0wMMqTd7OAs9935GkZqf04JObQ-XgE8pqCZpgI=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Amazing tasting food and service. This place rocks. Never dissapointed once. My trip to Vancouver is not completed without stopping here once, sometimes even twice. Try any item of the list, and you wouldn't be disappointed. Little expensive and loud but overall, came for the food and was not disappointed.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPIxoO_816ZRQZDnwE5Xip9WakiqrJd7RyB_U-r&fid=0x0:0xb32e17c9b67b82e6"],"When":"2024-8-12"}]

[{"Name":"Amy Chan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXXqddZyajPNoFhSfeKC0jxyRc2Om1n2-N6OKu8IHOhfMDJ3cE=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"First to use DoorDash to order food from this restaurant. The grilled lemongrass chicken vermicelli was so small portion. I ordered same food from other Vietnamese restaurant with similar price, the portion was much bigger.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPTpWZ7i_SuLRM6m26G35pr7bgjLI2riLsdXRkY&fid=0x0:0x909964153c312c90"],"When":"2024-7-12"},{"Name":"Con Chronicler","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocILXHCRtdvFXgn0tTM0h8ev_q8sKeKrNAJG8b_jtfVRSIcGpg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This place is definitely a good local, almost hidden eatery for your occasions. The food is tastier than your average pho place. The service never fails to impress, and the atmosphere is classic. Good local pick.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMdGhiMyU57zwF9W6rPccuTqm453LI99hD-vpFE&fid=0x0:0x909964153c312c90"],"When":"2023-12-9"},{"Name":"This food","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUaxcCslaGrcC0u202g67ni7XJGWWGyPYtSKkUjWo5gpcXXO0Yv=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Delicious broth. For 5pm it was not busy, which was great until 6 pm hit. I ordered the house special pho (number 14) and a rice plate (number 62) with grilled pork chop and chicken. The chicken was a thigh only. The rice meal was smaller than I expected, but it was still delicious. Overall great service.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNf4u1dcKzFRycLcxA8x8yOkOZwJ7mdwngEdKIc&fid=0x0:0x909964153c312c90"],"When":"2022-5-27"},{"Name":"Sheena Chandra","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUR3p0C7A3HRi4N9KLcpFSMzefABROoXAyx8Eabt7Fead-uz_M=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"We got great service from the young guy working but unfortunately our tea cups had a long black hair right in it. They quickly exchanged it for us but when I went to pick up a spoon it was dirty as well. Pho broth was nice but sadly I was already turned off.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO5xjTrkMW7Yr2BKUU5tF5H7qEQMlnIk6ATmRlv&fid=0x0:0x909964153c312c90"],"When":"2018-2-4"},{"Name":"eduardo0","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocK2doVpQGldcyxWFXT6quW54ugCUNmn5RMVpSuGqlS2jzmv_g=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"I'm so disappointed that all noodles are broken into pieces when I pick them up,( I ordered No.6), and the man who served us didn't say any sorry or apology at all when I showed him that.
Will never go again!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPuP01z3PYKHYwA5epy7SqcoptT8YmYDNgGkaTg&fid=0x0:0x909964153c312c90"],"When":"2023-10-8"},{"Name":"Paul Ng","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVWUZ49Ul-3bVyJjJAjiIzsDwRpD0pREaGPqHRlWfDN0XxY4lrGiA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Clean, spacious restaurant located in the plaza with plenty of parking.  Price gone up but the portion size remains. Soup is very hot with a very thick layer of oil but a bit salty. Meat looks fresh. Overall is good.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO4afomF0XOYZjZ3irvwLWsX0IGl06D-9rR0Uge&fid=0x0:0x909964153c312c90"],"When":"2022-7-4"},{"Name":"DLH","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKNxoVJChN19TlxEyh2PqXcySZWcsWGp-pw0aGewSStRgeU=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Regulars here since opened. Kim, Johnny and all the servers are super friendly, know the regulars and their orders.
Food is consistent and prices very reasonable. You can definitely get a good cheap meal here as lots of variety. Phō is always hot but does contain MSG for those who want to avoid. However the won ton soup and beef stew with noodle soup does not. Too many tasty options to list. Tea is complimentary and their own special blend.
Vegan/vegetarian options offered.

Busy during lunch on weekdays. Service and food prepared quickly. Would be 5 star if more attention given to cleaning the walls and booths as noodles in soup splashes. 😆

Update(June 2020)- prices increased to reflect current food costs.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOvrW95FLAX8CyDznhdvGAPQAhQB_3l---vuXQ&fid=0x0:0x909964153c312c90"],"When":"2020-6-22"},{"Name":"Jason Hale","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKcIIL_X2tX-dj2FeQITrAXMnZDDnnpAP2sIZG_Ttu-IMw9Gg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Ordered delivery, bad choice. All noodles for soup had clearly been out for hours, they all clumped together even in the broth. The shrimp in the vermicelli bowl were leathery, threw them all out after first bite. Would not order again. Brutal!","Images":null,"When":""}]

user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Jay Swackhamer","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIoZ_wv1qiAi4KdqsYmTyxBMiU8sQ2GWvYO6Jr1f4H_xi_xiOM=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"It’s sushi. It’s “all you can eat” (*)

Every plate was good and well-presented. Service was friendly and fine. Quality was okay. Rolls were good, nice quality to the rice.

Sashimi was pretty small chunks — probably due to the “20 pieces per person” limit (*).

* typical state of the “sushi buffet” these days. Smaller portions, same price.

Nothing against Nordel Sushi, prices have gone up a lot (doubled!!) in just the last 3-4 years. Gone are the days of actually “unlimited” sashimi of high quality.  The quality of the AYCE menu here was “sufficient” but I wouldn’t say as good as times past. But since there’s such a dearth of quality sushi buffet places, I have no real complaints here, it is what it is now.

I would I come back? Not for the AYCE. I’d probably come back to try the a la Carte menu instead, which may be better value/quality.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMziNRaMe-l_3C-FfvzwLdwhenhvRjFx2mix0gZ&fid=0x0:0xbae6aeffcd1b7d0"],"When":"2024-9-10"},{"Name":"Denise Knauer","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW7AxkMI0ZXwyViMlCuoRJl_IXUEpXeOkBTeu91MLXTGLUteDj-=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Unbelievably horrible customer service!  We've been coming here for years, and it's generally been pretty good. Today, however, was a different story.
We spent over $90 for dinner, and it was extremely disappointing and a waste of money, to say the least. We ordered a few items, including a Cali Roll Combo and Crunchy Cali Rolls with brown rice and real crab. The Cali Rolls in the combo had brown, old avocado and the Nigiri Tuna tasted off and very fishy.The Crunchy Cali Rolls tasted off, with a nasty sour taste.  Both left such a foul taste in our mouths, I'm waiting to see if we get food poisoning (fingers crossed that doesn't happen).
When I phoned and told them about our experience, I was told that there was nothing they could do for us. He said if there was anything significantly wrong with our order, he could give us a refund, but because it only tasted foul, he couldn't do anything for us.   They had apparently been serving these dishes all day, and no one else complained, so too bad. I said that was disappointing and we would find a new sushi place, to which he responded, "OK, bye."  Apparently they're not too upset or worried about losing faithful customers.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNUZ33kEbtOjto5tIeikNPQK8mNCTxD11OAZ9RZ&fid=0x0:0xbae6aeffcd1b7d0"],"When":"2024-8-15"},{"Name":"Tess Hildebrand","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJuanHbzMa_LrfMx102cX4d_u_8flJPfZXTrFCcVJCoyyvwDQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"Today was our third visit to this place, and I really love the aesthetic of the place and it was neat having a nearby AYCE place, but the food has been hit and miss and today was the most egrigious. We were served rancid salmon - I thought it had just been stained by the lettuce somehow but it was black on the inside and had a rancid smell. The staff was entirely unapologetic about serving me food poisoning on a plate. Honestly I regret tipping at all.
Needless to say we won't be back, as I'm now questioning the way their kitchen is managed.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOp7dThPmP0zhCF9CJujWqfI3iLb_9AuQ037cN2&fid=0x0:0xbae6aeffcd1b7d0"],"When":"2024-10-5"},{"Name":"Lala B","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJgajmLwMBgGE9264N-jfBkh9m_ivt1oXmNtZY-maZnh6HJLU0=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"This was the smallest and worst nigiri I ever had. For $17, that's insane! It tasted awful too. You could get better at a grocery store :( to make matters worse, the lunch set next to it was $15.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPNPChAJDZyACVGgl430ozpSzMcIIesyaCgXb_a&fid=0x0:0xbae6aeffcd1b7d0"],"When":"2024-9-12"},{"Name":"Terrill Lyngen","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVpaF5MBLC6tJzaPrc78Mx7uXvKYwG_JuMSyBlKDQ1ZzIUjgePG=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"Rotten avocado in my last order of California rolls, very disappointed.

I have eaten here many times in the past. It has been a while due to Skip the Dishes boycott, but I was in the area so I did a pickup order. The order was done on time, as it always has been. Service was fine. Prices are fine.

The food has always been a bit on the quickly made side but the prices were good enough so no complaints. Rolls are often a little inconsistent but portions were fine.

This time though, rotten avocado in multiple California rolls bought for my kids! Lots of dark spots and dark areas, some maybe from contact with nori but some clearly not. It was so bad I had to pick through everything to make sure food was safe to eat. It really ruined my experience and broke my trust. This much brown avocado would have been quite obvious to the chef, so no excuse IMO.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM7qPOQfxHd_DOwx7Am8VoSQF0ADvVXOt4PxZZz&fid=0x0:0xbae6aeffcd1b7d0"],"When":"2023-10-15"},{"Name":"Victor Li","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUMFE5BNhgNfk5RtFjElijU5COak-F8KWg7vkC2eOWy-GXpNlUM=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I've been wanting to check this place out for a while. I finally got the chance and I'm not disappointed. Came here at 4pm on a Wednesday and got the AYCE Dinner menu.

I don't get why other reviewers had a bad impression about this place, but I didn't see anything that was a major concern. On the contrary, it's one of the better AYCE sushi places I've been too. Sure the sushi might seemed like it had more rice to them (not all rolls, but some), but this is a AYCE place. You won't find a AYCE/Buffet that doesn't add extra starch or whatnot to bulk up the food. The sashimi is limited to 20 pieces per person and a bit smaller then the usual gigantic pieces and the negiri is definitely half the size of a regular piece you'd find anywhere else; the fish/topping they don't skimp on either. The tempura is crispy/crunchy, the prawns are regular sized and the yam are half pieces. The gyoza was nicely crispy as well. Personally, I would get the chicken teriyaki. I was hoping for a more crispy skin, but it fell flat when it arrived to the table; it could've been the sauce though, but the chicken did seem a little dry/tough.

When I think of this place now, I think of sensible/petite pieces. Which is great because it gives you a chance to try other things on the menu. The service was quick and the servers are attentive. The best thing is they don't even skimp on your food. I've gone to many other AYCEs and when you order, you're missing a few items; hoping they you eventually forget. This place doesn't do that. They give you everything you order.

Overall, a very good experience and I recommend you check it out if you have a hankering for Japanese food. I'll definitely be back in the future.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOHVUVgNqPgi7AzBh04eT7xScIjalP8gqxI0wUE&fid=0x0:0xbae6aeffcd1b7d0"],"When":"2024-2-22"},{"Name":"Betty Orellana Murcia","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUcu6WKHpuVOgrfNampCwsacpBebTY8L5h4jd9AMWFBpcWJweAvAA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"One of my families favourite restaurants! [{"Name":"Merlin Jose","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWcYx_3Zvjc8iJkthMK_lV6pMFulyPn4wKtWzuvrlUZ1YHIl40JLA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We loved the place!!food is so delicious
Staff was so friendly and energetic
Vancouver needed such a place to introduce Kerala cuisine
Snacks were so delicious
Will definitely will be back","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMHW1nV9OWaueO742vAgndMmm0r0NWl0f23bdV2&fid=0x0:0x8977aa39415a4dc9"],"When":"2024-10-26"},{"Name":"Jaison Joseph Joy","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW7SgfWf1KQN22Vp2LdMadlR8nIIJ4UIwa6B3qmISAobjckQc-q=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Loved the Beef items on the menu. I pickedup and food was ready on time. Good work Anitha Chechi and crew.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMMFmDWHtDSRAsJIcHV8XVGo5IgaX7o3uSdfwqJ&fid=0x0:0x8977aa39415a4dc9"],"When":"2024-12-1"},{"Name":"Anoop Arunan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV_K_sQAM-iiTr5XdEr-OslQ-F5KXFamFwV0fmV5pgrcMvXsbkTxA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I always loved the food here since it always tastes like home made and feels nostalgic. If you are from Kerala, highly recommended to try it out. Also tried out the daily lunch delivery and amazed with the variety of Kerala dishes I received which I never received anywhere else in Vancouver. I am craving to try it out again.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMpQNGFyfvU5oPnGr2KcgxOjqUeIqzT48gedkF1&fid=0x0:0x8977aa39415a4dc9"],"When":"2024-3-14"},{"Name":"Mangesh Sanware","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIhtpWwplilg77UPZMnYtiReouwjfA4lME56l1QCEEnVa6UBw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I r visited Circle Bar and Grill for the first time and had a fantastic experience. I tried the chicken cutlets, which were perfectly cooked—crispy on the outside and tender inside has good Kerala flavor in that cutlets. The highlight was definitely the fried banana; it was a delightful sweet treat that paired beautifully with the kerala chai. The ambiance was inviting, and the service was friendly.Overall, it was an awesome experience, and I can't wait to return to try more from their menu!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"PrakashBeingHappyHuman (Nehru)","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVNRVd-Qym6CS9zbH4Tb0_yvIJ2yga_kaEo1LswYVZ1sG2_HhHt=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Honestly I’m not from Kerala. But I love few foods  from Kerala. When comes to quality and quality of food are equally delicious. I bought the fish poluchathu. Undoubtedly good one.

Other day I bought goat briyani. Sorry no comments about that. If you are Tamil Nadu, honestly I won’t recommend briyani for sure.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipODSeGqWy3rj-zxTG2_P8lPcMMG_oUwRHLWwPbL&fid=0x0:0x8977aa39415a4dc9"],"When":"2020-7-21"},{"Name":"Gazal","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLc1etQ87f5KhbE0oSwuhhmNjbA9vBXTnqoSOC-Iw1svplENw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"The Perfect Circle

The smell of coconut oil garnished curry is still with me. They have almost all the best kerala(South Indian) dishes in their menu. Since they are pretty new, we got the wonderful opportunity to taste most of the menu item. Chemmeen Muringakka Curry(Prawns Curry) is my favorite from the menu. The perfect mix of flavours and taste.

Tried Kappa Biriyani, Kappa and Beef Ularthiyath. Great food and awesome hospitality.

Amazing interior work and ambiance. This is the best place to hang out with friends. You can eat, play some card games and enjoy the moments with your friends. Will come again to drink some tea with Parippu Vada.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM8N_6dBRZq_yVgTMeD1U_CeXzCToLKHHQIgzoM&fid=0x0:0x8977aa39415a4dc9"],"When":"2019-11-9"},{"Name":"Ash Chate","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKnUsSKo48tXLJsuyN63Bx0y4p81mUY4k1QsDAbLqobbOjlxA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"Not worth the price! Bad aftertaste and portion size ain't even enough for a baby. Nashtakachodam","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPGrhGi7Zgu4tJ8NHBaf8N5ioBArV54Q7CmP7f5&fid=0x0:0x8977aa39415a4dc9"],"When":"2024-10-26"},{"Name":"Kiran Daniel","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWy2qM9ooU20km1GTIdwOssSgIxlpylB3E-EdwRU7pDtFMEQOyh=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Delicious Kerala dishes at reasonable prices. The Circle Bar and Grill is a must visit for authentic kerala food. We bought the Rice with seafood combo + crab roast, and boy was it good!!!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMOKnYBOptsx_qyKxppGF1nnYcobK3RXmW-ayXd&fid=0x0:0x8977aa39415a4dc9"],"When":"2020-11-23"}]

The food was absolutely delicious, fresh, and flavorful—the best I’ve had. The staff, especially the girls working there, were extremely polite, friendly, and attentive, making me feel very welcomed. The store was spotlessly clean, which added to the overall positive experience. I left feeling great and can’t wait to visit again. Highly recommend!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Ramone Prakash","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX6nKvsyDb_dx48cKeTpD1Kq-NOUT8qtIdNEhldnZYhUio2fQ3a=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Portions and taste both meet my expectations.

I have eaten far better middle-eastern shawarmas. Such a waste of money and my trust that I had in them for making me a yummy meal when I was starving. The chicken was dry and had no flavour. Only good part was the mini salad in this. Never ordering again.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPeyp75byHZzj6v19GgeDpTu-J5e17xqoPT3BPR&fid=0x0:0x17ae8fd7d92fe2fc"],"When":"2023-3-12"},{"Name":"Anmol Gill","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVEApICp9SbuPMyP0K0VkgirWkZsltt0_L4nL4jLbVbdVRclFQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":""I had an amazing dining experience last night! The atmosphere was cozy and inviting, with friendly staff who made us feel right at home. The menu offered a wide variety of options, and I opted for the chicken and rice which was cooked to perfection. The flavors were incredible, and the portion size was generous. I ended the meal with a delicious baklava that left me wanting more. Overall, I highly recommend for a wonderful night out. Can't wait to go back!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Sanju k","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUD-KZivo3kdkFBWLGljv5a0o834M0YwVAOW9bLSRUGUfBmJce1=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"i been coming here for awhile and im just gonna say the food is okay because i had the rice and chicken and the chicken is a little hard but the service is wonderful","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPyGX9NvJ3FZcstkUFqqFtbXQuVTt5FkQE8q3XY&fid=0x0:0x17ae8fd7d92fe2fc"],"When":"2023-12-28"},{"Name":"Andrew Takahashi","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLngnzoQri0Ba1hqpThIo9w8KcNDjI4Du9Y6TgkdnIFPWP0hQk=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This would be the only exception my wife would allow me to have any sort of an Affair…one that is with a Donair.

They’re open late night and the Caribbean Chicken rice hits the spot! Will recommend 10/10 to have an affair at least once.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOfhICwuBFj06C7RY8wERi6tXtuoerUjqweUqnm&fid=0x0:0x17ae8fd7d92fe2fc"],"When":"2024-3-29"},{"Name":"BrownDadBeigeKids BDBK","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJLPLp3l1Fyvn-yvqe9H0G8JVQg_0DFyo3aGPl4Xz-YW4gD_Q=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Absolutely disappointing, tasteless mess.

I ordered a chicken and falafel wrap.

The falafel was microwaved, so that alone disqualifies this from getting a good rating.

Both wraps were cold, as if they came out of the fridge.

2 bites into the chicken wrap and the whole thing fell apart. The meat was cold and chewy, hard to eat and my stomach hurts now that I tired.

I would not recommend this to anyone, it can not be described as a donair. It was insulting even for a generic donair.

I should have followed my instincts when they microwaved the falafel and just walked out.

Save your money and go elsewhere. I wish I did.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNBj5dZNQRjM26fi8bxHjM044HbxJkVASu8LVtP&fid=0x0:0x17ae8fd7d92fe2fc"],"When":"2022-9-27"}]

user_reviews: [{"Name":"Ms Mama bear","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVLWX5Jxdcwj2wHgBV-1-8EZaNxwhCM_H5mxOtG_pdo6jDTOTR2=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Small little pizza joint in Delta but was always known to our family as awesome pizza with amazing crust which is very hard to find around here. We’ve been coming back to this joint for many many years now however, tonight we were extremely disappointed to the upmost the toppings were not fresh and the shrimp was freezer burnt if you look in the pictures, it’s very noticeable, I didn’t want to risk my children getting sick so I threw out their pieces and the remaining. When in doubt throw it out, I will always stick by that nothing is worth getting Yourself or your family sick. I just don’t understand how this went unnoticed at a restaurant and in this time, and we spent so much to having food ordered in is such a luxury that not many of us can afford to have this experience to the upmost disappointment. There was a hint of salt in the butter on the pancake, but I won’t deduct a star for that. I think it’s a great restaurant overall.

The tall Canadian waiter seemed a bit indifferent—maybe he was having a bad day, but he was very good-looking. I hope it’s just today that’s off for him :) Still, I appreciate his service.

I really like this restaurant, and I’ll definitely be coming back!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMNnlDp_uvITpGmzCy6dY_7iwvT6Eb5ggYdDFA6&fid=0x0:0x1bc1cd6d183f13af"],"When":"2024-10-23"},{"Name":"Kapil Mittal","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJ8k_5eXnIHj1lMV7OJlFNees9CW13_o7Z7kDqI2xpMPIo6rQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I recently visited Denny's in North Delta, and I was thoroughly impressed by both the food and the service. Denny’s North Delta is definitely a great spot for a hearty meal and a fantastic shake .","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP8OexMKcbp-SHSb-eb5FzeUqhB_82xL4E_4vAM&fid=0x0:0x1bc1cd6d183f13af"],"When":"2024-9-7"},{"Name":"Candice Queen","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUfgEkQOx3GUfH1ato6-x-AFDIE4ON3VPH54ClXdIrOt5EIbFzw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Visited this Denny’s location with some friends. [{"Name":"Zeeshan Sohail","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXQzSgXcEIo5d0fY039IL3LLi7k1i-9eyjB9u0xnur9BQekUdtD=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Their claim to fame, the first place in BC to offer truly authentic Karahi. The Koila Chicken Karahi, Lahori Chicken Karahi and Achari Chicken Karahi all have their own special place. Served with naan fresh off the tandoor. Good selection of mocktails on the side. Recommended.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNysEDwjfKW3vrpaSaKZNGP7H0yK1mPWdUZZbA1&fid=0x0:0x88d700e948135efd"],"When":"2024-11-30"},{"Name":"Gohar Waqar","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLbOU8o3D9K7Q9BsC1RluJ-bQrE-m8AqivvlUInY1Lk56blQw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We were visiting with family from Seattle. The food is just Amazing.    Had chicken Lahori, lamb shenwari and nehari. All food was extremely fresh and authentic taste.  The owner him self came and checked on us.  We even did biryani take out.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOD9ue1zR0xouMkLuwEFwjCQxDbuGw75kVhyV5H&fid=0x0:0x88d700e948135efd"],"When":"2024-7-25"},{"Name":"shilpa mahey","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXnZ6zL8F42CZtwouCWKJLYTB08bq00S4QzDZxek-jG49FN7HI=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Hi
Me and my husband went in for lunch. It was a buffet day. Karahi chicken- naan ,chole-bhature, fried fish , mutton soup, french fries and halwa. Food was tasty and staff was refilling the food hot and fresh. Tea was finished in the kettle nearby the buffet so we ordered to refill but it took longer time so we left . Although the experience was good, but i think they need to work on their Service.staff looked very tired and exhausted.
Personally i feel,food choices were less as per the price of per plate.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM6eztgOZr1y-mL1gSXjwEm2OKlgOY2If9hQhp8&fid=0x0:0x88d700e948135efd"],"When":"2024-9-9"},{"Name":"Ahmad Awais","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVKCENA3EQDxfNwGRkIzdwRQJIr8-nzzvbQk_P3TVWN1UAiJIKg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Barney's Karahiwala buffet was really good. From the moment you step inside, the warm and inviting atmosphere sets the tone for a memorable dining experience. The food is nothing short of spectacular, with each dish offering a distinct and delicious taste.

The tastiest Karahi I have had anywhere in Canada. Really tasty. Unbelievable!

The fries at Barney's Karahiwala are another highlight. Often overlooked at many restaurants, the fries here were exceptional—crispy on the outside and soft on the inside, making them the perfect accompaniment to the meal. They were a delightful surprise and complemented the spicier dishes perfectly.

Also I want to say that the staff here works extra hard. Female staff bringing food upstairs again and again from the kitchen downstairs. I don’t know their names. My guess is the owner is Arshad seemed like a very humble and nice guy. Please thank your staff for us and keep them happy. Hard working people.

The Karahi, the restaurant’s namesake dish, truly lived up to expectations. It was bursting with robust flavors, featuring tender meat cooked in a rich, spicy gravy. The complexity of the spices created a harmonious blend that was both comforting and exciting to the taste buds. Each bite was a testament to the chef's expertise and the use of high-quality ingredients.

A special mention goes to the owner, who was incredibly friendly and hospitable.

The Chana Masala, was unfortunately very bland, I talked to the owner he said that was intentional and offered to make it with spice and tarka next time. He personally checked in to ensure everything was to our liking and even promised to make a spicier version of the Chana Masala for us on our next visit. This personal touch added to the overall positive experience, making us feel valued and welcomed.

In conclusion, Barney's Karahiwala is a must-visit for anyone in Surrey looking for delicious, authentic South Asian cuisine. With its tasty dishes, friendly service, and inviting atmosphere, it promises a dining experience that will leave you looking forward to your next visit.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOVaNmlWNSVNvyCr9KmO39TrtNfnmBzo0C21B1G&fid=0x0:0x88d700e948135efd"],"When":"2024-6-17"},{"Name":"samra khalid","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXs2qSAsTg55dIlF-si-Zppj95oi-N4B2CxFDpnKQMFmEzpjCciCQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Excellent experience of having authentic scrumptious karahis(Koila, Shinwari and kabab karahis). Each karahi was unique in taste with a perfect blend of flavors and masalas.
Best service by friendly staff. They came repeatedly to check if anything was needed. Though the main dine-in hall was full and was no table to accommodate our group of 12 people but they  offered us the buffet area space on second floor. Great ambience with family friendly environment.
Highly recommended for KARAHI and TANDOORI NAAN LOVERS!!!
Go dine-in or takeout!!
Butter naans, Koila karahi, kabab boneless karahi and lamb shinwari karahis all became our favorite 👍👌👌🫶🇨🇦 and so as fresh tandoori buttery naans.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOnJmk81cdUC71JQ8WUbd4VVNuy12vOYxPa_1H1&fid=0x0:0x88d700e948135efd"],"When":"2023-12-24"},{"Name":"sajjad khan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLqH2SyzcPjPGArU85x5k3Zkz_11s_-QKPkgvWaP2D6VxOEzA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"The food quality was really bad and service was beyond words","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMO7sDUSgsCnvBE82bfJFWqn6AHSB2lvuR8K1dC&fid=0x0:0x88d700e948135efd"],"When":"2024-12-15"},{"Name":"Prabh pannu","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocL3jQYRSS03YYJx66DwacAxPQdLk7doFwpPaMvMQ9-tjC0EPg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Worst food i have ever had in Surrey, BC. One dish was burned out and other was look like made 3-4 days ago. When I ask for refund they talk nonsense over the phone.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPCvXh6MZMDXgCwJEzrRLLmnEfYJMfzwgJ8u2Nc&fid=0x0:0x88d700e948135efd"],"When":"2024-7-25"},{"Name":"Mirza Tabish Baig","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUl7GQfl2pfswRrb4P6IC5qamH4G05gisHHtklFWgav8momC8mZgA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I visited this restaurant with my family for my niece birthday, we ordered Shanwari Kadhai, grill platter & biryani. I must say the taste was soo flavorful and tasty. Everything was cooked so perfectly.

user_reviews:
[{"Name":"S W","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIMJsU1zZuekdZWUUFOfcZm6o_649kDNomJFxd7YLUv5tNdZg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Great food and quick service. We ordered chicken Biryani and chicken Tikka Masala with garlic Naan, and they were delicious. There were plenty of chicken chunks, and they were so tender and flavourful. The Tikka Masala sauce went well with garlic Naan, but we like it better with rice. We have no issue finding parking. There are limited tables, but we were seated right away at one of the small tables.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMSWNz_PZRUnzbQ2vSESg_LtVYHA7RCBb9M81wR&fid=0x0:0xbf32c1d1263af934"],"When":"2024-12-17"},{"Name":"simran kaur","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWhwxSdfnR_TbFJ4Kse9zfGCek1oJpTHtqau8aX_2uSmDcAMB4=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The food was delicious, never came to this location before but came after watching the weekend special video on instagram and they did not disappoint. Amazing experience, quick service, staff were professional and friendly. Loved it…. Must visit👍🏻","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM-7rHLbTg7reBR4rhCMh74iDsoFWQPWjo51S2Q&fid=0x0:0xbf32c1d1263af934"],"When":"2024-12-15"},{"Name":"Sakshi Sharma","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUoFYD-Y8kosoj3l3UjXFhy1qIaSnGvb0dpDYNqaPp2WdJq7fLZ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Disappointing and Unsafe Experience
I recently take out a samosa patty burger, and to my shock, I found a piece of clear tape inside the food. This is completely unacceptable and raises serious concerns about hygiene and quality control. It’s disheartening to see such negligence in food preparation. I hope manager takes immediate action to ensure such incidents don’t happen again, as this could pose a health hazard.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNxGQ_EPeUpYy1kuixV7G6_hH3cR0-dtjooHSGQ&fid=0x0:0xbf32c1d1263af934"],"When":"2024-12-17"},{"Name":"AFRAZ ALI SYED","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKOwY3iP8Bd591O1hTc1qe8Z0RvrBTT5CVDRDE6ztF17pOlvw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":""I had an amazing experience here at ustaadg.The food was absolutely delicious, especially the chicken biryani, which had the perfect blend of spices. The rumali roti was soft and paired perfectly with the rich, flavorful panner tikka masala. The service was excellent; the staff was attentive and made sure we had everything we needed. The ambiance was cozy and welcoming, making it a great spot for a relaxing meal. The prices were also reasonable considering the generous portion sizes. I'll definitely be coming back and highly recommend this place to anyone looking for authentic Indian food","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM0jpqNBMcSxZMBUNg9UcHk3xp55pI1vLM7qKk7&fid=0x0:0xbf32c1d1263af934"],"When":"2024-10-5"},{"Name":"Ankur Rajput","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVFptjUhVsmmwxyileNdJZlQeDLAv7CaZ-zibPYSfZbElI1TMya=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Ustaad G Scott road offers a diverse selection of authentic North Indian cuisine. I ordered the Amritsar naan Aaloo and mix, which is a chef’s special. Overall, it tasted good, but the crispness was a bit lacking compared to my expectations. Still, it was better than what I usually get in Seattle. The weekend special poori bhaji thali was a great deal, and my wife and daughter loved it. On the way back, I packed butter chicken and chicken kadhai, but both dishes were on the sweeter side, which I didn’t enjoy as much. The lassi was really delicious, with just the right amount of sweetness. However, the tea was overly sweet and inconsistent; the first cup was small, and the second was served in a large cup.

The ambience felt a bit cheap and low quality. The spacing between the tables was minimal, likely to fit more tables, which made the place feel congested.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPqII62CTFbsZMcg4fdibRgAxjewbiMGv0x0myJ&fid=0x0:0xbf32c1d1263af934"],"When":"2024-7-7"},{"Name":"Jaspreet Kaur","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocI5iKS_T6u8BXYhlyyp5useO9_wfYDr16wH10PbwXlzpdvMZw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Review:

I am extremely disappointed with the service I received. From the moment I walked in, it felt as if I was imposing on the staff, rather than being welcomed as a customer. The employees seemed annoyed by basic questions, and each request for assistance was met with eye rolls or dismissive responses.

The worst part was the forced gratitude; after every interaction, I was “reminded” to be thankful for their “help.” It was as if they wanted praise for doing the bare minimum. This left me feeling uncomfortable and unwelcome. Good customer service should be natural and respectful, not something forced or demanded.

I would not recommend this place to anyone looking for respectful, professional customer service. There are plenty of other businesses that know how to treat their customers right.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMvP1xbvDivrXcDyBhOVF5XswtEUbe_l35Q96N4&fid=0x0:0xbf32c1d1263af934"],"When":"2024-10-7"},{"Name":"Navjot Virk","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJZ3rTGtkYeBXwApKdmTNKT7OxGyZ-hYZLsYzYvHU85rclu4A=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"From the warm welcome to the impeccable service, everything about this restaurant was top-notch. The food was delicious, with each dish beautifully presented and packed with flavor. Highly recommend this place for anyone looking for a memorable meal. Will definitely be back!
The staff was friendly, attentive, and knowledgeable. They made the experience truly enjoyable and went above and beyond to ensure we were well taken care of. Highly impressed!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Harsh Dev Singh Rawal","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX-GpPGJPJylDURmY4siIXIm12IUofd0p8QT-vhHIQjub97LiXv=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"“Ustaad G on Scott Road offers tasty food, but the service could use some improvement. The staff could be more attentive and responsive to enhance the overall dining experience. With great food and a little more focus on customer service, this place has the potential to become a favorite spot.”","Images":null,"When":""}]

Friend had a sandwich which was a triple decker with salad.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP0cPyFd4Z9Isyj_nlVEjr6CorEUw1YhFcztuzj&fid=0x0:0xff652bf97dac55e1"],"When":"2024-5-7"},{"Name":"Ravinder","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLkPloS5guSgzrcPyY4emO5BrXTqYyFfYe_2yvQHJjiKU7UVFI=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Some people have bad experiences but I’ve been here 3 times now and it’s been pretty decent every time.
