No decaf Coffee available.
Recommended.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN6BzuRL0esuREsYzgMV-4NXRmAvnd60Sm3UZrt&fid=0x0:0x94c83aa359d6149b"],"When":"2021-7-29"},{"Name":"Timothy Tucker","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWB-QBkVXjJExh3Sxc4Wc1q3FY_8R0LUD2KRoP8ORYAyZKJbpMddA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Nothing fancy here but good food, very friendly staff that remembered our order on the second visit a week later. [{"Name":"Florence Nguyen","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXVO86G7y5AWnQKVB96sxpl0fIwqtk5O6VgA2wVC8hmk_H8_J_X=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We visited around noon, and despite how crowded it was, the service was quick and efficient. The staff were so warm and welcoming. I'm currently 9 months pregnant, and while waiting, she offered me a free drink, which was really sweet. The food was fantastic—I especially loved the crispy pork belly.  I’ll definitely be coming back!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMuG489ecVLLOuJva8shLFRgWdqjxURjpA3xaK8&fid=0x0:0x7d819c908ae2141e"],"When":"2024-10-12"},{"Name":"Cindy Rose","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXh0Mb2aZNKSbCg3ecIqP5jBLg_O2xXbsUeepw6K_Oegut6R9ZuHA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"2024-July.

We were here before noon and got seated right away.

Service was fast. The food was delicious. The servers were nice and polite. The price is good!

Authentic Filipino breakfast!

You should try it!

Bon Appétit 😋","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNz0R9cjeJ-JvE_TKhc3IFT4bE4RTDHhRQtHnVg&fid=0x0:0x7d819c908ae2141e"],"When":"2024-7-21"},{"Name":"Mark Ranges","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJqC34bwyQmEaCqU17TT41PfEGWaSmPBBGc9HbxiPptGekAAg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We’ve been coming here for years, and every time we leave, we’re stuffed and satisfied. The food is fantastic—I’m always ordering the tapa and wings. Prices are super affordable, and it’s my top spot for authentic Filipino silog meals. Highly recommend, 10/10!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOLRXV2TTxpSN_e8G5bkF3zMJY_1t0_9djZyJXk&fid=0x0:0x7d819c908ae2141e"],"When":"2024-10-28"},{"Name":"Sarah Love","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW10_PKOS624ix13nj8YKTo4TAQBtxqwAyn-GvxxaJgFFQ6c7ib5A=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This is one of our favorite place!!

We recently came by to bring my sister and my niece who is visiting in town. EpicSilog is me and my husband go-to for Authentic Filipino food in BC so my family must try it during their visit. The owner was really nice and approchable, we get to chitchat to found out that she and her family was from Winnipeg, MB as well. It was so nice seeing fellow Winnipegers. She gave us a sample of her Mango Mousse. She was thinking of adding it to their already delish menu list and ask us to send her a feedback. I wanted to send her my input on it but I didnt get her contact. Hopefully this will able to reach her? The Mango was so fresh and big chunks was a real bonus, which I am sure people will appreciate because I certainly did! The cake layer was soft and not dry at all, and the buttercream/ganache/creamcheese, not sure what the cream was made of, super delish! I found myself kept on scooping until its was just the empty cup left. It was not too sweet nor bland. A perfect taste of a great dessert. I see myself ordering this type of mouse if she ever decided to make one for orders 😍","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMWFKsf8e7lAG8Ff8Vlfc1yrXXCejM69mcAmfO8&fid=0x0:0x7d819c908ae2141e"],"When":"2024-7-3"},{"Name":"Tearna Salvesen","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU_A5qweBOzpqxR3-rNhjGapVyg_fFMEktwqcm_lRq1vNUpevSGfA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Epic Grill Silogs was highly recommended from my friend in Texas so when we came to Vancouver we had to try it! We were not disappointed. We were greeted with the warmest welcome and felt like part of the family as soon as we entered. It was our first time trying Filipino food and it was delicious! They helped us know what was on the menu and what  we’d like when we ordered. We came with our 2 sons 5 & 2 & they were so kind towards them. Thank you Epic for such an amazing experience we will be back!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOK6CqPdP45c4fvLVwJ5Db8YnOUoHLjpIzWs9w5&fid=0x0:0x7d819c908ae2141e"],"When":"2024-8-6"},{"Name":"Lois Currie","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVxx2Cy3OtPnIV7ATZ8jN12pCE5duu7FrrOsh2g0unMKYijMl7F=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Called to have a bite before the long drive back to Abbotsford.  First experience in a Filipino restaurant!  Loved the new to me flavours!  The desert cake was amazing  Sansrival! Best cake I’ve ever tasted.  Will come again!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO07DiILthYrSBbmTwVkiuz9FlzTSqc9Hhm-igq&fid=0x0:0x7d819c908ae2141e"],"When":"2024-11-9"},{"Name":"Vince Yim","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXlccfol_s7cVFsysxrYrf_T1fOgZ-_ZbICE8ZGBj4hBR-e6EEC=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"It's a small hole-in-the-wall restaurant serving the kind of food you want when you're completely hungover. Had the lechon (crispy pork belly) and chicken wing silog and was satisfied for under $20 plus tip. Would eat here again.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP-cKIMv4WjCJGg9eeansTRfDclACc9tToecSiH&fid=0x0:0x7d819c908ae2141e"],"When":"2024-6-16"},{"Name":"Mark","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXLCDNKZNSnQVXC4-n8_gC6gvvz07auZUisA0OI-YC3M3gT2DMb=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"Had a mediocre meal here. The pineapple-calamansi juice tasted like it came from a can and the dessert was overly sweet. The Silogs were just meh.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOyoBVb4pGmX9kXMUR-io_ghWUT39sAPjLGGoV9&fid=0x0:0x7d819c908ae2141e"],"When":"2024-7-2"}]

[{"Name":"Kingstoon II Grimaldi Jr.","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUz2eH6UkUhbtc0lz4B8UduJaxS50vGlTDywl29HS1vY0pivk5KYA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We ordered lots of different type of dim sums here.  They were very delicious. Service was good, quick, efficient.  No complaints here.  Definitely would come back.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipObyJH_Fq_KdGvJCn0ERqhJGWlwwSM_5Ky_Qx9i&fid=0x0:0x7863782144d6ee07"],"When":"2024-12-14"},{"Name":"Macsen W.","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU7R507e1tQogS7ePLx183cUitHIjVF1AWY7PSdCxN71xj5ZpqStw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"This place is packed. Appointment is recommended. Good Chinese food!

We had dim sum today. All were pretty good except the 炸兩. The 炸兩 was not crunchy at all, it tastes like it's from yesterday.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO3YfGUklIR5X6H5b7YWp11aGkXk0rxq12p1bSg&fid=0x0:0x7863782144d6ee07"],"When":"2024-5-29"},{"Name":"Martin Wu","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjULMBim-Ni19dCGFXpGm1CvL7Cr8xdePUcEl6LFYL17MUm47-fO=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"I still remember it clearly; it was on March 6, 2024. The waiter had only brought me one bowl of rice, which wasn’t enough. I requested an additional one, but he was too busy to bring it. After waiting too long, I asked another waiter for the rice, even saying, “Where is the rice? Should I get it myself?” The second waiter eventually handed me another bowl.

Later, when I went to pay the bill, the first waiter showed that I had eaten three bowls of rice. I said, “Oh, you made a mistake, I only ate two bowls of rice.” He then changed the bill to two but returned, insisting, “Actually, you’re mistaken - you ate three!”

What the hell?😲😲😲 Why??? Why would I lie about $2???🤬🤬🤬

I was angered by his attitude and refused to pay the bill, demanding that they show me the CCTV footage, or I wouldn’t pay a cent.

He told his coworker and the manager, who simply said it was a minor issue and that there were no cameras at the table. The manager wasn’t sure how many bowls I ate but kept repeating that it wasn’t a big deal, eventually letting it go.

Throughout this whole process, no one apologized. Their attitude was extremely arrogant, as if I really had eaten three bowls of rice and was just trying to cheat them out of paying for one! It was incredibly disrespectful! I’m not a beggar!😡😡😡

I paid the bill, but left no tip.👎

It wasn’t about the $2 rice - it was about dignity. I told them there was no reason to lie over $2. The waiter deserved the outcome.

Never going back again!🚮","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMwgaKZBJ9Q-Vvq-ea3SsXQGMPajvwot_R6kPOI&fid=0x0:0x7863782144d6ee07"],"When":"2024-9-29"},{"Name":"David Lee","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLNwj-tocDNurlkNhoZbpg8dTD12QCPPJsLdYV67lCEubvUbQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Enjoyed a big Thanksgiving dim sum meal with 22 family and friends. Ordered all the usuals and they were great as always. Staff are very attentive and quick. Service was quick. My favourite dim sum in Richmond.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOeg2uLFLKMYEEPtzDS7LmRZ1NiM70HutxtyEMS&fid=0x0:0x7863782144d6ee07"],"When":"2024-10-15"},{"Name":"JULIAN","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXmN6h9xGA5SXgnOme5PJ7HPPVdLQeDEaVeZ41Y0FCfy4PIwpH9=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Pretty good authentic Hong Kong dim sum. Reasonable price too. There might be a little wait time during lunch hour but it’s not too bad.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOWO9yxwQEaQLJLAnc-s8ptZXk68AYXsJN2YNtK&fid=0x0:0x7863782144d6ee07"],"When":"2024-8-7"},{"Name":"Karthik Iyer","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocK7GvZL5IcR0xXdyQamH5ox9IhO000LZTmPj3hP7AyCjAagu_g=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Good Chinese food huge menu.
They don’t do dumplings for dinner. I assumed it was served even at dinner time, was a little disappointed about that. But the food was great","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMGzdx2D_4w9FjWfKGsyd5Q22SBv01WLTrSkaBr&fid=0x0:0x7863782144d6ee07"],"When":"2024-7-11"},{"Name":"Cheryl Chan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXKRqwGsiyntapcBOAHD9FtzNPiBoZCzUhMf_hjWst1Da_zYAf8=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Went there for family dinner…place was situated in Aberdeen Centre… lots of parking available. The restaurant is quite big & nicely spaced table.
Service is good, no complaints. Food is good & nicely presented. All in all a good experience for decent Chinese food. This restaurant has been here for a long time which is a testament to decent & good Chinese food.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPg5TfT2f7MEP5Fcp4OqMGzI-3y3EvF3waOeXnT&fid=0x0:0x7863782144d6ee07"],"When":"2024-1-27"},{"Name":"Hoang Le","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUA6JZv8oy7kLYHtzcsV_vlG50p6ak9xnr0WvXguFOqp_Bgm85M0A=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I read an article recommending Chef Tony's two restaurants for dim sum and we picked this one to try. The food was very good, including all their vegetarian options. The siu mai was tasty with delicate skin. The pork ribs on noodles were ordered by mistake but turned out to be a pleasant surprise. All in all, a really good dim sum meal for a fair price. I highly recommend the bittermelon dessert ball but you have to eat it while it's hot and crispy. The only complaints were the chicken feet looked so skinny and dry while turning out to be moist and soft. The pan-fried turnip cake looked thin and stale but the flavour turned out to be good. So just some visual miscues that didn't take away from the meal.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMcK3VlI-W9veFtvzqV4PGrxb8anLzAyVtafTqB&fid=0x0:0x7863782144d6ee07"],"When":"2023-7-17"}]

user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Snaily","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJlbJ8J0xXQ2XR8ZZZXb4Dn8acK4QkurqXEPoF79rl3nwl4yQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"All the food we got were luke warm. Not the best dim sum we had. Price is not low but quality does not really catch up. But this is the only place in Vancouver so far that I found 榴莲酥. It’s not the best I’ve had but again other yum cha place does not offer it anymore. The crust is kinda hard.

Parking underground $2.25 for 1 hr and $3.25 for 1.5 hr. Fortune terrace only reimburse $2.25 but T&T reimburse $3.25. So just do 1 hr here.

Final bill with 5 dim sum for 2 people was $70 before tip.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOxMkBlM2VeM3D6M48fiL4GiA5lK0umpYmu12-w&fid=0x0:0xc64f088ae0e05c63"],"When":"2024-9-14"},{"Name":"Spike Luk","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVljR41LewaD1cz5kVqUD3bmc9ybJSH00GIF-DrHusS8cKNejJe=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"We decided to take the family to Fortune Terrace Chinese Cuisine for dim sum.  It’s a fairly new restaurant as we have seen it build out while visiting the Oval for the last couple of years.  We have read and heard good and bad things about the restaurant.
First of all parking is underground and reimbursed at $2.50.  So if you paid for two hours they will reimburse half of it.
We made reservations for 12:15 and were seated right away by a friendly host.
It was Saturday and the restaurant was busy.  The servers could be seen quickly picking up plates and serving dim sum to each table.
Once we sat down we went through the order sheet that was in english and chinese.   The form seemed a little busy but if you take your time it’s pretty straight forward to check off what you want to order.
We ordered Jasmine tea but you have a full selection so just ask.
Once we gave the order to the server the dim sum came fairly quickly.
I give props to the chefs for attempting to elevate the dim sum.  That being said some things are better left alone.
The pineapple bun with wagyu beef was a nice treat.  Honestly I could not tell if it was beef or char siu (roast pork).  It was very yummy though.
The fried mochi balls with pork aka ham sui gok was yummy.  The green food colouring was not necessary.
The fried Taro balls with scallop were good.
The shrimp spring rolls were nicely done.
The abalone truffle sauce siu mai was delicious however this brings me to one of my complaints.  If you are going to elevate dim sum you also have to be consistent in plating and presentation.  Take a look at my pic and see where one of the abalones is off centred.
The traditional dishes, beef balls, tripe, chicken feet,  and pork wrapped in bean curd are done well.
The fried radish cake in XO sauce was really tasty but could have used more bean sprouts garnish and sauce!
The har gao shrimp dumplings were good.  Really not sure there was a need for a green wrap to the middle one.
The shrimp and scallop dumpling was good.
The salted egg yolk buns were cute but more importantly the filling super yummy.
We also ordered the fried taro and lychee bun.  It was ok.
The green mochi and black sesame lava bun was good.
Overall it was a good experience.  The server was very good and let members take pics before cutting the dim sum for serving.
If you want a traditional dim sum experience there are other restaurants out there that will offer more bang for the buck.
Our bill was about $300 for 7 of us.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMLNlsePhVzG_5TGlWf3KFJqp9g15bBY77sVD89&fid=0x0:0xc64f088ae0e05c63"],"When":"2024-7-21"},{"Name":"La Mc","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJ3bmuxSiXCjm1iot5JpVUU_Lxxw4iPTmDpAUVL9Q9e-760ag=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I’m going to give this place a 5 stars for the following:

- It’s not a big place but for a wedding it was very intimate and perfect for this purpose.
- Food was good with some special unique dishes.
- service was responsive which is important when you are there serving so many dishes and various drinks.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN84Lr8z4-eElLPbEwgpdxjHM5TcZSXP0SGdgEi&fid=0x0:0xc64f088ae0e05c63"],"When":"2024-10-6"},{"Name":"Junhua Chen","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUXxr7N9U4iv6nEFijXKvyBgZmRQZVZlxLrBqwPq87wnlqswGv9kA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba7-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Fortune Terrace has great service and the food is good. They will also reimburse the CAD$4.5 parking fee, which is a nice touch.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNREUOIaTas3KFJnzggtdbnphbWUFPGfwmWN7IY&fid=0x0:0xc64f088ae0e05c63"],"When":"2021-9-2"},{"Name":"Yun","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWp7pdS58D6BxZas-oP224TAyLzNPJ48ZcA73CYmOhSMFsOmTi4=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"This restaurant made our Vancouver trip very pleasant.  We were amused by their unique dim sum presentation so we were back for king crab dinner on the same day!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNuHmRk6ehdUf136Knc3-iURESqEul8N01YrMJJ&fid=0x0:0xc64f088ae0e05c63"],"When":"2024-6-2"},{"Name":"Sandra Chan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUS3d7aZA4lMhkB4lrjOTrDjB_p6PvngmeWQeM0VFHPfzqli2Uc=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"My first time here. We were a large group so got to share a variety of dishes - most were very tasty. The restaurant is large and open, so quite noisy. There’s underground parking; pay first and it’ll be taken off the bill. It’s on the pricey end compared to other Chinese restaurants.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN8WAAXGZTA-J2xjXPZa5c-2lH1cEWRHxKEGiOn&fid=0x0:0xc64f088ae0e05c63"],"When":"2024-4-28"},{"Name":"Daniel Lee","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJJPPwe1UGPzBjSlskyCna5pxZbncE7o_-4QmMFJvgKz1-O9w=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Price does not match quality or service. We had a friend in our party so the service was excellent, but all the attention went to our friend, the service person did not say a word to the rest of us.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMJxbhIGcMOows61jvwqSzlxwDEPatuSYaatc0W&fid=0x0:0xc64f088ae0e05c63"],"When":"2024-12-7"},{"Name":"Michelle M","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWeetN-W20mnzvtvgZG8vAeDlWwG6zd354oPCvc1I4B_3Cjy_PI=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"My second time eating here for dimsum and it seems like the quality and presentation has gone down. The restaurant looks fancy and staff was efficient but the food is what we came for.

They were super strict on the time limit on a Sunday. I liked that it was free parking especially around that area.

The dimsum was good, nothing was extremely special besides the mango roll. Which is mango sago wrapped in a mochi skin. Everything wasn’t overly salty or greasy. Price point was a little bit higher.

The least favourite is the salt and pepper squid which was tough and overly fried. I enjoyed the salted egg yolk bun too.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPojWwdQamMJsbOAW97YRZr2ED6mN2XlXepnFJ3&fid=0x0:0xc64f088ae0e05c63"],"When":"2023-10-16"}]

user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Tyra Baltram","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKvzE7mZZZY3BoRgyYVAmckgE999jzZibrXNp_9UUb3Q9Lw6A=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We had a fantastic lunch at Cactus Club Cafe. Upon arriving without a reservation, we were told it would be a wait to be seated outside, or we could get seated inside the Lounge immediately. I wanted the harbour views from the terrace so I opted to wait. I'd say it was about a 10 to 15 minute wait, but I didn't mind because watching the hostess work was amazing. She was very efficient, a powerhouse in heels, and with a smile.

Once we were finally seated at our table, they didn't have physical menus, only virtual, but this suited me fine. I finally decided on the Truffle Parmesan Chicken and my partner got the Steak.

The food was sublime. The chicken was absolutely delicious, crispy outside, and well seasoned. The gnocchi was to die for, melt in your mouth soft, and the sauce was flavourful. Even the mushrooms were absolutely gorgeous tasting, like an explosion of flavour in your mouth. My partner's steak was good, but my chicken was so much better.

On the other hand, the drinks were very poor. A bit too boozy for my tastes and expensive.

We also got the chocolate cake to share and it was good but super rich and decadent. We could barely finish it between the two of us and the vanilla ice cream did little to help.

Overall, Cactus is clearly a popular spot and the food is enough justification why. I would love to go back and have their chicken again, so I highly recommend it if you are going to check it out!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO_v_CNbqgFBuRPQcRLX0kV89uQlV2uMlojf4w6&fid=0x0:0x60248a028fed8b2a"],"When":"2024-9-21"},{"Name":"Anton Castillo","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJOQnue1D_0cDF6CxLvXY1pJBzVXlenLeHbcfuDm1CVjN6ChQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Aidan our server was very nice and knowledgeable. We we’re group of 11 people with separate table. I ordered Rigatoni Bolognese and explained thoroughly what ingredients its made of. He was very patient and entertaining. We had a time to chat with him while paying our bills. He made our experience at Cactus Club Coal Harbour very memorable.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM9R50IR-w-yaJlFM7FHDzD4Om-Vxj6JwJHAczg&fid=0x0:0x60248a028fed8b2a"],"When":"2024-12-19"},{"Name":"Amy Rexroat","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKvlF1N7YfdtUGZyGXxG3y40Ry6JG_x_Afz3pqnz7hjNtxfmA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Our server, Jade, was amazing.  She made 2 fantastic suggestions, the red coconut curry and the butternut squash Ravioli.  We got both and shared them, and substituted chicken for the prawns on the Raviolis. Both dishes were excellent!!! We were seated outside on the heated patio, which was plenty warm. Jade provided great service and was extremely kind and welcoming.  We will definitely go back.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOT0K3ddm7PLXgMxojOd4T90PBOzhqDSIL49PV4&fid=0x0:0x60248a028fed8b2a"],"When":"2024-12-7"},{"Name":"Shawn","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWjDFHDIcbtV_DjbplKljLcAMOcHcimjCyqMXoLTCCbOhYL58Lu=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Amazing views if you get a table at the waterview dining area. Highly advise reserving, as it's quite busy.

The food is spectacular. The dijon salmon and crispy tofu bowl are delicious and the sides of fries are addictive.

The service is friendly and accommodating to dietary restrictions like lactose intolerance.

The washrooms are clean, huge, and luxurious. There is a TV in front of every urinal!!

10/10 we will be coming back!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMwa21AjIz3PW9GVHj6Z-KCcs2oBxsuhy8-Ak4O&fid=0x0:0x60248a028fed8b2a"],"When":"2024-10-26"},{"Name":"Dana Fayoumi","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUvsbA8LIAipLh--rd2OENPaerFN1HCx-loZG0Yx9ajd7UqTnqw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We really enjoyed everything at the restaurant! The vibes the food the view and the service. We ordered all 3 sushi plates and they were amazing. The calamari is also really good. We also ordered the avocado salad, its good but not very special. Highly recommended place","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPSkrdiLc_O6B0alTXciiAhu-5OeBYRw0MCWTnk&fid=0x0:0x60248a028fed8b2a"],"When":"2024-11-3"},{"Name":"Erin Hansen","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV1chjvhTi0s-q0iJkgsURXCf8YCwx3OTVGiG5jgofZF-z5sHMb=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Food was very good as was the service! Definitely recommend  reservation. We came by on a Sunday night with one, and it was packed. There did seem to be a line available for walk-ins. I got the spaghetti portofino and my husband got the tuna poke bowl. The Portofino was one of our favorite dishes we had in all of our Vancouver stay.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPTDYsNaPDGGiZXjN0IJ6Oh0O8G_TZrJm-x-E-Z&fid=0x0:0x60248a028fed8b2a"],"When":"2024-12-21"},{"Name":"Sarah Kosari","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWRKJF1Yntnp-zRLmumvc9e-i3Wwazxmkif9r_MkSiD9JZJ8ngfpA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I absolutely love the location and setup of the Cactus Club at Coal Harbour! The stunning waterfront views combined with the sleek and modern design make it a standout spot. My go-to drink here is the Sangria—it’s always refreshing and perfectly crafted.
The food, atmosphere, and service are consistently top-notch, making every visit an enjoyable experience. It’s no wonder this has become a favorite go-to spot for me and my friends whenever we’re in downtown. Highly recommend!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNI6rYh-wTG-T1ruA-PQ4Ps3Y6Y3tkrDTToHOwA&fid=0x0:0x60248a028fed8b2a"],"When":"2024-12-5"},{"Name":"Karan Singhal","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVP5J5MGNh8IDxrGZuOVcfyJTyWcMqxdNNlxz7hcVpBCrBWw29TuA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"6 or 6.5. Tuna poke bowl is great and healthy. Red curry is also really good but maybe double chicken since there’s not enough. Worth coming if around the convention center for sure","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOyTMyMkHyRBDz41cwNeTC8RD1aacZr9ATXDNhr&fid=0x0:0x60248a028fed8b2a"],"When":"2024-12-22"}]

user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Mr Reviewer","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJCEFN36D2SvEOMAjati6BuzGzt03Az0mGZppTsNlwq_OZPIQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"What a great way to end our 4000km+ roadtrip between Calgary and Vancouver Island! Before heading home we wanted to have one last dinner by the water and I found this place on google maps!

We really enjoyed the view! I made a reservation and was given a nice spot outside facing out towards the water which I believe was the best seats in the house in my opinion.

The staff was very nice and we had no issues with them.

The tartar, fish&chips, as well as salmon was delicious! I do have a few things that could be improved. The tartar appetizer comes with chips to dip but you don't get a whole lot. The plate didn't feel full. Still delicious. The fish&chips was great but just a little too much batter on the fish.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNk3rHPosVuv5mAv3yL9IQyjw5hCaPnIfAdbR00&fid=0x0:0xf381e8c770190b92"],"When":"2024-9-7"},{"Name":"Elmira Nazari","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUS8psOPde-fgvVYsglTVKj-j9hpNdB1347mGr_T9d11yAStREO4w=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Overall good service, food presentation and flavours. Waterfront venue with outdoor patio seating. Service was okay, nothing above and beyond. There are decently better restaurants at this price point. We ordered mostly seafood dishes. The crab was sub-par, hard to open due to soft shells and salty. The muscles, clams, shrimp and oysters were all fairly fresh and delicious. Seafood chowder was one of the better ones we've tried. The salad was our extra order, but it ended up being one our favourites here with the dressing and ingredients used. Caesar cocktails above par in texture and flavour.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMx62wxAGpByDMY6wZMC8H-oRvXX_7cumVmv4IJ&fid=0x0:0xf381e8c770190b92"],"When":"2024-6-3"},{"Name":"Jioh Kim","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUKSWfpbNYcWQsWaiXfEMb52v-8T7Q_sZwrESiKgHFQas3hVA414Q=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Awesome waterfront restaurant with heated patio. I loved the details for having blankets on every chair for chillier days and the boathouse decorations. We tried the Tuna Tataki Salad, Tuna Tartare appetizer and the crab dip! Everything was delicious, especially the salad - tangy sweet sauce with fresh raw tuna with all the crunches worked so well all together. Also the service by John was excellent!!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNcB8eK6If08T0fVMk3-Jfm1Sw89dnCkMmQOVjF&fid=0x0:0xf381e8c770190b92"],"When":"2024-10-15"},{"Name":"Ross Manson","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVEpVSqeqsTvRNtUJOrSLjIA9rzMulA6RrCY8I-EdxSNnHKVrVT=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Went here for my birthday last week and had a great meal with my fiancée and a friend. We made reservations for Thursday at 7pm and the place was pretty quiet, though it wasn’t the nicest weather out, so Steveston period was pretty quiet. I’m a huge seafood fan and love a good seafood tower, so with the help of my friend we did our best to take down the yatch sized tower! We were both thinking should we order an appy just in case the tower isn’t enough and I was soooo glad we didn’t! The tower has soo much seafood and could easily fulfill even 4 people with a sufficient amount of food, though with 4 you may need an appetizer? My fiancée had the fish and chips and she said she enjoyed them, nothing special but good fish and chips all the same! Our server was great, treating us all to a welcome/happy birthday shot and a nice piece of cake for dessert. The restaurant is a great spot and must be even better during a nice day. Solid food, service and atmosphere and would definitely go back to try something off the menu that is not a tower. Thanks for a great birthday meal!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNVJD3Rakdl49snNIC_WrRnG8va7P2leXXyV4kq&fid=0x0:0xf381e8c770190b92"],"When":"2024-10-1"},{"Name":"Cody K","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKtsK86_MBqsog-rDOnkrv2oXxx0XCD_anFgr30-6w0NUAe-Q=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Our server Mel really made this experience incredible. The food was good, but the view and the service is really what made this experience excellent. If you ask for Mel, you will have a great time with fantastic recommendations.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOT2bT8AeOdnFfM1xaWBC4I4XQrLK5r9MMWa1mR&fid=0x0:0xf381e8c770190b92"],"When":"2024-8-3"},{"Name":"Eva Zia","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUJp1CScTOq-jdIBVBA-K4f_r74TZU-kRd9MclConVIiSCPfy3Y=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"H
"We went here for dinner, and everything was excellent. The view at sunset was especially beautiful, the food was all great, and the cocktails were delicious. Highly recommended."","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMkSvREe3ziqsOIGtAnoGugRAz3nwg76iAP3H3T&fid=0x0:0xf381e8c770190b92"],"When":"2024-8-19"},{"Name":"Brandi Bruce","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKKeG0WrfuxUhK3Ku-ntETaFtmYelZqEOEApt-_bYkBAl-UqA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I attended a staff Christmas event here on December 12th. It was my first time at this restaurant.

The atmosphere is so welcoming and cozy. We were there at night and the lighting along with the Christmas decor was amazing.

For the event there was a set menu with a few choices for each course. I chose the 5 spice short ribs which were insanely tender and delicious. The truffle mashed potatoes were perfect as well.

The best part of the experience was our main server, Melanie. She was so friendly and warm and has amazing people skills! Always around when we needed a refill or top up. A level of service and kindness you don’t often see in the service industry these days.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Thanhha Ho","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVgS9YuCHUfmftaf64u1KV9rTAYd_9KujoU4NWr7V6IXVIrZA8k=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Great location right on the wharf!   Seatings available indoor and outdoor.   Great fresh seafood selections.   For 3 adults an order of 2 tier seafood variety plate is sufficient.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP5yg-FLrrM5TgxoKLLAAbQQZYUislKBj6XOw3B&fid=0x0:0xf381e8c770190b92"],"When":"2024-6-22"}]

[{"Name":"C S","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJuJuczs95n5im7BgwLrX3r1-rzt25HaRNL-elqFF8jgyqbtQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"My friends and I dined here two weeks ago, and everything—from the food to the ambience—was amazing! However, what truly made the evening unforgettable was the outstanding service provided by Christina and Goose. Despite the restaurant being busy, they went above and beyond to make my two friends' birthdays extra special. They surprised us with complimentary champagne and a lovely birthday dessert platter, which truly made the celebration memorable","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPcA_wmnIDzA8FL5cvxF8dav3LILK6Iwv0bTJo0&fid=0x0:0x270ea311df9d277a"],"When":"2024-12-19"},{"Name":"Tatyana Ayrapetova","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXhKy-98t6ZdKhPzAFPxODP0Ie3Uo94lXS45JQrA-ha8UeYbax-0w=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Beautiful posh place with an amazing service. The food was fabulous as well as our wine. On not so bright side, the rooftop fireplace was way too hot. Also, I was taken down by hostesses who gave full 10 min of attention to a couple before me and made me wait in the doorstep","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOjgPdKkW4DDohQMruf4DKd-Jzxocw8C6J3zW-z&fid=0x0:0x270ea311df9d277a"],"When":"2024-11-17"},{"Name":"Angie M. Prieto Paez","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXZPKGXyNx-m47A1dNyvsbJAj-dIrn36q2eSJ81ZJgXBZ_UHFt-ZQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Our first time, I liked the ambience; I chose the roof, which was a really good option. However, we didn't have a great start with the cocktails; we asked for a passionfruit mojito, but it was not as I had expected. There was too much ice, and we couldn't taste the liquor. Starters were okay; burrata salad was my favorite. Dinner finalized much better for my partner with his choice of New York stake and a fantastic surprise of a dessert for his birthday.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOf3-gYmQIbJC5PPHR22T38800zEMR1tZ9pRuTF&fid=0x0:0x270ea311df9d277a"],"When":"2024-12-19"},{"Name":"Ivetta Abramyan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVWna-qgjBouZPH-f2av_biFEbTaNeBAzefwCDwybRahPzT_qCv=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Highly recommend this place for several reasons! 1. Great happy hour 2. Beautiful ambiance 3. Excellent service

We had the mac n cheese sticks, sliders and jerk chicken pizza (spicy!). They even brought me a surprise birthday dessert, their butter cake (which was delicious)!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOuvIY7ybkVy3yCDaKfSTmpWYvtoQEVGj7w-gH1&fid=0x0:0x270ea311df9d277a"],"When":"2024-8-25"},{"Name":"Munro Stuff","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWj0Wcuk6ox5dfAeJ4fAaMbhX_F-nzzt3p5oc_f0hBd0NpbGSM=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"It's clear that the team here really cares about guests and their overall experience - service from the entire team was excellent. Beautiful space. Great Happy Hour menu. Charcuterie had a good variety, though I missed the hummus of years past and there are now too few crisps (add some baguette pieces to the mix?). Calamari was light and perfectly presented (wow, a sleeve on the lemon to strain seeds). Jerk chicken flatbread had a definite kick and was delish. All great for sharing. You know an establishment actually cares when their washroom is a thing of beauty! Looking forward to our next visit already.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMRXAyWVLimigU_hbhclbJJMhNKYm4nvOGvtjup&fid=0x0:0x270ea311df9d277a"],"When":"2024-8-8"},{"Name":"Charlotte Dean","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLktyaYj6PuJurHWpIjlCBdZlL90dsKhsj_QA0D_xmMcb5pvA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"What a beautiful rooftop patio with amazing service, food, and happy hour options!! Our server, Sydney, was exceptional and really made our experience with her wonderful attentiveness and recommendations. The oysters, wagyu hot stone and butter cake were all delicious!! Thank you!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP4h1s9ZCyRFy_-xN6bimsskVrlZX1yvZ2eoXZT&fid=0x0:0x270ea311df9d277a"],"When":"2024-8-12"},{"Name":"Dales Auto Service","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUnof06SuhxRVKPZWIiLlR60MICvwSP3SWhcWmVDRhT8khQkLblpw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We’re in town for a staycation and enjoyed brunch at Black and Blue Rooftop. Service was top notch, the atmosphere was very nice and the food was great.

We highly recommend.

Thanks again!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOArKc5r8q8l5Jh88xqjnPtgCrgtAUNlfyR9yA1&fid=0x0:0x270ea311df9d277a"],"When":"2024-11-11"},{"Name":"Liz Basson","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXHcrDoEcSgNl20_Kapu_UXuu1wZRs6EL6r48CezJkwfFdro-Gy=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"On a beautiful summer night, The Roof at Black + Blue was the perfect location for a birthday celebration. With attentive, friendly service, delightful birthday surprises, and every bite and sip a delectable experience, we will definitely be back! Thank you to the team for giving my husband the birthday dinner he deserved!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOoZ-AIn5QsSkBYLnC68eyYRjkx6lFsHYkXf6JS&fid=0x0:0x270ea311df9d277a"],"When":"2024-8-4"}]

user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Mehul Gautam","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVUWfCAHcbrboibLKGQvB-6XITmMahnsJsanCyw3xnR-9XifHCrTQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The food is extremely delicious - way better than most other restaurants I have been to.
I absolutely love the Cajun chicken sandwich - my all time favourite dish. I love the New York Cheesecake too. It is one of the most perfect cheesecakes that I have had in a long time!

I had a fabulous time there with the nicest / warmest service. They truly go above & beyond in providing the best.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO3KIoMTVJfKfqA9Be0Ann4veN0P7b6IkvDUBUm&fid=0x0:0xc4ca7558f4984c8e"],"When":"2024-12-23"},{"Name":"Kenneth Lai","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVaxVGYXfpPoTmAfNhLJtbs31BGbuX8DK_7Hj5GOcCBNwv8VjrvXA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba7-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"I recently visited Cactus Cafe in Richmond, and it was a fantastic experience! The vegan burger was simply excellent – packed with flavor and cooked to perfection. Their chicken tacos were equally impressive, with tender chicken and fresh toppings that made each bite delightful. The highlight, though, was the peanut butter crunch dessert, which was outstanding – a perfect mix of creamy and crunchy textures that left me craving more. The ambiance was cozy, and the staff were friendly and attentive. Cactus Cafe is a must-visit spot in Richmond, whether you’re vegan or not. Highly recommended!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN6kWg2fgouL-I-M4wHPGdDkguPjlBmgVq_ZIiz&fid=0x0:0xc4ca7558f4984c8e"],"When":"2024-11-11"},{"Name":"Samantha","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLiBNPV0WM2QyZIomdZFReW3hhBQYlq1lHEnztGJxFPhA7qVw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I had a great dining experience at Cactus Club Cafe in Richmond. I've visited Cactus on several locations, but this is the first time I felt happy to return. My food was delayed a bit because the white rice wasn’t ready yet, but the waitress was incredibly polite and offered me the option to wait 20 minutes or choose an alternative rice. I was perfectly fine with switching, and what really surprised me was when the waitress came back to apologize and offered me a free dessert for the wait. That was a lovely gesture!

Our server, Elise M., was also very attentive and cheerful, making sure we had everything we needed. I want to give her a special thanks for making our night enjoyable. Overall, I had a wonderful dining experience with my friends and look forward to going back!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOJN90V_EXgJOYtVQGxebD-lj6uJIJhJyHaS1xP&fid=0x0:0xc4ca7558f4984c8e"],"When":"2024-11-1"},{"Name":"Fionn Lai","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJ6QM4xX4rnjDy7uQ9_UX1ud-FeXhAIPbUGuv1ks1vTREnqqQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Overall food was good, service was great! Atmosphere was nice. I got the Bolognese! Tasted very good! Definitely will come back. It’s located in Richmond centre which is convenient if you need to wait for your table.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNEnRAs2w4SiuAoDKVyu31i2KIF5RDPE5JAETel&fid=0x0:0xc4ca7558f4984c8e"],"When":"2024-11-24"},{"Name":"Hakan Guzgan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUA_W8rhFsh5vl3N-SwOXx9x2M4aBXN2TS01V15E4k2zvHSImaORA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"**Delicious Food and Exceptional Service at Cactus Club Cafe Richmond**

Cactus Club Cafe in Richmond is a must-visit restaurant if you're in the area. The atmosphere is vibrant and colorful, setting the perfect mood for any occasion. The menu offers a fantastic variety of food and drinks, with something to satisfy every palate. I highly recommend their Epic IPA—it's simply delicious. My personal favorite is the Cajun chicken burger with yam fries, a dish that never disappoints.

The location is also very convenient, with easy access by bus and SkyTrain, and plenty of free parking available. After enjoying a meal, you can even take a stroll over to Richmond Center Mall for some shopping.

What truly sets this place apart, though, is the outstanding service. The staff are incredibly friendly and fun, making every dining experience special. I’ve had the pleasure of being served by Jennifer, Noah, and Jacob, all of whom are professional and ensure your food is made just right.

Cactus Club Cafe has maintained its delicious taste and high standards for over 20 years, and I highly recommend everyone give it a try. You won’t be disappointed!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOF7ti8v468n1FFezlBcmt_fjh3dwk1RAjH_Ux2&fid=0x0:0xc4ca7558f4984c8e"],"When":"2024-8-29"},{"Name":"Sylvia Lan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLZOrignIxZtNQr5fqOb9lpoqxcw0LTJa79u5ODK0MTYwholQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Beautiful and cozy environment. Consistent decent food quality. Friendly and welcoming staff. Quick and professional services. Cactus Club is always a good choice of place to sit down and chat with friends!

Pricing is a little pricey but definitely worthy for the overall experience and especially for the outstanding services!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP26iEjSMRNVBNnfPq-72euLPyULvjGJOjwecNY&fid=0x0:0xc4ca7558f4984c8e"],"When":"2024-8-21"},{"Name":"ユノアYunoa","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUjb-9fmtTSx8hqCIoWqnedMR35nqhPIaEnKm2tWMaX_d-sIJvR=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Mmm I wouldn’t say the food was that bad but they did switch me and my friend’s steak wellness, I wanted rare and she wanted medium rare, but I got medium rare and she got rare. It wasn’t that bad but I did think my steak was a little burnt on the outside which was harder to chew, the lobster I had was also wayyy too salty, it just tasted like sea water, other than that the other stuff was fine and the drinks were fine but we learned we don’t like margaritas that much.

But the server we had was very nice and attentive so the service was good.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPJ0iJK9scJMRMbPemMWoWsjlcvQEFVpoxYtei2&fid=0x0:0xc4ca7558f4984c8e"],"When":"2024-10-22"},{"Name":"szigeti anna","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXO8wV_bW0HLPIGb8SlgqJHo9eo9SWQK2r_1IJkrboM1Vf4-rwcxw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The food was amazing, wine pairing was ok but ! Sayoka was the sweetest waitress, made the experience that much better! She always made sure I was taken care of and she was very attentive but not over baring 10/10 would recommend!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMYXWCgy7qrY_nmphufMCn86hCQm2zRV-nMYhri&fid=0x0:0xc4ca7558f4984c8e"],"When":"2024-12-14"}]

user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Arturs Mons","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVynJ4wFaO1n4O08x-FxTv1KPmlWKP1TXMDnyQPLz_hUxyhn-oQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"The Story Cafe in Vancouver is a charming spot with a lot of potential. The ambiance is cozy, and the menu offers a nice variety of options. We visited during the Taylor Swift concert weekend, and while it was clear they were overwhelmed and understaffed, the staff were doing their best to keep up.

The food arrived a bit cold, which was disappointing, but given the situation, I understand it was a tough night for the team. Based on the quality of the dishes and the overall vibe, I’m confident that under normal circumstances, this would be a five-star experience. I’d love to return on a quieter day to enjoy everything as it’s meant to be!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPV1mNxPTn5IitYwtvs1dKRCN9iQbVRShN2bDvl&fid=0x0:0x63843290b0d51c86"],"When":"2024-12-12"},{"Name":"Jimmy Zhou","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX72ZuhWzFJa-dvzhpIYEgFMddZHT0-fUecIaPoe_e7xYZfxGcl=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"This cafe is located a few minutes away from a lot of accommodations and hotels. I would say it's worth it to grab lunch here, especially if you're nearby on a visit.

The overall atmosphere was warm and inviting, and the host and servers were kind and prompt.

I would say that it took around 40 minutes for our food to come after we had ordered it, so it's a bit slow. I can understand because we did come during the lunch rush and they were slammed.

I had a salad and the vegetables were a bit wet still, but the balsamic dressing and choice of vegetables was decent. The sweet potato yum fries were a bit cold by the time they arrived to use, but they were seasoned well and still fairly crispy.

My girlfriend had an eggs Benedict dish and I think the execution of it was fairly well done. They didn't ask for how she wanted her eggs done though, so definitely inform them if you specifically want a doneness. The other execution or weird decision was putting arugula underneath hot bacon. It was wilted, unseasoned, bitter and a bit wet. That was a fairly weird decision instead of quickly dressing it with something and putting it off to the side so it wouldn't wilt. I could understand if it was cooked or quickly tossed in a pan, but it was just raw arugula.

My absolute favourite thing here was the Danish. It was warm, just sweet enough, and had delicious blueberries on top.

Overall a good experience and definitely worth a visit if you're in Vancouver.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMnmrQb7SginX-ZnuQRw7Ox30xls5Z42hUTjFsr&fid=0x0:0x63843290b0d51c86"],"When":"2024-11-17"},{"Name":"Salicious Kim (Sally)","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocInfzvmZm95_WrqVSbcEKA0Tgk4zl4fxg9m-xCs8Eo9eA95Zg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Had an amazing time at this brunch spot! The vibe is fantastic, and the fresh fruit and veggies were a highlight. The homemade cinnamon scones were absolutely delicious! Can’t wait to come back and try their dinner menu next time!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM6C_G78w9JDmilB6xzIlq7xpWXGVJYH3I1FcJa&fid=0x0:0x63843290b0d51c86"],"When":"2024-12-18"},{"Name":"Robby","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXJ-mLrUBAdbxFI-rq7JMdzcjfcQ46QLRBeK1iakz6QSOQJV1hw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I was looking for a great place to eat since my hotel didn't have any restaurants there.  I ended up finding this little gem in Richmond. What an amazing place to eat. The food was delicious, the servers were amazing. Plus they had someone playing live music.  I definitely recommend the lobster tail fettuccine. The beef Wellington that I had the day before was delicious. Calamari was to die for. I definitely recommend this place.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN3Y3i2NiQ5Ll3-WdLWOW6lbCurWY-kZk8T8Z0r&fid=0x0:0x63843290b0d51c86"],"When":"2024-11-22"},{"Name":"Ken B.","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKi0UHEqvrtK9b7zXvBSni89V4qdFRQmlmzKuNqGFJ9iPTWGGw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Really good burger, patty was perfectly cooked, soft and juicy with a nice seared crust. Very thick portion as well. Mushrooms were good wish they added a bit more but were perfectly cooked. Bun was very good, nice quality brioche bun. Fries were perfectly cooked but wished the portion was a bit larger. Sat in the patio section, was very nice with a cool breeze and shaded. Staff were very friendly and tentative. Parking is tricky, there’s free street parking but very limited and gets filled up quick. There’s paid parking across the street for $3 for the day.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPJ0me9deJmUNU93PUsM5nFaqD92ygjHQtOHtT-&fid=0x0:0x63843290b0d51c86"],"When":"2024-7-28"},{"Name":"Brian Elliot","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW5nmQDckWv_Feg-5tMfrYNL52aqQJp-RBmsekEQHclKwYnQYxK=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Had a delicious brunch here recently so came back to try their dinner. The food did not disappoint. Everything was outstanding, exceeding expectations. In particular, the bone-in pork chop was probably one of the best I’ve ever had. My one complaint is their reservation cancellation policy - $25 per head if you cancel in less than 24 hours before your reservation. If they credited that towards your next meal that wouldn’t be so bad but this just feels like highway robbery. Sometimes things happen and you cannot make your dinner reservation. The penalty should not be so steep.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMAiu92LuOVzg7wBL0_wMs7Rh7yqCWoN6MRLpFy&fid=0x0:0x63843290b0d51c86"],"When":"2024-9-27"},{"Name":"Liu Michael","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWHubzgRvxrqGivghxc_d32W51utoPqDbWe9VZ4ufHewZxCA8BM=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Hosted a small birthday party here with my friends. The overall experience was very good.

Food ⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️:
-The appetizers were generally good, how ever the portion of the beef carpaccio was slightly disappointing.
-Clam chowder was praised by my wife and her friends!
-main courses were very delicious. The duck breast was sensational. The Beef wellington was cooked properly and had a rich mushroom flavour. Albeit the lamb rack had great flavours and was cooked to perfection, portions were lacking in terms of the price of it.

Overall a very happy experience! Would definitely try their brunch options next time!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO-vk1kLtJRHHTjuSBG59tWSqYARUOwH2OetbEp&fid=0x0:0x63843290b0d51c86"],"When":"2024-10-27"},{"Name":"Jeff Seto","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXN5eSiEJJYqhpXbvL8bGaB50DfYGUdv8NYlxsNP3x_sp8eEujrRA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Always came for brunch so first time having dinner and it was on point! Charred octopus was full of flavour and tender and the beef pappadelle was yum. Lava cake was a nice finish to a great evening. Highly recommended.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMk-V2jz6Ev71SeoA-nXD-xMls-dvB5vWXHr69o&fid=0x0:0x63843290b0d51c86"],"When":"2024-12-14"}]

title: Seahorse Grill
descriptions: Globally inspired eats from paella to pizza are offered at this cozy bistro with patio tables.

[{"Name":"Darlene Kemp","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXgwwGuFoHvNYs2Uy7o6DnrTQFssfKNuG22yRrnqcR8DXBJmDcMGg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Love this hidden gem in Crescent Beach. This unique, house style restaurant is amazing. We were greeted with a smile and seated immediately (we had a reservation, which is recommended). Our table was lovely, by the window, overlooking their outdoor seating area. The atmosphere, service and menu is great. We ordered starters (seared tuna, beef carpaccio) and they were fantastic 🙌 we all ordered different mains (surf & turf special, pallea, Lobster pot pie, vegetable gnocchi),  all were delicious and the food presentation was impressive. Our waiter was knowledgeable and gave us wine pairing recommendations as well. We will definitely come back to The Seahorse Grill and recommend it. Thank you for a lovely evening 🥰","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO_3tVI4sTwUdlgr0WWGzBe7zuTUsZD45TlihLn&fid=0x0:0xaed5de496f8de74e"],"When":"2024-6-30"},{"Name":"James Barrie","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWCxyDjM2jgIDyVPcJu7LeqXob1oe8LoyJjBFdcDvRS1RVTflG0ZA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Wonderful dinner, small venue but covid ready. The service was great- attentive and really friendly. Food was an excellent balance. I had a grilled sockeye salmon stuffed with halibut wrapped in cabbage on a garlic white wine sauce. My wife had beef short rib mashed potatoes which were so tender it melts in your mouth. Loved the flavours. Highly recommended, I'm not a "foodie" but I do like to eat!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPXoCvTwOis5QkoDD1mt_0RP-ZMmMueKj07umqX&fid=0x0:0xaed5de496f8de74e"],"When":"2021-2-6"},{"Name":"Darlene Knotts","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLD9O4_ETWF1vCl7xWTstG2UuhEyKuGKgdfXI1PCCAt2Yg_2Q=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"What a lovely little restaurant, so quaint and love setting.
Service was amazing and the food was outstanding.
We had the special NewYork steak with prawns, mashed potatoes and veggies with a Demi glaze.. Amazing! Steak had so much flavour and cooked to perfection.
We also had the brazed short ribs which was very good along with scallops that melted in your mouth.
We had lemon Tart and Lava chocolate Cake which was enjoyed by all.
We will be back for sure.. 🍷🍷","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Riya Singh","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVqWLer4LFtExAvYYx-YjWyjua4OtCIP8eVNUjf2qRXKiXHIWrkFQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Good food, good ambiance, lovely location.
Tried salmon with lemon risotto and aperol spritz.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP2H9CQp8oYJBt7y591spE2yzWbkpg8L6H6BNPf&fid=0x0:0xaed5de496f8de74e"],"When":"2024-8-10"},{"Name":"Anna Manansala","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUmPEjbEU--G6ZvwM9BF3cXB1twGAgi58wl6xVmDzsfFIrX-aN6=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"We tried accessing the glass door but were rudely stopped by the waiter; nevertheless, the waiter tried to be friendly after we ordered our meal. The lady staff, on the other hand, is very helpful.

Nice seafood, but expensive. Though thanks to my boyfriend as usual. Mwuah!

April 26 2024 🌸","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPbb500LYffYC23cp9MzFzFF0ms9A_FLwXeqNEy&fid=0x0:0xaed5de496f8de74e"],"When":"2024-5-7"},{"Name":"Sisca Gunawan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKTU--R0s_pOXpUMctBKBXVuvQ5Je7i65cJeGh1NtPNJIq6Cg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Had a wedding dinner here on a hot sunny weekend. The place was small but cozy, a bit warm no ac. Parking was a bit of a challenge since there was only street parking and there were a few events going on nearby. But Food was great. Service was good.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNUGin-DezGBMba7blRwVIo4a7TttUjus3U2dVE&fid=0x0:0xaed5de496f8de74e"],"When":"2018-8-4"},{"Name":"Sharina Grewal","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKMDBIuJcXk4lu_v45haN4xlvdpNnTNwK6q_rru91VUfIstsw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"This is a cute little place by crescent beach! We parked at the beach and walked down, extremely busy during the summer on weekends so beware of that (not the restaurant itself but the area due to the beach) it took us maybe 15 minutes to walk from the beach! We sat on the patio but the windows were open with the kitchen nearby so it was extremely hot! I’m not sure if would have been the same if we sat inside because it was quite small. The service was good she backed in a few times! And wasn’t too pushy gave us time to enjoy our food.
I’m not positive I’m not an oyster professional or anything but they just tasted off maybe cause this was later in the evening 7pm ish. They just weren’t as fresh. The paella was good my husband enjoyed it.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO2YtWCKEFwm92I3IuH9r28CdEBrZu7U6w1NNlN&fid=0x0:0xaed5de496f8de74e"],"When":"2019-8-6"},{"Name":"Graeme","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJy-SzUva4l6WZ1E2xjkKtkf3mfKbHvgq9S_xovEVn23Ss8dB0=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This is a cool, classy, and a little bit eclectic joint in Crescent Beach that's worth the drive. I recommend getting a cozy table in the back garden and going with one of the frequently changing specials. The kalamari starter is a must though. Their adaptions of dishes are creative and delish!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNGeweEFNPwrgP6U0phzNi37FboGQkMwiA9Y_FH&fid=0x0:0xaed5de496f8de74e"],"When":"2019-8-5"}]

user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Andy Chiang","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU6Ytd6jvLjiUIKjc2DLdidLuwgHbgPUD4GPhFuPOLEoqlZ2vbh=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Cool spot on Commercial Drive with a top floor patio. Generous happy hour selections and a few tasty bites. Definitely get the chips and dip as it’s delicious and a favourite of mine.

While the spot is cool, it does seem to take a bit before you get your drink orders, not sure if it’s just busy or just getting ready to start for the day.

Overall, cool spot to pass some time, grab some drinks and a quick snack with friends.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOVXFkHXH_AFgSinbhYY4HHB206PEKLYq-mlTe0&fid=0x0:0x6a66ac6b59932937"],"When":"2024-9-21"},{"Name":"June Tulips","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWBB7orQoE65U9x6vCSwo7xnatdAueK1RLu0dqZ_yIaXcmiguus=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I was looking for a nice place to have a glass (or more) of wine and a snack. This was my first visit to Social and I was not disappointed. They were able to seat me right away on the top floor. It was a very rainy cold day but they had heaters on so the window seat was still nice. I was there for happy hour, the happy hour menu was pretty extensive for both drinks and food. I ended getting the charcuterie board. The meats, cheeses and sides were fresh and delicious. The service was excellent, everyone was friendly and attentive. I look forward to returning.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNsEbcikBurLbmnf0Yj8m-9Q5kN_BhziCtzxWXn&fid=0x0:0x6a66ac6b59932937"],"When":"2024-10-21"},{"Name":"Mandy Sam","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWfdcmtmnw1QBUKzc568p_XlShrjauBmzaYnb3AklL4JCX7IFSL3g=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"We visited the establishment on a Thursday evening for their happy hour offerings. They were able to accommodate our group of five on the rooftop, which had a cozy atmosphere and a pleasant vibe. The service was great, with two attentive servers ensuring that we had everything we needed.

Regarding the culinary aspect, we decided to sample a variety of dishes, including the tuna tatake, beet salad, butternut squash ravioli, chicken sando, tuna taco, truffle fries, and the cold peanut satay noodles. While the dishes were satisfactory, they did not exceed our expectations or leave a particularly memorable impression. However, their cocktails were pretty good though. We ordered cloud 10 and the social pups.

Service, atmosphere, and drinks were great, but the food could've been better.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMhrGjSm9XiXV2PIqZ4htpUw-nKovOQ5zhOx6E8&fid=0x0:0x6a66ac6b59932937"],"When":"2024-7-28"},{"Name":"Manie Randhawa (Manie)","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX4I6oHsIGvirVrYsWWRSF7sua7bht2B5PgwM4Up3ev0g3EE_oW=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Visited this restaurant quite few times but now thought of reviewing it. First visit , we visited on a weekday so the real vibe of this place was missing. I like how the seating is arranged haphazardly in a good way. Not very luxury but fancy in its own sense. Decor is instagram able. Food is delicious and has variety in both veg & non-veg. Drinks in the bar menu are pretty straightforward. Options of cocktails available. I liked virgin ceaser and the tofu dish that I ordered.
Pretty much all dishes are very colourful. On the Weekends , you might have to wait for a table.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMd0gz9Jn8KdbYm6IZUrtjj-Euq48rfXyRSGZ7Z&fid=0x0:0x6a66ac6b59932937"],"When":"2024-11-27"},{"Name":"J Y","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVTIS8BE6DfyzEIO0AQ1m3gbjUdSWDPBmTS1KjWjpwVHsngxJ-VvA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Decided to go to Social for their happy hour and loved their patio. It reminded me so much of the patio in Miami (South Beach).

Ordered edamame and loved the sesame mayo that came with the edamame. It was so unique that I suspect they made their own mayo. It was also very big portion. Ordered cerviche which was filled with large pieces of shrimp. Very delicious. Also had their happy hour burger. Wow. A very nice burger. The bacon jam and crispy toasted bun and aioli was EXCELLENT. Would definitely come here again at to try their other food. Delicious food and great atmosphere.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMdEetxw3oLjbAmPqlKqUhk9A0vnWSESPyRbF5O&fid=0x0:0x6a66ac6b59932937"],"When":"2024-7-24"},{"Name":"Vivian","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocK5oIohR4fUBBrbBee_LLq3WUW8Q6ENGMJVFgSz8SVr8PH9Ag=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"I booked in advance for a patio seating during a sunny day for Happy Hour. When I arrived, the hostess put me in a spot where the sun was literally shining on your face. As much as I love the sun, I didn't want to potentially get a sunburn, so I asked if I could switch spot. However, she said other empty tables & booths have been reserved by other people. (I am pretty sure when you made reservation, there wasn't an option as to which table you want to sit) so I am surprised she wasn't being flexible. When asked if I could at least turned my chair the other way, she said unfortunately no, due to the spacing (perhaps the waitress might not have enough space to walk around?) but I was very certain, there would still have space.

Luckily, another server at the patio was very understanding and helped us asked the hostess again and finally we were able to move to another table before the food arrive. *Note: one of the empty tables was empty the whole time, she could have easily switch me at the beginning.

The food was pretty good for Happy Hour, I would say the price is a bit expensive. We ordered Ahi Tuna Sushi Taco, Taco with braised beef, Chicken Karaage Bao, Ravioli Prawn Trio, Chicken Wings & Social Dumplings. The highlights were: Ahi Tuna Sushi Taco, Ravioli and Chicken Wings. I would stay away from the dumplings. They felt like Costco dumplings.

The ambience was very chic and cute.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNl2O3Mr2GtlNKpL45sHiCpC3gWrQ7ApH5qagKo&fid=0x0:0x6a66ac6b59932937"],"When":"2024-5-14"},{"Name":"Crystal V","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVOrYBDfamCcGwaoc4y4YTAzbOj5CnXedrGNjEJzFa22f0CXj1f=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Overall, fantastic place. We had a reservation on the patio, which provided a cozy atmosphere. Our waitress was super kind and welcoming. The food was delicious. We took advantage of the shareables to try several of the dishes. The lychee sour is sooo good. I definitely recommend giving it a try.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMtCielUHz9Hy5Hokkqzn1N6Nzc0l6K-0f-6Qix&fid=0x0:0x6a66ac6b59932937"],"When":"2024-6-13"},{"Name":"Mila Nguyen","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJ0-BEEHIZ6OpbiIStlOE0ILSZCaWlfyUw4bby4my-gpr2Lt-4=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"We ordered the sushi tacos, chicken kaarage baos, trio shrimp ravioli, truffle fries, and chicken sando. I thought the food was mediocre. It sort of tasted like something from the freezer section. Each dish had a strange combination of flavors, and meat was dry and tough. My favorite was the shrimp ravioli. The sandwich buns were soaked from the coleslaw dressing. A very disappointing food experience. The server was friendly and attentive.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOVT5szbsndxjjYruO-3UKE0MLaaG8vUVDT_Tg_&fid=0x0:0x6a66ac6b59932937"],"When":"2024-5-1"}]

[{"Name":"Alireza Mahdian","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW0UiNNVRyZjtmU8TuMFZWagjDEpOucA4a-KVpCiuYYILJ-rcBw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Mahony's at False Creek offers a unique ambiance that's on the darker side, which some might find appealing, though it’s not to my taste. Their cocktails are a highlight—I'd highly recommend the Spicy Mango Margarita; it's exceptional.

The appetizers are decent. The wings are tasty, but the fries are pretty standard, and the nachos are just okay. Unfortunately, the main course falls short. The pizzas, especially the Meat Lovers, were overly salty and perhaps some of the worst I’ve had in Vancouver. The fish and chips were disappointingly bland, and needing to request salt for a dish is far from ideal.

Overall, I wouldn’t recommend Mahony's for the main course. However, it’s a good spot to relax and enjoy some cocktails if that’s your focus.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPB4A8OcuCRBXYpSnVSR8Dv7mWlz-ocO5DOBjwp&fid=0x0:0xfee417e217dd63e7"],"When":"2024-10-13"},{"Name":"Alex MZ","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWFAZ3nTWliK_VtSenzw4uXoch_XcB3H6HxxbxlrUtcPTBIKY4A=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"A well located branch of a chain restaurant in Vancouver. This place has a beautiful patio which is lovely to dine in Summer time and enjoying the view. Besides of location, food and service is good. Spinach dip was so good. Calamari was so-so. Live music is performed in some weekend I guess, better to call and check.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP2P_NgF2gS3QjuC0ex_msLtNPjerc7ok1-Ke1I&fid=0x0:0xfee417e217dd63e7"],"When":"2024-11-24"},{"Name":"Tay Cun","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVISvV4V-lNqhgBJaNaxP5l32SM4_qpYYBDmmefTcVji7eDYTQz=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"The food is delicious and portion sizes are decent.
They are pet friendly which is a plus although the pet friendly seating is right at the exit of the False Creek Ferry so it does get a little hectic.
We were entertaining family visiting from abroad and had a great time. It was a great spot for eats before hopping on the ferry to Granville Island.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMwTbG6b-2Vo4kXu2vbVX0mLPJq7M62VKG-5xpm&fid=0x0:0xfee417e217dd63e7"],"When":"2024-8-8"},{"Name":"Lizzie G","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIs7GuwCphNV7dZ0l4sPc3kyk134hdt-GN0zf6584QBAaeg3IuS=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Super cute spot! Would recommend for their patio on the water. Our server was so kind and the pretzel bites and calamari were tasty! I wish the pretzel bites came with cheese instead of the honey mustard but it hit the spot.

Great pit stop for some apps while on our bike ride.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMf_aokPJhzocD8ofeNeNnO5PfsJI9vQXUfYSm_&fid=0x0:0xfee417e217dd63e7"],"When":"2024-9-3"},{"Name":"Rachel","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV9HyW9EjTjpSgeCCza_X2_Hl91YZJNAaxmckSbsx6fdmko2g8=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Lovely spot along the water. We were outside for the view. The sun hits pretty strongly in the evening regardless of the sun shade, but I still would’ve sat outside. The food was terrific, appetizers and meal, as was the seasonal beer I tried. They are very doggo friendly with water bowls at every table on the patio. Would definitely go back again.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOmJ9NMkxKyV0s-sSg4wcwSRwcCu_jqM-8f1G8w&fid=0x0:0xfee417e217dd63e7"],"When":"2024-9-5"},{"Name":"Joey Lam","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIncJBLfbVzRO24PRdfxE4-hovZn6C_s4RV_vqsGslULP8YEA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"We live close by and have been here a few times. Their food is good and the patio is one of the best in the summer.

Today, we were only here to watch the COPA third place match between Canada 🇨🇦 and Uruguay 🇺🇾. I was a bit surprised to see not many people and staff seemed to care about the match. We were placed at the bar with a small TV in front of us. It almost felt like private area for us; however, it lacked of the atmosphere of a sports pub. Seemed like the staff only cared if we would have another drink.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO32VPVePp7ptRzdrUFo7dsbzy3f05Pjma9klW0&fid=0x0:0xfee417e217dd63e7"],"When":"2024-7-21"},{"Name":"Alexis desloges","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUJYQj6LpCMziVYo3OUFRBQqqDtPhJlHOg8jlUwtFMDsEnodl3W=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Simply put it is an epic view of downtown. This is one of the place where I like bringing my friends from out of town. Obviously for the view from its terrace right on the water. The service is always great there. It is a bite pricy for what you get food wise, but on a sunny day the view and its atmosphere vastly compensate.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNNUtagZLtsRrf4U9ycgs4qSdT4Xrsbg_1Aec60&fid=0x0:0xfee417e217dd63e7"],"When":"2024-7-13"},{"Name":"June Tulips","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWBB7orQoE65U9x6vCSwo7xnatdAueK1RLu0dqZ_yIaXcmiguus=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I've walked by many times, and today I finally visited! The view off the patio was beautiful, the food was yummy, and the service was great. The aqua taxi was just below so very convenient as well.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP-qytsJxZjjnwV4WsUkLWD9s8mBV5FKV4uPi5o&fid=0x0:0xfee417e217dd63e7"],"When":"2024-6-23"}]
